    "upload_date": "20180309",
    "duration": 90,
    "view_count": 281,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.72, \"end\": 8.66, \"text\": \"A scary situation in Bremerton, Washington was caught on camera.\"}, {\"start\": 8.66, \"end\": 16.5, \"text\": \"A woman was getting ready to leave her home when she noticed a man running down the street,\"}, {\"start\": 16.5, \"end\": 18.76, \"text\": \"heading towards her truck.\"}, {\"start\": 18.76, \"end\": 21.86, \"text\": \"Her child was inside the truck.\"}, {\"start\": 21.86, \"end\": 29.08, \"text\": \"When she walked to the passenger side, the man jumped in the driver's seat and try to\"}, {\"start\": 29.08, \"end\": 31.3, \"text\": \"steal the vehicle.\"}, {\"start\": 31.3, \"end\": 35.66, \"text\": \"The mother clung to the door, trying to stop him.\"}, {\"start\": 35.66, \"end\": 40.02, \"text\": \"She tried to pull him out but he slapped and hit her.\"}, {\"start\": 40.02, \"end\": 48.36, \"text\": \"Authorities say the man threatened to kill them as he tried to drive away, but he crashed\"}, {\"start\": 48.36, \"end\": 52.72, \"text\": \"into a concrete retaining wall with the woman clinging to the side of the truck.\"}, {\"start\": 52.72, \"end\": 54.7, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 82.6, \"end\": 89.46, \"text\": \"The man eventually took off on foot but police caught up with him and arrested him.\"}]"
  },
  "Y7p6Y2ky-iI": {
    "video_id": "Y7p6Y2ky-iI",
    "title": "Facebook overhauls privacy settings, tools (ASL - 3.28.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180329",
    "duration": 60,
    "view_count": 160,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.92, \"end\": 4.9, \"text\": \"Facebook is changing its privacy settings.\"}, {\"start\": 4.9, \"end\": 14.96, \"text\": \"The changes are as a result of the data breach by Cambridge Analytica.\"}, {\"start\": 14.96, \"end\": 21.44, \"text\": \"Facebook says the new security settings will let users decide what personal information\"}, {\"start\": 21.44, \"end\": 27.44, \"text\": \"Facebook and third-party apps keep.\"}, {\"start\": 27.44, \"end\": 40.48, \"text\": \"Facebook is also adding a privacy shortcuts menu, where people can control the ads they receive.\"}, {\"start\": 40.48, \"end\": 48.96, \"text\": \"There will also be a new access your information button which allows people to delete anything\"}, {\"start\": 48.96, \"end\": 54.4, \"text\": \"from their timelines or profiles that they no longer want on Facebook.\"}, {\"start\": 54.4, \"end\": 59.68, \"text\": \"The changes will be rolling out in a few weeks.\"}]"
  },
  "--6bmFM9wT4": {
    "video_id": "--6bmFM9wT4",
    "title": "5.25.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180526",
    "duration": 630,
    "view_count": 1065,
    "description": "5.25.18 - \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Tropical Storm could develop in the gulf this week\n-Harvey Weinstein surrenders\n-Shots fired in Indiana middle school, suspect in custody\n-“Dancing doctor” faces multiple malpractice lawsuits\n-NTSB recommends seat belts on school buses\n-Pregnant cat’s priceless reaction \n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds from notable organizations such as GALLAUDET UNIVERSITY, CNN, FOX, ABC, CBS, TB",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 6.32, \"end\": 7.44, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 7.44, \"end\": 10.02, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.02, \"end\": 11.22, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 11.22, \"end\": 14.5, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 16.84, \"end\": 25.42, \"text\": \"We are about a week away from the start of the 2018 Atlantic hurricane season and the\"}, {\"start\": 25.42, \"end\": 31.32, \"text\": \"tropics are already stirring.\"}, {\"start\": 31.32, \"end\": 36.78, \"text\": \"This is a look at \\\"Invest 90-L.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 36.8, \"end\": 48.62, \"text\": \"The National Hurricane Center says there is a 90 percent chance Invest 90-L could develop\"}, {\"start\": 48.62, \"end\": 59.94, \"text\": \"into a subtropical or tropical depression over the next five days.\"}, {\"start\": 59.94, \"end\": 65.74, \"text\": \"And there's even a chance it could develop into a named storm.\"}, {\"start\": 65.74, \"end\": 77.4, \"text\": \"So if you have Memorial Day plans anywhere from Louisiana to Southwest Florida, you'll\"}, {\"start\": 77.4, \"end\": 83.26, \"text\": \"want to keep an eye on this.\"}, {\"start\": 83.26, \"end\": 95.68, \"text\": \"Scientists predict this Atlantic hurricane season will be less severe than last year\"}, {\"start\": 95.68, \"end\": 103.28, \"text\": \"with possibly 10 to 16 storms, four of which could become hurricanes.\"}, {\"start\": 103.28, \"end\": 115.36, \"text\": \"2017 was particularly active with six major hurricanes including hurricanes Harvey, Irma\"}, {\"start\": 115.36, \"end\": 118.84, \"text\": \"and Maria.\"}, {\"start\": 122.38, \"end\": 135.18, \"text\": \"Disgraced filmmaker Harvey Weinstein walked into the New York City Police Department on\"}, {\"start\": 135.18, \"end\": 137.02, \"text\": \"Friday morning and turned himself in to authorities.\"}, {\"start\": 137.02, \"end\": 148.2, \"text\": \"He is charged with first and third degree rape and committing a criminal sex act involving\"}, {\"start\": 148.2, \"end\": 151.98, \"text\": \"two separate women.\"}, {\"start\": 151.98, \"end\": 163.82, \"text\": \"In the statement, the NYPD thanked the brave survivors for their courage to come forward\"}, {\"start\": 163.82, \"end\": 165.97, \"text\": \"and seek justice.\"}, {\"start\": 165.97, \"end\": 178.52, \"text\": \"Weinstein later appeared in New York County Supreme Court for a bond hearing, where prosecutors\"}, {\"start\": 178.52, \"end\": 188.46, \"text\": \"alleged he used his position, money and power to lure young women into situations where\"}, {\"start\": 188.46, \"end\": 191.4, \"text\": \"he was able to violate them sexually.\"}, {\"start\": 191.4, \"end\": 205.96, \"text\": \"He pleaded not guilty and still maintains that any sexual activity he engaged in was consensual.\"}, {\"start\": 205.96, \"end\": 212.68, \"text\": \"The judge set his bond at $10 million.\"}, {\"start\": 212.68, \"end\": 224.5, \"text\": \"One of the first women to publicly accuse Weinstein of assault was actress Rose McGowan.\"}, {\"start\": 224.5, \"end\": 236.26, \"text\": \"She released a statement on Instagram saying \\\"I, and so many of Harvey Weinstein's survivors,\"}, {\"start\": 236.26, \"end\": 240.52, \"text\": \"had given up hope that our rapists would be held accountable by law.\"}, {\"start\": 240.52, \"end\": 246.46, \"text\": \"Twenty years ago I swore that I would right this wrong.\"}, {\"start\": 246.46, \"end\": 250.92, \"text\": \"Today we are one step closer to justice.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 254.38, \"end\": 264.22, \"text\": \"Police in Indiana say at 9:06 AM Friday morning an active shooter 911 call came in from Noblesville\"}, {\"start\": 264.22, \"end\": 267.92, \"text\": \"West middle school.\"}, {\"start\": 267.92, \"end\": 276.72, \"text\": \"Several local and state law enforcement agencies quickly converged at the school.\"}, {\"start\": 276.72, \"end\": 285.06, \"text\": \"Thirty minutes later a male student was taken into custody in a classroom.\"}, {\"start\": 285.06, \"end\": 292.72, \"text\": \"Investigators are not releasing his name or age, which indicates he may be a minor.\"}, {\"start\": 292.72, \"end\": 305.24, \"text\": \"They say he asked for permission to leave the classroom and returned with two handguns.\"}, {\"start\": 305.24, \"end\": 312.22, \"text\": \"Three people were hurt -- two adults and one student -- but no information was provided\"}, {\"start\": 312.22, \"end\": 317.58, \"text\": \"as to how they were injured.\"}, {\"start\": 317.58, \"end\": 325.28, \"text\": \"Investigators say it will take days to process the crime scene and question the suspect and\"}, {\"start\": 325.28, \"end\": 331.44, \"text\": \"witnesses to determine a motive for the shooting.\"}, {\"start\": 337.12, \"end\": 350.59, \"text\": \"This is Atlanta-area dermatologist Dr. Windell Boutte on video singing and dancing in the\"}, {\"start\": 350.59, \"end\": 352.68, \"text\": \"middle of surgery.\"}, {\"start\": 352.68, \"end\": 361.12, \"text\": \"According to Headline News more than 20 videos like this one were posted to the doctor's\"}, {\"start\": 361.12, \"end\": 366.8, \"text\": \"public YouTube channel for promotional purposes.\"}, {\"start\": 366.8, \"end\": 377.34, \"text\": \"They have since been deleted but patients have taken notice and now she is facing several\"}, {\"start\": 377.34, \"end\": 380.34, \"text\": \"malpractice lawsuits.\"}, {\"start\": 380.42, \"end\": 394.18, \"text\": \"Female patients claim they've suffered infections, facial disfigurement, even brain damage following\"}, {\"start\": 394.18, \"end\": 396.6, \"text\": \"procedures with Boutte.\"}, {\"start\": 396.6, \"end\": 403.94, \"text\": \"The lawsuits claim she's unqualified to do many of the procedure she advertises.\"}, {\"start\": 403.94, \"end\": 412.84, \"text\": \"The Georgia Composite Medical Board has had information regarding Boutte's allegedly unsafe\"}, {\"start\": 412.84, \"end\": 423.66, \"text\": \"practices since at least March 20 of 2016 but because a final ruling is not been decided,\"}, {\"start\": 423.66, \"end\": 428.64, \"text\": \"Boutte continues to perform procedures.\"}, {\"start\": 428.64, \"end\": 438.46, \"text\": \"Boutte's office and her attorneys did not respond to Headline News' request for comment.\"}, {\"start\": 442.34, \"end\": 448.38, \"text\": \"The National Transportation Safety Board is recommending seatbelts be used on all new\"}, {\"start\": 448.38, \"end\": 453.34, \"text\": \"school buses across the country.\"}, {\"start\": 453.34, \"end\": 466.18, \"text\": \"The NTSB is basing its findings on two crashes in 2016 -- one in Tennessee and the other\"}, {\"start\": 466.18, \"end\": 475.44, \"text\": \"in Maryland that left a total of 12 people dead and 37 injured.\"}, {\"start\": 475.44, \"end\": 490.6, \"text\": \"Currently only eight states require some type of restraint for students on buses.\"}, {\"start\": 490.6, \"end\": 506.26, \"text\": \"And four of those states are urged by the NTSB to upgrade from lap belts to shoulder belts.\"}, {\"start\": 506.26, \"end\": 511.52, \"text\": \"This recommendation also comes less than a week after a deadly school bus crash in New\"}, {\"start\": 511.52, \"end\": 521.0, \"text\": \"Jersey that left one student and one teacher dead.\"}, {\"start\": 521.0, \"end\": 531.92, \"text\": \"The bus driver, 77-year-old Hudy Muldrow, Sr, appeared in court today.\"}, {\"start\": 531.92, \"end\": 537.44, \"text\": \"He's charged with vehicular homicide.\"}, {\"start\": 540.86, \"end\": 551.5, \"text\": \"A cat named Ulla in Greenland gets an ultrasound and finds out she's pregnant.\"}, {\"start\": 551.5, \"end\": 558.4, \"text\": \"But it's her reaction that is going viral!\"}, {\"start\": 558.4, \"end\": 569.76, \"text\": \"The expression seems to say \\\"OMG! You've got to be kidding me?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 569.76, \"end\": 578.08, \"text\": \"The pictures were posted on Reddit with the caption \\\"When you find out you're pregnant.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 578.08, \"end\": 586.22, \"text\": \"The pictures were taken by the animal shelter in Greenland that conducted the ultrasound.\"}, {\"start\": 586.24, \"end\": 595.92, \"text\": \"And if that wasn't enough big news for Ulla, she's also been adopted!\"}, {\"start\": 598.88, \"end\": 602.04, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 602.04, \"end\": 604.06, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 604.06, \"end\": 607.66, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 607.66, \"end\": 614.24, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 614.24, \"end\": 616.72, \"text\": \"Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 616.72, \"end\": 618.52, \"text\": \"Your life.\"}, {\"start\": 618.52, \"end\": 621.8, \"text\": \"Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "JZmNueMInnk": {
    "video_id": "JZmNueMInnk",
    "title": "Sign1News 3.14.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180315",
    "duration": 448,
    "view_count": 919,
    "description": "3.14.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-National school walkouts all over the world\n-Atlanta Area Deaf students walkout\n-Dog dies in airplane overhead bin\n-Stephen Hawking dies at age 76\n-Ford recalls 1.4M cars, steering wheel can come off\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to loca",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.06, \"end\": 9.62, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.62, \"end\": 11.86, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 11.86, \"end\": 13.34, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 13.34, \"end\": 17.24, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.86, \"end\": 24.7, \"text\": \"This morning students around the world staged walkouts.\"}, {\"start\": 24.78, \"end\": 38.12, \"text\": \"At 10 AM in each local time zone, students, parents and supporters of all ages showed\"}, {\"start\": 38.12, \"end\": 40.36, \"text\": \"solidarity for the 17 people killed in Parkland, Florida one month ago.\"}, {\"start\": 40.36, \"end\": 44.82, \"text\": \"Here are some of the images from around the country and the world.\"}, {\"start\": 44.96, \"end\": 53.86, \"text\": \"For students at Marjory Stoneman Douglas high school, the walkout was their way of demanding\"}, {\"start\": 53.86, \"end\": 61.08, \"text\": \"gun law change and to honor their fallen friends.\"}, {\"start\": 61.08, \"end\": 71.48, \"text\": \"In Los Angeles, students walked out to the football field and spelled out #ENOUGH.\"}, {\"start\": 71.48, \"end\": 79.88, \"text\": \"In New York students held a 17 minute silent lie-in/sit-in.\"}, {\"start\": 79.88, \"end\": 87.48, \"text\": \"In Washington DC students held a silent protest by turning their backs to the White House.\"}, {\"start\": 87.48, \"end\": 93.72, \"text\": \"This protest actually went global.\"}, {\"start\": 93.72, \"end\": 100.88, \"text\": \"Students in Israel showed their support by walking out and holding up a sign that read\"}, {\"start\": 100.88, \"end\": 103.29, \"text\": \"\\\"Let this be the last one.\"}, {\"start\": 103.29, \"end\": 106.4, \"text\": \"We stand with you.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 106.4, \"end\": 112.98, \"text\": \"And in Tanzania a little girl holds up a sign that says #ENOUGH.\"}, {\"start\": 114.56, \"end\": 125.78, \"text\": \"In Atlanta the students at Atlanta Area School for the Deaf sent a strong message and showed\"}, {\"start\": 125.78, \"end\": 129.66, \"text\": \"their support by walking out at exactly 10 AM.\"}, {\"start\": 129.66, \"end\": 134.52, \"text\": \"Student leaders encouraged their classmates to hold up their hands up in addition to holding\"}, {\"start\": 134.52, \"end\": 137.2, \"text\": \"up signs.\"}, {\"start\": 137.2, \"end\": 141.38, \"text\": \"The sign displayed powerful messages.\"}, {\"start\": 141.38, \"end\": 148.34, \"text\": \"One sign read \\\"Are we next?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 148.34, \"end\": 157.34, \"text\": \"One young girl stuck her head through a big sign with a bull's-eye painted on it.\"}, {\"start\": 157.34, \"end\": 159.54, \"text\": \"The message read \\\"Don't shoot!\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 159.54, \"end\": 167.56, \"text\": \"Another sign simply read \\\"We are students. We are victims.  We are change.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 169.68, \"end\": 175.06, \"text\": \"We want to warn you: some of the images in this story may be disturbing.\"}, {\"start\": 175.06, \"end\": 183.04, \"text\": \"A dog died on a United airlines flight Monday after a flight attendant forced the owner\"}, {\"start\": 183.04, \"end\": 189.12, \"text\": \"to put the pet's carrier in an overhead compartment.\"}, {\"start\": 189.12, \"end\": 197.62, \"text\": \"Catalina Robledo was flying from Houston to New York, a four hour flight.\"}, {\"start\": 197.62, \"end\": 204.24, \"text\": \"She says she paid to bring her dog Kokito on board but the flight attendant would not\"}, {\"start\": 204.24, \"end\": 207.88, \"text\": \"let her keep the dog on the floor.\"}, {\"start\": 207.88, \"end\": 214.599, \"text\": \"After putting Kokito in the overhead bin, Robledo said she could hear the dog barking\"}, {\"start\": 214.6, \"end\": 217.34, \"text\": \"and barking.\"}, {\"start\": 217.34, \"end\": 220.36, \"text\": \"Then it stopped.\"}, {\"start\": 220.36, \"end\": 225.72, \"text\": \"When she opened the overhead bin, this is what she saw.\"}, {\"start\": 225.72, \"end\": 229.16, \"text\": \"Robledo posted this picture of her dead dog on her Facebook page.\"}, {\"start\": 229.16, \"end\": 237.04, \"text\": \"United Airlines issued a statement, calling the death a tragic accident.\"}, {\"start\": 237.04, \"end\": 245.32, \"text\": \"A spokesperson for the airline said the flight attendant should not have made Robledo put\"}, {\"start\": 245.32, \"end\": 250.0, \"text\": \"the dog in the bin for carry-on bags.\"}, {\"start\": 250.0, \"end\": 256.7, \"text\": \"United says it will pay for the dog's necropsy and is investigating the matter to prevent\"}, {\"start\": 256.7, \"end\": 259.12, \"text\": \"it from happening again.\"}, {\"start\": 259.12, \"end\": 269.62, \"text\": \"A report from the US Department of Transportation says 24 pets died on US planes in 2017.\"}, {\"start\": 269.62, \"end\": 278.32, \"text\": \"Eighteen of those pets were on United flights.\"}, {\"start\": 281.2, \"end\": 288.52, \"text\": \"Acclaimed British physicist Stephen Hawking has died.\"}, {\"start\": 288.52, \"end\": 293.82, \"text\": \"He was wildly considered the world's greatest living scientist.\"}, {\"start\": 293.82, \"end\": 301.1, \"text\": \"For more than 30 years he was a professor at Cambridge University, specializing in the\"}, {\"start\": 301.1, \"end\": 304.28, \"text\": \"study of black holes.\"}, {\"start\": 304.28, \"end\": 313.48, \"text\": \"He theorized space and time began with the \\\"Big Bang\\\" and space and time will end in\"}, {\"start\": 313.48, \"end\": 315.86, \"text\": \"black holes.\"}, {\"start\": 315.86, \"end\": 336.14, \"text\": \"Hawking's book \\\"A Brief History of Time\\\" explained astrophysics in simple terms and sold more\"}, {\"start\": 336.14, \"end\": 339.92, \"text\": \"than 10 million copies.\"}, {\"start\": 339.92, \"end\": 345.72, \"text\": \"It is considered one of the best-selling science books ever written.\"}, {\"start\": 345.72, \"end\": 353.7, \"text\": \"Hawking lived with ALS (Lou Gehrig's disease) since 1963.\"}, {\"start\": 353.7, \"end\": 362.64, \"text\": \"He spent much of his time confined to a wheelchair and relying on a speech synthesizer to speak\"}, {\"start\": 362.64, \"end\": 365.1, \"text\": \"for him.\"}, {\"start\": 365.1, \"end\": 370.04, \"text\": \"Hawking was 76 years old when he died.\"}, {\"start\": 371.32, \"end\": 382.4, \"text\": \"If you drive a Ford Fusion or Lincoln MKZS, we have an important recall tell you about.\"}, {\"start\": 382.4, \"end\": 394.02, \"text\": \"Ford is recalling 1.4 million vehicles because a bolt can come loose on the steering wheel\"}, {\"start\": 394.02, \"end\": 396.32, \"text\": \"and, in some cases, cause it to detach while driving.\"}, {\"start\": 396.32, \"end\": 410.48, \"text\": \"The affected models are for Fusions and Lincoln MKZS from 2014 to 2018.\"}, {\"start\": 410.48, \"end\": 418.02, \"text\": \"The automaker says two accidents due to the malfunction have already been reported.\"}, {\"start\": 420.38, \"end\": 423.34, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 423.34, \"end\": 424.74, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 424.74, \"end\": 427.44, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 427.44, \"end\": 432.74, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 432.74, \"end\": 441.18, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "Bawbmhprvqs": {
    "video_id": "Bawbmhprvqs",
    "title": "“Black Panther” rises and falls in one weekend (ASL - 3.25.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180326",
    "duration": 131,
    "view_count": 149,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.84, \"end\": 11.54, \"text\": \"The movie \\\"Black Panther\\\" is now the top grossing superhero film of all-time in North America.\"}, {\"start\": 11.54, \"end\": 25.38, \"text\": \"According to the Hollywood Reporter, \\\"Black Panther\\\" passed 2012's \\\"The Avengers\\\" Saturday\"}, {\"start\": 25.38, \"end\": 28.98, \"text\": \"to become number one all-time in the superhero genre.\"}, {\"start\": 28.98, \"end\": 35.68, \"text\": \"And Variety reports that the film should reach the $630 million mark at the US box office\"}, {\"start\": 35.68, \"end\": 39.48, \"text\": \"this weekend.\"}, {\"start\": 39.48, \"end\": 50.22, \"text\": \"That would make the film the fifth highest grossing movie in US history behind just \\\"Star\"}, {\"start\": 50.22, \"end\": 66.2, \"text\": \"Wars: The Force Awakens,\\\" \\\"Avatar,\\\" \\\"Titanic\\\" and \\\"Jurassic World.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 66.2, \"end\": 74.56, \"text\": \"Globally, \\\"Black Panther\\\" has made more than $1.2 billion to date.\"}, {\"start\": 74.56, \"end\": 84.64, \"text\": \"But this weekend \\\"Black Panther's\\\" five week streak at number one at the box office came\"}, {\"start\": 84.64, \"end\": 88.16, \"text\": \"to an end.\"}, {\"start\": 88.16, \"end\": 104.66, \"text\": \"\\\"Pacific Rim Uprising\\\" is now the number one movie in the country, bringing in about $28 million.\"}, {\"start\": 104.66, \"end\": 111.32, \"text\": \"\\\"Black Panther\\\" slipped to number two, bringing in $17 million.\"}, {\"start\": 111.32, \"end\": 125.06, \"text\": \"The number three spot went to the faith-based film \\\"I Can Only Imagine,\\\" which earned $13.9\"}, {\"start\": 125.06, \"end\": 127.66, \"text\": \"million in its second weekend.\"}]"
  },
  "favoQ0F6Q0U": {
    "video_id": "favoQ0F6Q0U",
    "title": "Update: GVRA cancels policy change on Gallaudet/NTID (ASL - 3.8.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180309",
    "duration": 90,
    "view_count": 56,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.88, \"end\": 16.18, \"text\": \"Yesterday we told you about the Georgia Vocational Rehabilitation Agency's proposed policy change\"}, {\"start\": 16.18, \"end\": 27.2, \"text\": \"that would have removed Gallaudet University and the National Technical Institute for the\"}, {\"start\": 27.2, \"end\": 28.74, \"text\": \"Deaf from its list of approved schools for college funding.\"}, {\"start\": 28.74, \"end\": 36.24, \"text\": \"The policy change would have impacted thousands of Deaf and hard-of-hearing students across\"}, {\"start\": 36.24, \"end\": 38.44, \"text\": \"the state.\"}, {\"start\": 38.44, \"end\": 45.1, \"text\": \"The Deaf community was prepared to show up in masses to protest the policy change.\"}, {\"start\": 45.1, \"end\": 59.62, \"text\": \"But today GVRA Executive Director Sean Casey released this statement.\"}, {\"start\": 59.62, \"end\": 65.8, \"text\": \"It says he has listened to the heartfelt concerns about the change.\"}, {\"start\": 65.8, \"end\": 71.88, \"text\": \"As a result Casey says he's revoking the proposed policy change effective immediately.\"}, {\"start\": 71.88, \"end\": 84.56, \"text\": \"This means every student currently enrolled at Gallaudet or NTID, plus future applicants,\"}, {\"start\": 84.56, \"end\": 87.74, \"text\": \"will have the opportunity to pursue their education with no changes to services and\"}, {\"start\": 87.8, \"end\": 89.68, \"text\": \"tuition assistance.\"}]"
  },
  "IW98HansqCk": {
    "video_id": "IW98HansqCk",
    "title": "Sign1News 10.29.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171030",
    "duration": 406,
    "view_count": 246,
    "description": "October 29, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-PUERTO RICO GOVERNOR CANCELS WHITEFISH CONTRACT\n-5TH ANNIVERSARY OF SUPERSTORM SANDY\n-ESCAPED PRISONER CAPTURED IN TEXAS  \n-TWO WOMEN RESCUED AFTER 5 MONTHS AT SEA  \n-IPHONE 10 SCREEN REPAIRS WILL COST $275  \n-WEEKEND BOX OFFICE \n-IT'S NATIONAL CAT DAY\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds from notable",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.0, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 14.0, \"text\": \"And here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 17.0, \"end\": 22.0, \"text\": \"The governor of Puerto Rico wants to cancel the contract with\"}, {\"start\": 22.0, \"end\": 27.0, \"text\": \"Whitefish immediately. Whitefish is a small\"}, {\"start\": 27.0, \"end\": 32.0, \"text\": \"Montana utility company that was hired for $300 million dollars\"}, {\"start\": 32.0, \"end\": 37.0, \"text\": \"to help Puerto Rico restore power on the island.\"}, {\"start\": 37.0, \"end\": 42.0, \"text\": \"It's been a month since Hurricane Maria hit the island and\"}, {\"start\": 42.0, \"end\": 47.0, \"text\": \"70 percent of the country is still without power. Governor Ricardo\"}, {\"start\": 47.0, \"end\": 52.0, \"text\": \"Rossello has now brought in a review\"}, {\"start\": 52.0, \"end\": 58.0, \"text\": \"board to figure out how Whitefish was given the contract in the first place.\"}, {\"start\": 58.0, \"end\": 62.0, \"text\": \"Whitefish is based in the hometown of\"}, {\"start\": 62.0, \"end\": 68.0, \"text\": \"U.S. Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke\"}, {\"start\": 68.0, \"end\": 72.0, \"text\": \"and that has raised concerns about how the company got the contract.\"}, {\"start\": 73.0, \"end\": 76.0, \"text\": \"But Zinke says he had nothing to do with the contract.\"}, {\"start\": 77.0, \"end\": 82.0, \"text\": \"Rossello says he is now working with governors in New York and Florida\"}, {\"start\": 83.0, \"end\": 88.0, \"text\": \"to bring energy workers from those states to help Puerto Rico as quickly as possible.\"}, {\"start\": 90.0, \"end\": 95.0, \"text\": \"Today marks the five year anniversary of Superstorm\"}, {\"start\": 96.0, \"end\": 100.0, \"text\": \"Sandy hitting New Jersey and New York.\"}, {\"start\": 100.0, \"end\": 107.0, \"text\": \"Sandy caused tens of billions of dollars in damage\"}, {\"start\": 107.0, \"end\": 111.0, \"text\": \"and killed about 150 people in the Caribbean,\"}, {\"start\": 111.0, \"end\": 116.0, \"text\": \"U.S. and Canada. And it looks like another big storm\"}, {\"start\": 116.0, \"end\": 122.0, \"text\": \"will lash the northeast tonight into Monday morning.\"}, {\"start\": 122.0, \"end\": 126.0, \"text\": \"This storm is named Phillipe.\"}, {\"start\": 128.0, \"end\": 133.0, \"text\": \"Wednesday morning jail officials in West Virginia say a prisoner named\"}, {\"start\": 133.0, \"end\": 138.0, \"text\": \"Todd Wayne Boyes disguised himself as\"}, {\"start\": 138.0, \"end\": 142.0, \"text\": \"a civilian and walked out of jail.\"}, {\"start\": 143.0, \"end\": 148.0, \"text\": \"Jail staff didn't realize he was gone until\"}, {\"start\": 148.0, \"end\": 153.0, \"text\": \"36 hours later. Boyes escaped a few days\"}, {\"start\": 153.0, \"end\": 158.0, \"text\": \"before he would have been sentenced to three to 20 years in prison.\"}, {\"start\": 158.0, \"end\": 163.0, \"text\": \"Officials say Boyes made it all the way to\"}, {\"start\": 163.0, \"end\": 167.0, \"text\": \"Laredo Texas before he was finally caught and\"}, {\"start\": 167.0, \"end\": 172.0, \"text\": \"placed back behind bars. Last year he pleaded guilty\"}, {\"start\": 172.0, \"end\": 177.0, \"text\": \"to fleeing from police after a carjacking and a car chase with officers.\"}, {\"start\": 180.0, \"end\": 185.0, \"text\": \"Two women and their dogs were finally rescued after being stranded\"}, {\"start\": 185.0, \"end\": 190.0, \"text\": \"at sea for five months. They were supposed to sail across\"}, {\"start\": 190.0, \"end\": 195.0, \"text\": \"the Pacific Ocean from Hawaii to Tahiti.\"}, {\"start\": 196.0, \"end\": 201.0, \"text\": \"But a month into the trip they hit turbulence at sea.\"}, {\"start\": 201.0, \"end\": 206.0, \"text\": \"The boat was badly damaged. The mast broke\"}, {\"start\": 207.0, \"end\": 211.0, \"text\": \"and the engine shut off. They veered so far off course\"}, {\"start\": 212.0, \"end\": 216.0, \"text\": \"no one could hear their distress calls.\"}, {\"start\": 216.0, \"end\": 221.0, \"text\": \"And sharks were starting to circle their boat. Five months\"}, {\"start\": 221.0, \"end\": 226.0, \"text\": \"passed by. The women feared\"}, {\"start\": 226.0, \"end\": 229.0, \"text\": \"they would never be found.\"}, {\"start\": 229.0, \"end\": 234.0, \"text\": \"But miraculously a fishing vessel sailed by and spotted them.\"}, {\"start\": 234.0, \"end\": 239.0, \"text\": \"The fishermen contacted the U.S. Coast Guard and the women were rescued.\"}, {\"start\": 239.0, \"end\": 243.0, \"text\": \"The women say they were able to stay alive for five months\"}, {\"start\": 244.0, \"end\": 249.0, \"text\": \"because they brought water purifiers\"}, {\"start\": 249.0, \"end\": 253.0, \"text\": \"and a year's worth of food with them.\"}, {\"start\": 255.0, \"end\": 260.0, \"text\": \"If you decided to buy Apple's fancy new iPhone 10\"}, {\"start\": 260.0, \"end\": 265.0, \"text\": \"make sure you also invest in a case and a screen protector.\"}, {\"start\": 265.0, \"end\": 268.0, \"text\": \"That's because if the screen breaks it will cost you\"}, {\"start\": 268.0, \"end\": 273.0, \"text\": \"$275 to fix it. That's nearly $100 more than\"}, {\"start\": 273.0, \"end\": 278.0, \"text\": \"repairs for the iPhone 8 Plus.\"}, {\"start\": 278.0, \"end\": 283.0, \"text\": \"If you've purchased the extended warranty the\"}, {\"start\": 284.0, \"end\": 289.0, \"text\": \"repair price comes down a bit. However the third time will\"}, {\"start\": 289.0, \"end\": 293.0, \"text\": \"raise your repair cost significantly.\"}, {\"start\": 296.0, \"end\": 300.0, \"text\": \"Movies with scary themes swept the box office this\"}, {\"start\": 300.0, \"end\": 305.0, \"text\": \"Halloween weekend. The top spot went to the horror\"}, {\"start\": 305.0, \"end\": 310.0, \"text\": \"flick Jigsaw. It raked in more than\"}, {\"start\": 310.0, \"end\": 314.0, \"text\": \"60 million dollars. At number two the\"}, {\"start\": 315.0, \"end\": 320.0, \"text\": \"Tyler Perry comedy\"}, {\"start\": 320.024, \"end\": 327.924, \"text\": \"Boo Two A Madea Halloween.\"}, {\"start\": 328.0, \"end\": 333.0, \"text\": \"The comedy is expected to bring in about 10 million dollars.\"}, {\"start\": 333.0, \"end\": 338.0, \"text\": \"And at number three Geostorm, a sci-fi thriller about\"}, {\"start\": 338.0, \"end\": 346.0, \"text\": \"a global weather disaster. It's expected to pull in about 5.7 million dollars this weekend.\"}, {\"start\": 349.024, \"end\": 351.999, \"text\": \"Pet owners are encouraged to celebrate\"}, {\"start\": 352.0, \"end\": 357.0, \"text\": \"the cat in their lives. Today October 29th\"}, {\"start\": 357.0, \"end\": 362.0, \"text\": \"is National Cat Day. The day was established to recognize\"}, {\"start\": 362.0, \"end\": 367.0, \"text\": \"the number of cats that need to be rescued. But if it feels like we just celebrated\"}, {\"start\": 367.0, \"end\": 371.0, \"text\": \"our feline friends, you're right. October 16th was global cat day\"}, {\"start\": 371.0, \"end\": 374.0, \"text\": \"and it focused on\"}, {\"start\": 374.024, \"end\": 378.024, \"text\": \"policies to protect cats.\"}, {\"start\": 381.0, \"end\": 385.0, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today. I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 385.0, \"end\": 387.0, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 387.024, \"end\": 392.099, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 392.1, \"end\": 398.1, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "nQlx2P5wxvk": {
    "video_id": "nQlx2P5wxvk",
    "title": "Three deadly packages explode in Texas neighborhoods (ASL - 3.12.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180313",
    "duration": 66,
    "view_count": 253,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.08, \"end\": 10.36, \"text\": \"Law enforcement agencies in Austin, Texas have issued an emergency public safety alert.\"}, {\"start\": 10.36, \"end\": 16.64, \"text\": \"Three package bombs have exploded over the last 10 days and investigators believe they\"}, {\"start\": 16.64, \"end\": 21.36, \"text\": \"are somehow connected.\"}, {\"start\": 21.36, \"end\": 32.26, \"text\": \"In all three incidents, the victims picked up a strange package left on their doorstep,\"}, {\"start\": 32.26, \"end\": 33.97, \"text\": \"then it exploded.\"}, {\"start\": 33.97, \"end\": 44.4, \"text\": \"The last two explosions happened this morning within hours and a few blocks of each other.\"}, {\"start\": 44.4, \"end\": 47.96, \"text\": \"The first blast happened on March 2.\"}, {\"start\": 47.96, \"end\": 49.9, \"text\": \"One person was killed.\"}, {\"start\": 49.9, \"end\": 53.44, \"text\": \"Two others were critically injured.\"}, {\"start\": 53.44, \"end\": 61.66, \"text\": \"Until the person or persons responsible is caught, police are urging residents not to\"}, {\"start\": 61.66, \"end\": 66.12, \"text\": \"touch or open any unexpected packages and to call 911 immediately.\"}]"
  },
  "5OyIQChN5DA": {
    "video_id": "5OyIQChN5DA",
    "title": "Sign1News 10.16.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171017",
    "duration": 558,
    "view_count": 255,
    "description": "October 16, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-CALIFORNIA FIREFIGTHERS MAKING PROGRESS\n-MAN FINDS OUT FAMILY DOG SURVIVED FIRE\n-SPAIN WILDFIRES\n-OPHELIA BRINGS HURRICANE-FORCE WINDS\n-EERIE ORANGE SKY OVER LONDON\n-TRUMP HOLDS CABINET MEETING\n-ALYSSA MILANO STARTS ‘#METOO' MOVEMENT\n-PANDA CUBS MAKE THEIR DEBUT\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds fr",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.0, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 15.0, \"text\": \"Candace Jones. Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 18.0, \"end\": 23.0, \"text\": \"We have good news and bad news to report about the\"}, {\"start\": 23.0, \"end\": 28.0, \"text\": \"California wildfires. First the bad news.\"}, {\"start\": 29.0, \"end\": 34.0, \"text\": \"Unfortunately the death toll has risen to 40 people\"}, {\"start\": 34.0, \"end\": 38.0, \"text\": \"dead.  More than 200 people are\"}, {\"start\": 38.0, \"end\": 42.0, \"text\": \"still missing. Now the good news.\"}, {\"start\": 43.0, \"end\": 48.0, \"text\": \"Mandatory evacuation orders have\"}, {\"start\": 49.0, \"end\": 53.0, \"text\": \"been lifted in some areas. A few people are\"}, {\"start\": 53.0, \"end\": 58.0, \"text\": \"being allowed to return home.\"}, {\"start\": 58.0, \"end\": 63.0, \"text\": \"Fire officials say they feel confident they\"}, {\"start\": 63.0, \"end\": 67.0, \"text\": \"are making progress in putting\"}, {\"start\": 68.0, \"end\": 70.0, \"text\": \"the fires out.\"}, {\"start\": 74.0, \"end\": 79.0, \"text\": \"It was a joyous reunion for one California couple and their dog.\"}, {\"start\": 80.0, \"end\": 84.0, \"text\": \"The couple had to evacuate their home because of the\"}, {\"start\": 84.0, \"end\": 89.0, \"text\": \"fires. Their dog Izzy got scared\"}, {\"start\": 90.0, \"end\": 92.0, \"text\": \"and ran off.\"}, {\"start\": 92.0, \"end\": 97.0, \"text\": \"When the flames died down the couple went back\"}, {\"start\": 98.0, \"end\": 104.0, \"text\": \"to look for the dog. They called the dog's name several times.\"}, {\"start\": 104.0, \"end\": 108.0, \"text\": \"Lo and behold the dog came running out from the rubble\"}, {\"start\": 108.0, \"end\": 112.0, \"text\": \"unharmed.\"}, {\"start\": 112.0, \"end\": 115.0, \"text\": \"Now the couple says Izzy\"}, {\"start\": 116.0, \"end\": 120.0, \"text\": \"refuses to leave their side.\"}, {\"start\": 120.0, \"end\": 125.0, \"text\": \"She follows them every\"}, {\"start\": 125.0, \"end\": 126.0, \"text\": \"where they go.\"}, {\"start\": 129.0, \"end\": 134.0, \"text\": \"California is not the only region\"}, {\"start\": 134.0, \"end\": 139.0, \"text\": \"battling wildfires. Check out this massive fire.\"}, {\"start\": 139.0, \"end\": 143.0, \"text\": \"Fires are raging across northern\"}, {\"start\": 143.0, \"end\": 148.0, \"text\": \"Portugal and are spreading into Spain's\"}, {\"start\": 148.0, \"end\": 155.0, \"text\": \"northwest Galicia region.\"}, {\"start\": 155.0, \"end\": 159.0, \"text\": \"At least 35 people have been killed in both\"}, {\"start\": 159.0, \"end\": 164.0, \"text\": \"countries combined. Many others are\"}, {\"start\": 164.0, \"end\": 169.0, \"text\": \"reported injured or missing.\"}, {\"start\": 169.0, \"end\": 174.0, \"text\": \"More than 600 members of the Spanish armed\"}, {\"start\": 174.0, \"end\": 178.0, \"text\": \"forces are fighting the wildfires.\"}, {\"start\": 178.0, \"end\": 182.0, \"text\": \"Authorities in Portugal and Spain say\"}, {\"start\": 183.0, \"end\": 188.0, \"text\": \"they're trying to figure out how the fire started.\"}, {\"start\": 189.0, \"end\": 197.0, \"text\": \"They're thinking weather conditions played a major role.\"}, {\"start\": 199.0, \"end\": 203.0, \"text\": \"Last night Hurricane Ophelia was\"}, {\"start\": 203.0, \"end\": 208.0, \"text\": \"downgraded to a tropical\"}, {\"start\": 208.0, \"end\": 212.0, \"text\": \"storm. But that doesn't mean the storm has weakened.\"}, {\"start\": 213.0, \"end\": 218.0, \"text\": \"Today in Ireland, the United Kingdom and Scotland\"}, {\"start\": 219.0, \"end\": 224.0, \"text\": \"there was strong wind and heavy rain.\"}, {\"start\": 224.0, \"end\": 229.0, \"text\": \"Currently the storm has maximum sustained winds\"}, {\"start\": 229.0, \"end\": 232.0, \"text\": \"of 85 miles per hour.\"}, {\"start\": 232.0, \"end\": 237.0, \"text\": \"Ophelia has knocked out power to more than\"}, {\"start\": 237.0, \"end\": 241.0, \"text\": \"120,000 homes and businesses as it\"}, {\"start\": 242.0, \"end\": 247.0, \"text\": \"moves through. The Irish weather service issued\"}, {\"start\": 247.0, \"end\": 251.0, \"text\": \"a red severe weather warning and\"}, {\"start\": 252.0, \"end\": 257.0, \"text\": \"urged people to remain indoors and to stay away\"}, {\"start\": 257.0, \"end\": 259.0, \"text\": \"from coastal areas.\"}, {\"start\": 262.0, \"end\": 266.0, \"text\": \"In London several people looked up\"}, {\"start\": 268.0, \"end\": 271.0, \"text\": \"to see an orange colored sky.\"}, {\"start\": 271.0, \"end\": 276.0, \"text\": \"Forecasters say Ophelia is\"}, {\"start\": 276.0, \"end\": 281.0, \"text\": \"bringing very strong winds from the south.\"}, {\"start\": 281.0, \"end\": 286.0, \"text\": \"The winds are mixed with\"}, {\"start\": 286.0, \"end\": 290.0, \"text\": \"desert dust and smoke\"}, {\"start\": 290.0, \"end\": 294.0, \"text\": \"from Portugal's fires.\"}, {\"start\": 296.0, \"end\": 301.0, \"text\": \"All those particles in the atmosphere turned the sun's light to a weird\"}, {\"start\": 301.0, \"end\": 307.0, \"text\": \"shade of orange and red.\"}, {\"start\": 309.001, \"end\": 312.001, \"text\": \"Today President Trump\"}, {\"start\": 312.1, \"end\": 317.1, \"text\": \"met with his cabinet. They discussed\"}, {\"start\": 317.1, \"end\": 321.1, \"text\": \"several topics including healthcare reform,\"}, {\"start\": 322.0, \"end\": 329.0, \"text\": \"tax reform and welfare reform.\"}, {\"start\": 329.001, \"end\": 331.001, \"text\": \"The meeting comes as\"}, {\"start\": 332.0, \"end\": 337.0, \"text\": \"the Trump administration struggles to pass legislation\"}, {\"start\": 337.0, \"end\": 342.0, \"text\": \"through Congress despite Republicans controlling\"}, {\"start\": 342.0, \"end\": 349.0, \"text\": \"both the House and the Senate.\"}, {\"start\": 349.001, \"end\": 352.001, \"text\": \"Earlier this year Trump\"}, {\"start\": 352.1, \"end\": 357.1, \"text\": \"failed to pass healthcare reform. Currently he's\"}, {\"start\": 357.1, \"end\": 361.1, \"text\": \"working to pass tax reform legislation but not\"}, {\"start\": 363.0, \"end\": 367.0, \"text\": \"with much success. Now President Trump\"}, {\"start\": 368.0, \"end\": 374.0, \"text\": \"says he will start to consider reforming the nation's\"}, {\"start\": 374.0, \"end\": 378.0, \"text\": \"welfare system. He says too many\"}, {\"start\": 379.0, \"end\": 383.0, \"text\": \"people are not receiving what they need\"}, {\"start\": 383.0, \"end\": 388.0, \"text\": \"to live while others are taking advantage of the welfare system.\"}, {\"start\": 391.24, \"end\": 392.99, \"text\": \"On Sunday actress\"}, {\"start\": 393.0, \"end\": 399.0, \"text\": \"Alyssa Milano started a social media\"}, {\"start\": 399.0, \"end\": 403.0, \"text\": \"protest. The protest is a result of a growing\"}, {\"start\": 404.0, \"end\": 409.0, \"text\": \"number of sex abuse allegations against film producer Harvey Weinstein.\"}, {\"start\": 409.0, \"end\": 412.0, \"text\": \"On Twitter Milano posted\"}, {\"start\": 413.0, \"end\": 418.0, \"text\": \"\\\"If all the women who have been\"}, {\"start\": 418.0, \"end\": 423.0, \"text\": \"sexually harassed or assaulted wrote\"}, {\"start\": 424.0, \"end\": 429.0, \"text\": \"'Me Too' we might give people a sense of the\"}, {\"start\": 430.0, \"end\": 435.0, \"text\": \"magnitude of the problem. Hash tag 'Me Too'\"}, {\"start\": 435.0, \"end\": 440.0, \"text\": \"quickly started trending on Twitter and\"}, {\"start\": 440.0, \"end\": 444.0, \"text\": \"other celebrities started supporting Milano. Celebrities like\"}, {\"start\": 444.0, \"end\": 448.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga, Patricia\"}, {\"start\": 450.0, \"end\": 458.0, \"text\": \"Arquette and Rosario Dawson.\"}, {\"start\": 464.0, \"end\": 466.0, \"text\": \"In China\"}, {\"start\": 466.0, \"end\": 468.0, \"text\": \"a conservation center\"}, {\"start\": 468.0, \"end\": 472.0, \"text\": \"debuts not one,\"}, {\"start\": 473.0, \"end\": 478.0, \"text\": \"not two but 36 new\"}, {\"start\": 478.0, \"end\": 483.0, \"text\": \"panda cubs. All the cubs were born in 2017 but\"}, {\"start\": 483.0, \"end\": 488.0, \"text\": \"vary in age and size. It is the largest number\"}, {\"start\": 489.0, \"end\": 494.0, \"text\": \"of births in a single year since the breeding program began.\"}, {\"start\": 494.0, \"end\": 498.0, \"text\": \"These baby pandas\"}, {\"start\": 498.0, \"end\": 501.0, \"text\": \"will help increase the panda population\"}, {\"start\": 501.0, \"end\": 506.0, \"text\": \"over the next several years. The adorable creatures\"}, {\"start\": 506.0, \"end\": 514.0, \"text\": \"are in danger of being wiped out.\"}, {\"start\": 514.0, \"end\": 518.0, \"text\": \"Each cub could potentially be reintroduced\"}, {\"start\": 518.0, \"end\": 523.0, \"text\": \"into the wild at a later time and hopefully will start breeding\"}, {\"start\": 523.0, \"end\": 528.0, \"text\": \"on their own.\"}, {\"start\": 531.0, \"end\": 536.0, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today. I am Candace Jones. Thank you\"}, {\"start\": 537.0, \"end\": 543.0, \"text\": \"for watching Sign1News. Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 543.0, \"end\": 549.0, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "QNBWZrjumaA": {
    "video_id": "QNBWZrjumaA",
    "title": "Sign1News 2.6.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180207",
    "duration": 480,
    "view_count": 891,
    "description": "2.6.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).  \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Another government shutdown looming?\n-Most powerful rocket in the world launched\n-Prince Harry, Meghan Markle movie casted\n-Bud Light is buying Philly a beer!\n-French fry chemicals may cure baldness\n-Should you try souping?\n-Kylie Jenner reveals baby's name\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in Ameri",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 6.08, \"end\": 7.12, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 7.2, \"end\": 9.38, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 9.38, \"end\": 10.74, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 10.74, \"end\": 13.34, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 14.82, \"end\": 22.84, \"text\": \"It is been 15 days since the last government shutdown and now Washington is staring down\"}, {\"start\": 22.84, \"end\": 28.16, \"text\": \"the barrel of another potential stalemate in just 48 hours.\"}, {\"start\": 28.16, \"end\": 36.8, \"text\": \"Money is set to run out on Thursday and once again Congress is struggling to strike a last-minute\"}, {\"start\": 36.8, \"end\": 38.34, \"text\": \"deal.\"}, {\"start\": 38.34, \"end\": 46.02, \"text\": \"The House wants to pass another short-term bill to fund the government through March\"}, {\"start\": 46.02, \"end\": 48.44, \"text\": \"23rd.\"}, {\"start\": 48.44, \"end\": 57.08, \"text\": \"But Republicans blame Democrats for the failure to reach a long-term agreement because they\"}, {\"start\": 57.08, \"end\": 67.26, \"text\": \"want an agreement added to the bill that protects so-called \\\"dreamers\\\" from possible deportation.\"}, {\"start\": 67.26, \"end\": 73.92, \"text\": \"The House bill also includes full defense funding which could make it difficult for\"}, {\"start\": 73.92, \"end\": 79.34, \"text\": \"Senate Democrats to vote down.\"}, {\"start\": 79.34, \"end\": 86.6, \"text\": \"Senate Democrats will demand significant changes to the House bill but appear, at this point,\"}, {\"start\": 86.64, \"end\": 90.62, \"text\": \"to be on board with beefing up military funding.\"}, {\"start\": 93.0, \"end\": 101.82, \"text\": \"The most powerful rocket on the planet made its debut launch Tuesday afternoon.\"}, {\"start\": 101.82, \"end\": 104.48, \"text\": \"It's called \\\"Falcon Heavy.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 104.48, \"end\": 120.92, \"text\": \"The rockets thrust is nearly as strong as 20 Boeing 747 jetliners and could someday\"}, {\"start\": 120.92, \"end\": 124.58, \"text\": \"be able to take passengers to Mars.\"}, {\"start\": 124.58, \"end\": 135.8, \"text\": \"Space-X founder Elon Musk says exploring outerspace has been a longtime goal.\"}, {\"start\": 135.8, \"end\": 148.36, \"text\": \"Falcon Heavy will now start hauling satellites and other space items into orbit.\"}, {\"start\": 148.36, \"end\": 154.62, \"text\": \"Musk says the rockets could be used by the US government as well.\"}, {\"start\": 154.62, \"end\": 161.0, \"text\": \"The price tag for each Falcon Heavy launch is $90 million.\"}, {\"start\": 162.74, \"end\": 171.06, \"text\": \"Lifetime has cast Parisa Fitz-Henley and Murray Fraser in the title roles for the movie \\\"Harry\"}, {\"start\": 171.14, \"end\": 174.8, \"text\": \"and Meghan: A Royal Romance.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 174.8, \"end\": 179.94, \"text\": \"Fitz-Henley is best known for her role in Marvel's \\\"Jessica Jones\\\" on Netflix.\"}, {\"start\": 179.94, \"end\": 202.98, \"text\": \"And Fraser starred in the British miniseries \\\"The Loch\\\" and \\\"Victoria.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 202.98, \"end\": 209.9, \"text\": \"Vanity Fair reports production begins this week.\"}, {\"start\": 209.9, \"end\": 218.12, \"text\": \"The movie is set to air this spring before Prince Harry and Markle's May 19th wedding.\"}, {\"start\": 220.18, \"end\": 228.02, \"text\": \"Bud Light is about to make good on a very bold Super Bowl bet.\"}, {\"start\": 228.02, \"end\": 235.08, \"text\": \"Last summer Eagles lineman Lane Johnson promised beer for Philly fans if the Eagles won it\"}, {\"start\": 235.08, \"end\": 239.439, \"text\": \"all.\"}, {\"start\": 239.44, \"end\": 249.38, \"text\": \"The promise was made during an ESPN.com interview.\"}, {\"start\": 249.38, \"end\": 254.42, \"text\": \"Bud Light stepped in and promised to foot the bill.\"}, {\"start\": 254.42, \"end\": 261.31, \"text\": \"So on Thursday, during the city's victory parade, fans 21 and older can pick up a free\"}, {\"start\": 261.31, \"end\": 264.24, \"text\": \"beer along the parade route.\"}, {\"start\": 264.24, \"end\": 270.44, \"text\": \"Bud Light also proclaimed the parade day \\\"Philly Philly Day.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 272.78, \"end\": 283.1, \"text\": \"French fries may not be good for your waistline but it may be perfect for your hairline.\"}, {\"start\": 283.1, \"end\": 290.66, \"text\": \"Japanese scientists say they have found a new treatment for hair loss.\"}, {\"start\": 290.66, \"end\": 297.86, \"text\": \"According to a paper published in the journal \\\"Biomaterials,\\\" scientists were able to re-grow\"}, {\"start\": 297.86, \"end\": 306.0, \"text\": \"hair on mice using the method.\"}, {\"start\": 306.0, \"end\": 315.57, \"text\": \"The method uses the same type of silicon used by some fast food restaurants.\"}, {\"start\": 315.57, \"end\": 322.7, \"text\": \"Silicon is often added to french fries to prevent frothing or foaming.\"}, {\"start\": 322.7, \"end\": 334.92, \"text\": \"And that chemical helped the scientists mass-produce hair follicle germs -- a key ingredient in\"}, {\"start\": 334.98, \"end\": 338.76, \"text\": \"hair growth.\"}, {\"start\": 338.8, \"end\": 344.32, \"text\": \"Preliminary research suggests the same method will be just as successful when it's used\"}, {\"start\": 344.32, \"end\": 345.84, \"text\": \"on people.\"}, {\"start\": 347.68, \"end\": 357.08, \"text\": \"If you've hit a snag with your New Year's weight loss goal, there's a new trend worth trying.\"}, {\"start\": 357.08, \"end\": 365.04, \"text\": \"\\\"Souping\\\" has become more popular with people trying to shed a few pounds.\"}, {\"start\": 365.04, \"end\": 368.4, \"text\": \"So what's the slimming secret of soup?\"}, {\"start\": 368.4, \"end\": 381.9, \"text\": \"According to a professor of nutritional sciences at Penn State, binding water into food helps\"}, {\"start\": 381.9, \"end\": 385.9, \"text\": \"keep your stomach fuller for longer.\"}, {\"start\": 385.9, \"end\": 396.54, \"text\": \"Unlike juicing, souping can help stabilize blood sugar for more sustained energy.\"}, {\"start\": 396.54, \"end\": 404.16, \"text\": \"Plus the water in soup adds weight and volume so that you can have a satisfying amount without\"}, {\"start\": 404.16, \"end\": 406.76, \"text\": \"all the unwanted calories.\"}, {\"start\": 409.56, \"end\": 415.56, \"text\": \"Kylie Jenner gave birth to a baby girl last week.\"}, {\"start\": 415.56, \"end\": 420.46, \"text\": \"Today she announced the name of her baby on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 420.46, \"end\": 422.44, \"text\": \"Her name is \\\"Stormi.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 422.44, \"end\": 430.84, \"text\": \"Jenner did not publicly identify the father though she's been dating rapper Travis Scott.\"}, {\"start\": 430.84, \"end\": 437.96, \"text\": \"Jenner kept her pregnancy under wraps for months.\"}, {\"start\": 437.96, \"end\": 451.24, \"text\": \"But sources close to the Kardashians revealed in September that she was expecting.\"}, {\"start\": 453.28, \"end\": 455.56, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 455.56, \"end\": 457.22, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 457.22, \"end\": 459.54, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 459.54, \"end\": 464.74, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 464.86, \"end\": 471.28, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "5LX2paqf91Y": {
    "video_id": "5LX2paqf91Y",
    "title": "Sign1News 11.10.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171111",
    "duration": 511,
    "view_count": 428,
    "description": "November 10, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-LOUIE C.K. SAYS SEXUAL MISCONDUCT CLAIMS ARE TRUE\n-AARON HERNANDEZ BRAIN SCANS RELEASED\n-TRUMP ARRIVES AT APEC SUMMIT IN VIETNAM\n-PUERTO RICO POWER FAILURE\n-TWIN PEAKS TRIAL DEADLOCKED JURY\n-MOTORCYCLISTS ATTACK SEATTLE DRIVER\n-AMAZON POP-UP SHOPS IN WHOLE FOODS\n-LITTLE DEBBIE MARKETING PLOY\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.0, \"end\": 11.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 14.0, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 16.0, \"end\": 20.0, \"text\": \"Comedian Louie C.K. released a statement today\"}, {\"start\": 20.0, \"end\": 24.0, \"text\": \"admitting to accusations of sexual misconduct.\"}, {\"start\": 24.0, \"end\": 29.0, \"text\": \"He also says he's deeply remorseful for his behavior. His confession comes after\"}, {\"start\": 29.0, \"end\": 34.0, \"text\": \"a New York Times article in which five women\"}, {\"start\": 34.0, \"end\": 41.0, \"text\": \"accused C-K of inappropriate behavior including exposing himself in front of them.\"}, {\"start\": 41.0, \"end\": 47.0, \"text\": \"The scandal has affected C-K's ties with several companies.\"}, {\"start\": 48.0, \"end\": 53.0, \"text\": \"The movie company The Orchard's announced\"}, {\"start\": 53.0, \"end\": 58.0, \"text\": \"that the release of his new movie \\\"I Love You Daddy\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 58.0, \"end\": 61.0, \"text\": \"has been canceled.\"}, {\"start\": 62.0, \"end\": 67.0, \"text\": \"C.K. won't be appearing in an upcoming HBO autism\"}, {\"start\": 67.0, \"end\": 71.0, \"text\": \"benefit. And Netflix is scrapping plans for another\"}, {\"start\": 71.0, \"end\": 73.0, \"text\": \"standup special with him.\"}, {\"start\": 76.0, \"end\": 81.0, \"text\": \"Researchers at Boston University CTE center have released the\"}, {\"start\": 81.0, \"end\": 85.0, \"text\": \"brain scan of former NFL player\"}, {\"start\": 86.0, \"end\": 90.0, \"text\": \"Aaron Hernandez.\"}, {\"start\": 90.0, \"end\": 93.0, \"text\": \"Doctors say he had the worst case of chronic\"}, {\"start\": 94.0, \"end\": 99.0, \"text\": \"traumatic encephalopathy\"}, {\"start\": 99.0, \"end\": 104.0, \"text\": \"they have seen in a person so young.\"}, {\"start\": 104.024, \"end\": 106.024, \"text\": \"Hernandez was found to have stage three CTE\"}, {\"start\": 107.0, \"end\": 113.0, \"text\": \"and he was just 27 years old. Stage 4 is the most serious form.\"}, {\"start\": 113.0, \"end\": 117.0, \"text\": \"Researchers believe the condition is caused by repeated\"}, {\"start\": 117.0, \"end\": 123.0, \"text\": \"head trauma like tackles in football.\"}, {\"start\": 123.0, \"end\": 128.0, \"text\": \"The degenerative disease can only be diagnosed by\"}, {\"start\": 128.0, \"end\": 131.0, \"text\": \"examining the brain of a patient after death.\"}, {\"start\": 131.0, \"end\": 136.0, \"text\": \"Hernandez was serving a life sentence for\"}, {\"start\": 136.0, \"end\": 141.0, \"text\": \"murder at the time of his death.\"}, {\"start\": 141.0, \"end\": 143.0, \"text\": \"Hernandez hanged himself seven months ago.\"}, {\"start\": 144.0, \"end\": 148.0, \"text\": \"Doctors say they could not definitely connect the disease to\"}, {\"start\": 148.0, \"end\": 153.0, \"text\": \"Hernandez's behavior but pointed out CTE often affects judgment and\"}, {\"start\": 153.0, \"end\": 158.0, \"text\": \"emotions. Hernandez's family has filed a lawsuit\"}, {\"start\": 158.0, \"end\": 164.0, \"text\": \"against the NFL, accusing the league of hiding the dangers of head trauma.\"}, {\"start\": 167.0, \"end\": 172.0, \"text\": \"President Trump is on the fourth day of his tour of Asia.\"}, {\"start\": 172.0, \"end\": 177.0, \"text\": \"He attended the APEC summit in Da Nang, Vietnam, along with\"}, {\"start\": 177.0, \"end\": 182.0, \"text\": \"some of the world's most powerful political and business leaders.\"}, {\"start\": 182.0, \"end\": 186.0, \"text\": \"Trump is pushing his message of America first while at the same time\"}, {\"start\": 187.0, \"end\": 191.0, \"text\": \"trying to strengthen trade ties.\"}, {\"start\": 192.0, \"end\": 196.0, \"text\": \"He says the U.S. will no longer tolerate unfair trade practices that he\"}, {\"start\": 196.0, \"end\": 201.0, \"text\": \"believes takes advantage of America.\"}, {\"start\": 204.0, \"end\": 207.0, \"text\": \"Electrical crews in Puerto Rico had a major setback\"}, {\"start\": 207.0, \"end\": 212.0, \"text\": \"yesterday. There was a massive power outage\"}, {\"start\": 212.0, \"end\": 217.0, \"text\": \"in San Juan. Power across the island\"}, {\"start\": 217.0, \"end\": 222.0, \"text\": \"dropped from more than 40 percent down to only 18 percent.\"}, {\"start\": 222.0, \"end\": 228.0, \"text\": \"Puerto Rico's electric power authority said the failure was\"}, {\"start\": 228.0, \"end\": 233.0, \"text\": \"caused by a mechanical failure. By Friday morning, power was restored to 38 percent.\"}, {\"start\": 233.0, \"end\": 237.0, \"text\": \"Much of Puerto Rico has been without power since\"}, {\"start\": 237.0, \"end\": 242.0, \"text\": \"Hurricane Maria slammed into the island on September 20th.\"}, {\"start\": 245.0, \"end\": 252.0, \"text\": \"We have an update to a story we told you about yesterday.\"}, {\"start\": 252.0, \"end\": 256.0, \"text\": \"Bandidos biker gang leader Jake\"}, {\"start\": 257.0, \"end\": 262.0, \"text\": \"Carrizal is on trial for his involvement\"}, {\"start\": 262.0, \"end\": 267.0, \"text\": \"in the deadly gun battle between a rival gang at a\"}, {\"start\": 267.0, \"end\": 271.0, \"text\": \"Twin Peaks bar in Waco Texas. Nine people died.\"}, {\"start\": 273.0, \"end\": 277.0, \"text\": \"After 12 hours of deliberation the jury\"}, {\"start\": 277.0, \"end\": 282.0, \"text\": \"told the judge that they are deadlocked\"}, {\"start\": 282.0, \"end\": 287.0, \"text\": \"on two of the three charges.\"}, {\"start\": 287.0, \"end\": 293.0, \"text\": \"They can't seem to all agree on Carrizal's guilt or his innocence.\"}, {\"start\": 294.0, \"end\": 301.0, \"text\": \"It was not revealed what the one charge was they did agree on.\"}, {\"start\": 302.0, \"end\": 306.0, \"text\": \"The judge encouraged the jurors to continue deliberating\"}, {\"start\": 306.0, \"end\": 310.0, \"text\": \"hoping they will all come to a consensus.\"}, {\"start\": 310.0, \"end\": 315.0, \"text\": \"If the jurors find themselves deadlocked again the judge may declare\"}, {\"start\": 316.0, \"end\": 320.0, \"text\": \"a mistrial, which could lead to an entirely new trial.\"}, {\"start\": 323.0, \"end\": 326.0, \"text\": \"Back in August police in Seattle say a driver was attacked\"}, {\"start\": 326.0, \"end\": 333.0, \"text\": \"by a group of motorcyclists.\"}, {\"start\": 333.024, \"end\": 338.024, \"text\": \"Now there is a new lead in the case.\"}, {\"start\": 338.025, \"end\": 342.025, \"text\": \"Police just discovered the GoPro video of the attack.\"}, {\"start\": 343.0, \"end\": 346.0, \"text\": \"The attack happened during The Bomb Squad\"}, {\"start\": 346.0, \"end\": 351.0, \"text\": \"Takeover. That's when riders from all over the country\"}, {\"start\": 351.0, \"end\": 356.0, \"text\": \"converge on Seattle. The driver said dozens of riders\"}, {\"start\": 356.0, \"end\": 361.0, \"text\": \"pulled up beside him. They started popping wheelies and banging on his truck.\"}, {\"start\": 361.0, \"end\": 366.0, \"text\": \"When he got to the stop light the driver said the riders opened his door and\"}, {\"start\": 366.0, \"end\": 371.0, \"text\": \"someone punched him in the face. The driver said while he was fighting back\"}, {\"start\": 371.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"another rider put a gun to his head and that's\"}, {\"start\": 377.0, \"end\": 382.0, \"text\": \"when everybody scattered. Police are hoping that this video\"}, {\"start\": 382.024, \"end\": 385.024, \"text\": \"will help them identify the suspects.\"}, {\"start\": 388.0, \"end\": 392.0, \"text\": \"Amazon purchased Whole Foods this summer\"}, {\"start\": 392.024, \"end\": 395.024, \"text\": \"for more than 30 million dollars.\"}, {\"start\": 396.0, \"end\": 399.0, \"text\": \"Today Amazon announced it will open five\"}, {\"start\": 400.0, \"end\": 403.0, \"text\": \"pop up stores next week at Whole Foods locations in Illinois, Colorado,\"}, {\"start\": 403.001, \"end\": 406.001, \"text\": \"Michigan,  Florida\"}, {\"start\": 406.1, \"end\": 413.1, \"text\": \"and California.\"}, {\"start\": 413.2, \"end\": 418.2, \"text\": \"The pop up stores allow customers to test Amazon products\"}, {\"start\": 418.224, \"end\": 421.224, \"text\": \"and learn more about services\"}, {\"start\": 421.3, \"end\": 426.3, \"text\": \"like Amazon Prime membership.\"}, {\"start\": 428.0, \"end\": 432.0, \"text\": \"Snack maker Little Debbie\"}, {\"start\": 432.024, \"end\": 436.024, \"text\": \"has created a bit of a stir on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 436.3, \"end\": 441.3, \"text\": \"The company hinted that one of its popular treats will soon be gone forever.\"}, {\"start\": 442.0, \"end\": 445.0, \"text\": \"On Wednesday the company posted an image on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 445.0, \"end\": 450.0, \"text\": \"It showed four of its sweet snacks:\"}, {\"start\": 450.0, \"end\": 455.0, \"text\": \"Christmas Tree Cakes, Nutty Buddies,\"}, {\"start\": 455.024, \"end\": 459.024, \"text\": \"Oatmeal Creme Pies\"}, {\"start\": 459.048, \"end\": 462.048, \"text\": \"and Honey Buns.\"}, {\"start\": 462.072, \"end\": 468.072, \"text\": \"The post included the message: One gotta go forever. Which one?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 469.0, \"end\": 474.0, \"text\": \"Later the company admitted they posted the tweet\"}, {\"start\": 474.001, \"end\": 478.001, \"text\": \"just to get people talking about their favorite snack.\"}, {\"start\": 478.1, \"end\": 482.1, \"text\": \"So snacks fan don't worry. It was just a marketing ploy\"}, {\"start\": 483.0, \"end\": 487.0, \"text\": \"and there are no plans to get rid of any products.\"}, {\"start\": 490.0, \"end\": 493.0, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today. I am Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 493.024, \"end\": 495.024, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 495.048, \"end\": 498.048, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 498.072, \"end\": 504.072, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "3-8fEGeDfK4": {
    "video_id": "3-8fEGeDfK4",
    "title": "Nor’easter round 2 (ASL - 3.7.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180308",
    "duration": 56,
    "view_count": 50,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.7, \"end\": 7.76, \"text\": \"For the second time in a week a nor'easter is dumping snow across parts of the East Coast.\"}, {\"start\": 7.76, \"end\": 15.16, \"text\": \"More than 50 million people from Maryland to Maine are under winter storm warnings and watches.\"}, {\"start\": 15.22, \"end\": 18.74, \"text\": \"And more than 2,000 flights have been canceled.\"}, {\"start\": 18.74, \"end\": 22.64, \"text\": \"Many companies are sending their employees home early.\"}, {\"start\": 22.64, \"end\": 27.58, \"text\": \"Transportation officials say if you don't have to be on the road, stay home.\"}, {\"start\": 27.58, \"end\": 38.82, \"text\": \"Officials in Massachusetts say they've had to use drones to assess beach damage because\"}, {\"start\": 38.88, \"end\": 43.3, \"text\": \"of the continuous high tides.\"}, {\"start\": 43.3, \"end\": 51.1, \"text\": \"Some residents are now in a race against time to rebuild the seawall to protect their homes\"}, {\"start\": 51.16, \"end\": 54.84, \"text\": \"from the storm surge.\"}]"
  },
  "AZ_YIyaMbV4": {
    "video_id": "AZ_YIyaMbV4",
    "title": "Sign1News 2.18.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180219",
    "duration": 574,
    "view_count": 924,
    "description": "2.18.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).  \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Weekend box office: \"Black Panther\" breaks records\n-Let's discuss: superhero sign for \"Black Panther\"\n-Memorial for Florida school shooting victims\n-Teens express outrage\n-Family of victims fly free to Florida\n-Police investigate massive brawl on cruise ship\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in Ame",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.16, \"end\": 9.7, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.7, \"end\": 12.2, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 12.2, \"end\": 13.72, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 13.72, \"end\": 16.7, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.56, \"end\": 30.14, \"text\": \"\\\"Black Panther\\\" is number one at the weekend box office and it shattered a number of records\"}, {\"start\": 30.14, \"end\": 33.72, \"text\": \"along the way.\"}, {\"start\": 33.72, \"end\": 44.7, \"text\": \"The movie brought in an estimated $192 million, which breaks the record for a debut in February.\"}, {\"start\": 44.8, \"end\": 60.76, \"text\": \"It is also the second biggest opening for a Marvel Studios film, behind 2012's \\\"The\"}, {\"start\": 60.76, \"end\": 63.42, \"text\": \"Avengers.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 63.42, \"end\": 76.32, \"text\": \"\\\"Black Panther\\\" is Marvel's first film directed by an African-American.\"}, {\"start\": 76.32, \"end\": 88.98, \"text\": \"And movie experts say the film's record-breaking weekend could impact change in Hollywood by\"}, {\"start\": 88.98, \"end\": 100.56, \"text\": \"encouraging diversity in front of and behind the camera.\"}, {\"start\": 104.18, \"end\": 112.54, \"text\": \"The popularity of the film \\\"Black Panther\\\" has caused a big discussion in the deaf community.\"}, {\"start\": 112.54, \"end\": 122.46, \"text\": \"What is the official superhero sign for \\\"Black Panther?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 122.46, \"end\": 143.08, \"text\": \"\\\"America's Next Top Model\\\" star and deaf activist Nyle DiMarco and \\\"Children of a Lesser God\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 143.08, \"end\": 149.28, \"text\": \"Broadway star Lauren Ridloff recently released a video on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 149.28, \"end\": 153.34, \"text\": \"They say the sign for \\\"Black Panther\\\" is this...\"}, {\"start\": 156.86, \"end\": 171.46, \"text\": \"The black deaf community disagrees.\"}, {\"start\": 171.46, \"end\": 180.9, \"text\": \"The sign DiMarco uses is for an animal and the concept is not appropriate for the movie.\"}, {\"start\": 180.9, \"end\": 190.4, \"text\": \"But there are three sign suggestions that are gaining popularity on social media and\"}, {\"start\": 190.52, \"end\": 195.06, \"text\": \"in the black deaf community.\"}, {\"start\": 195.1, \"end\": 197.26, \"text\": \"There is this \\\"Black Panther\\\" sign,\"}, {\"start\": 200.22, \"end\": 201.92, \"text\": \"this \\\"Black Panther\\\" sign,\"}, {\"start\": 205.02, \"end\": 206.16, \"text\": \"and this one.\"}, {\"start\": 209.26, \"end\": 215.28, \"text\": \"We encourage you to watch the movie and tell us what you think: Which sign best matches\"}, {\"start\": 215.28, \"end\": 221.36, \"text\": \"the \\\"Black Panther\\\" character -- sign number one, two or three?\"}, {\"start\": 221.36, \"end\": 224.96, \"text\": \"We would love to hear your thoughts.\"}, {\"start\": 228.8, \"end\": 237.62, \"text\": \"Today hundreds of people paid tribute to the victims of the massacre at Marjory Stoneman\"}, {\"start\": 237.62, \"end\": 240.22, \"text\": \"Douglas high school.\"}, {\"start\": 240.22, \"end\": 248.46, \"text\": \"Seventeen white crosses with red hearts on the front have been placed in front of the\"}, {\"start\": 248.46, \"end\": 252.74, \"text\": \"school in memory of the 17 students and teachers killed.\"}, {\"start\": 252.74, \"end\": 260.94, \"text\": \"Mourners left flowers, teddy bears, balloons and notes.\"}, {\"start\": 260.94, \"end\": 265.86, \"text\": \"Others were still clearly shaken by the tragedy.\"}, {\"start\": 265.86, \"end\": 268.26, \"text\": \"They just hugged each other and cried.\"}, {\"start\": 271.3, \"end\": 279.62, \"text\": \"Survivors of the Florida school shooting are turning their grief into action.\"}, {\"start\": 279.62, \"end\": 286.72, \"text\": \"They are sending a direct message to President Trump and lawmakers.\"}, {\"start\": 286.72, \"end\": 292.72, \"text\": \"The message: address gun reform now!\"}, {\"start\": 292.72, \"end\": 305.22, \"text\": \"Cameron Kasky said: \\\"My message for the people in office is you're either with us or against us.\"}, {\"start\": 305.22, \"end\": 311.22, \"text\": \"We are losing our lives while adults are playing around.\"}, {\"start\": 311.22, \"end\": 317.28, \"text\": \"Our job is to go to school, learn and to not take a bullet.\"}, {\"start\": 317.28, \"end\": 327.58, \"text\": \"Your job is to protect us and our blood is on your hands.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 327.58, \"end\": 343.38, \"text\": \"Emma Gonzalez said: \\\"We want to have conversations with President Trump, Senator Marco Rubio\"}, {\"start\": 343.38, \"end\": 349.68, \"text\": \"and Governor Rick Scott about the fact that they are being supported by the NRA and we\"}, {\"start\": 349.68, \"end\": 355.14, \"text\": \"want to give them the opportunity to be on the side of right.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 355.14, \"end\": 365.54, \"text\": \"David Hogg had the strongest words for President Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 365.54, \"end\": 372.9, \"text\": \"He said: \\\"We've seen a government shutdown.\"}, {\"start\": 372.9, \"end\": 380.6, \"text\": \"We've seen tax reform but nothing to save our children's lives.\"}, {\"start\": 380.6, \"end\": 382.48, \"text\": \"Are you kidding me?\"}, {\"start\": 382.48, \"end\": 388.36, \"text\": \"You think now is the time to focus on the past and not the future to prevent the deaths\"}, {\"start\": 388.36, \"end\": 393.68, \"text\": \"of thousands of other children?\"}, {\"start\": 393.68, \"end\": 395.62, \"text\": \"You sicken me.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 398.72, \"end\": 410.68, \"text\": \"JetBlue wants to help the families impacted by Wednesday's shooting in Parkland, Florida.\"}, {\"start\": 410.68, \"end\": 415.7, \"text\": \"The airline announced on Saturday that it is offering free flights for victims' families\"}, {\"start\": 415.7, \"end\": 418.94, \"text\": \"traveling to Florida.\"}, {\"start\": 418.94, \"end\": 423.219, \"text\": \"JetBlue also announced a partnership with rideshare company Lyft to provide free ground\"}, {\"start\": 423.22, \"end\": 426.06, \"text\": \"transportation.\"}, {\"start\": 426.06, \"end\": 438.68, \"text\": \"JetBlue will also hold a blood drive at the BB&amp;T Center in Sunrise, Florida on Thursday,\"}, {\"start\": 438.68, \"end\": 444.72, \"text\": \"February 22nd, along with the NHL's Florida Panthers.\"}, {\"start\": 447.62, \"end\": 452.9, \"text\": \"We have the video of a massive brawl that broke out on a cruise ship.\"}, {\"start\": 452.9, \"end\": 460.06, \"text\": \"The 10-day Carnival cruise was headed to the South Pacific.\"}, {\"start\": 460.06, \"end\": 465.84, \"text\": \"Vicious brawls broke out over several days.\"}, {\"start\": 465.84, \"end\": 469.96, \"text\": \"Witnesses say it was horrifying.\"}, {\"start\": 469.96, \"end\": 477.28, \"text\": \"People were screaming, running, throwing glasses and blood was everywhere.\"}, {\"start\": 477.28, \"end\": 484.48, \"text\": \"Some passengers blame one group of 23 people who were traveling together, claiming the\"}, {\"start\": 484.48, \"end\": 490.86, \"text\": \"group was picking on any Australian person they could find.\"}, {\"start\": 490.86, \"end\": 496.54, \"text\": \"Others blame the ship security guards, claiming they were kicking passengers and punching\"}, {\"start\": 496.54, \"end\": 498.2, \"text\": \"women and children.\"}, {\"start\": 498.2, \"end\": 500.0, \"text\": \"See for yourself.\"}, {\"start\": 526.48, \"end\": 533.66, \"text\": \"The ship had to turn around and head back to Melbourne, Australia.\"}, {\"start\": 533.66, \"end\": 537.92, \"text\": \"Nine passengers were forced off the ship.\"}, {\"start\": 537.96, \"end\": 541.22, \"text\": \"Several passengers are demanding a refund.\"}, {\"start\": 541.22, \"end\": 544.36, \"text\": \"Others say they plan to sue.\"}, {\"start\": 547.1, \"end\": 550.16, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 550.16, \"end\": 551.74, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 551.74, \"end\": 553.84, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 553.84, \"end\": 559.16, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 559.16, \"end\": 565.12, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "PtCk2JK59NA": {
    "video_id": "PtCk2JK59NA",
    "title": "Man tries to stop hit and run with sledge hammer (ASL - 3.13.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180314",
    "duration": 94,
    "view_count": 132,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.34, \"end\": 8.9, \"text\": \"It was a wild scene on the streets of Miami this weekend.\"}, {\"start\": 8.94, \"end\": 11.54, \"text\": \"Two cars got into an accident.\"}, {\"start\": 11.54, \"end\": 15.16, \"text\": \"One car tried to leave the scene.\"}, {\"start\": 15.16, \"end\": 20.7, \"text\": \"That's when two men started yelling at the driver to stop, pounding on his car trying\"}, {\"start\": 20.7, \"end\": 22.86, \"text\": \"to open the car doors.\"}, {\"start\": 22.86, \"end\": 27.5, \"text\": \"The driver manages to pull away onto another street.\"}, {\"start\": 27.5, \"end\": 32.24, \"text\": \"A crowd follows.\"}, {\"start\": 32.24, \"end\": 40.18, \"text\": \"That's when one person pulls out a sledgehammer and begins breaking the windows of the car.\"}, {\"start\": 40.18, \"end\": 41.18, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 72.32, \"end\": 79.2, \"text\": \"The driver eventually pulls away again but was later arrested.\"}, {\"start\": 79.2, \"end\": 85.24, \"text\": \"He faces charges of fleeing and eluding police, leaving the scene of an accident and reckless\"}, {\"start\": 85.26, \"end\": 87.54, \"text\": \"driving.\"}, {\"start\": 87.54, \"end\": 93.02, \"text\": \"The arrest report says he may have been high on drugs.\"}]"
  },
  "0wTEsT9tG9A": {
    "video_id": "0wTEsT9tG9A",
    "title": "Girl can’t stop staring at Michelle Obama’s portrait (ASL - 3.4.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180305",
    "duration": 59,
    "view_count": 369,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 3.46, \"end\": 11.8, \"text\": \"This photo went viral this week.\"}, {\"start\": 11.8, \"end\": 20.66, \"text\": \"It was taken at the National Portrait Gallery by a visitor from North Carolina who posted\"}, {\"start\": 20.66, \"end\": 23.06, \"text\": \"it on his Facebook page.\"}, {\"start\": 23.06, \"end\": 33.0, \"text\": \"It shows two-year-old Parker Curry staring in awe at a towering portrait of former First\"}, {\"start\": 33.0, \"end\": 40.42, \"text\": \"Lady Michelle Obama.\"}, {\"start\": 40.42, \"end\": 44.5, \"text\": \"Parker's mother said the little girl was so amazed, she wouldn't even turn around for\"}, {\"start\": 44.5, \"end\": 48.2, \"text\": \"a picture.\"}, {\"start\": 48.2, \"end\": 53.8, \"text\": \"The mother says that Parker believes Michelle Obama is a queen and Parker wants to be a\"}, {\"start\": 53.84, \"end\": 57.62, \"text\": \"queen as well.\"}]"
  },
  "YeP-SqrjkyU": {
    "video_id": "YeP-SqrjkyU",
    "title": "Musician plays flute during brain surgery (ASL - 3.31.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180401",
    "duration": 40,
    "view_count": 210,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.5, \"end\": 8.8, \"text\": \"Sixty-three-year-old Anna Henry had been suffering from intense tremors in her left hand and fingers.\"}, {\"start\": 8.8, \"end\": 15.82, \"text\": \"So surgeons at the Texas Medical Center in Houston implanted tiny electrodes in her brain.\"}, {\"start\": 15.82, \"end\": 22.18, \"text\": \"While she was still an the operating table the team handed Henry her flute to test if\"}, {\"start\": 22.18, \"end\": 28.26, \"text\": \"her hands were steady enough to play.\"}, {\"start\": 28.26, \"end\": 38.32, \"text\": \"After playing one of her favorite classical concertos, doctors and nurses burst into applause.\"}]"
  },
  "Jmryac-HSgI": {
    "video_id": "Jmryac-HSgI",
    "title": "Sign1News 4.23.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180424",
    "duration": 473,
    "view_count": 1171,
    "description": "4.23.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Waffle House shooting suspect caught\n-It's a boy! Duchess of Cambridge gives birth \n-Shania Twain apologizes for Trump voting comment\n-Georgia man found guilty of murdering rich wife\n-Ex-NFL player apologizes for prom date gun photo\n-Van strikes, kills multiple pedestrians in Toronto\n-Ultra-rare corpse flower makes a big stink\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each da",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.9, \"end\": 9.56, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.56, \"end\": 11.3, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 11.3, \"end\": 12.92, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 12.92, \"end\": 16.08, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.84, \"end\": 27.34, \"text\": \"The suspect in the Waffle House shooting was captured today.\"}, {\"start\": 27.34, \"end\": 33.36, \"text\": \"Travis Reinking was on the run for 35 hours, wanted in the shooting deaths of four people.\"}, {\"start\": 33.36, \"end\": 38.9, \"text\": \"A citizen spotted him walking along the wood line and called 911.\"}, {\"start\": 38.9, \"end\": 45.82, \"text\": \"Ten minutes later, several local, state and federal law enforcement agencies converged\"}, {\"start\": 45.82, \"end\": 47.62, \"text\": \"at the location and apprehended him.\"}, {\"start\": 47.62, \"end\": 53.18, \"text\": \"Police say Reinking immediately fell to the ground and surrendered without any resistance.\"}, {\"start\": 53.18, \"end\": 57.48, \"text\": \"Police say Reinking was wearing a backpack at the time and inside they found a silver\"}, {\"start\": 57.48, \"end\": 63.48, \"text\": \"45-caliber semiautomatic gun.\"}, {\"start\": 63.48, \"end\": 67.4, \"text\": \"Reinking said nothing as he was being taken away.\"}, {\"start\": 70.38, \"end\": 85.56, \"text\": \"This is video of Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge and Prince William leaving St. Mary's Hospital\"}, {\"start\": 85.56, \"end\": 91.16, \"text\": \"with their newborn son, less than 24 hours after the birth.\"}, {\"start\": 91.16, \"end\": 102.4, \"text\": \"Their other two children, four-year-old Prince George and two-year-old Princess Charlotte\"}, {\"start\": 102.44, \"end\": 106.82, \"text\": \"left the hospital earlier after a short visit with their baby brother.\"}, {\"start\": 106.82, \"end\": 117.38, \"text\": \"The new royal baby is fifth in line to the British throne, after grandfather Prince Charles,\"}, {\"start\": 117.38, \"end\": 124.28, \"text\": \"father Prince William and two siblings.\"}, {\"start\": 124.28, \"end\": 131.5, \"text\": \"Kensington Palace said in a statement \\\"The Royal highnesses would like to thank all staff\"}, {\"start\": 131.5, \"end\": 133.86, \"text\": \"at the hospital for the care and treatment they have received.\"}, {\"start\": 133.86, \"end\": 139.76, \"text\": \"They would also like to thank everyone for their warm wishes.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 144.36, \"end\": 157.72, \"text\": \"This weekend country singer Shania Twain said in an interview with The Guardian that she\"}, {\"start\": 157.72, \"end\": 169.78, \"text\": \"would have voted for President Trump because he seemed honest, despite being offensive.\"}, {\"start\": 169.78, \"end\": 176.88, \"text\": \"Now she is backpedaling from those remarks after being slammed on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 176.88, \"end\": 185.26, \"text\": \"Twain says she does not hold any common moral beliefs with Trump and regretted appearing\"}, {\"start\": 185.26, \"end\": 188.58, \"text\": \"to endorse him.\"}, {\"start\": 188.58, \"end\": 195.76, \"text\": \"She said she was caught off guard by the question and admitted she gave an awkward answer.\"}, {\"start\": 195.76, \"end\": 204.02, \"text\": \"Twain also said her remarks are not an endorsement of Trump and that she makes music to bring\"}, {\"start\": 204.02, \"end\": 206.5, \"text\": \"people together.\"}, {\"start\": 206.5, \"end\": 211.66, \"text\": \"Of course, Twain would not have been able to vote for Trump in the 2016 election anyway\"}, {\"start\": 211.66, \"end\": 215.16, \"text\": \"because she is a Canadian citizen.\"}, {\"start\": 217.66, \"end\": 229.44, \"text\": \"Today a Georgia jury found Claud \\\"Tex\\\" McIver guilty of felony murder in the death of his\"}, {\"start\": 229.44, \"end\": 234.28, \"text\": \"wife Diane.\"}, {\"start\": 234.28, \"end\": 240.3, \"text\": \"He was also found guilty of trying to influence witnesses.\"}, {\"start\": 240.3, \"end\": 248.4, \"text\": \"In September 2016, the couple was on their way home from a weekend outing.\"}, {\"start\": 248.4, \"end\": 253.38, \"text\": \"A family friend was driving their SUV and Diane was sitting in the front seat.\"}, {\"start\": 253.38, \"end\": 264.3, \"text\": \"Tex said he was asleep in the backseat with a loaded revolver in his lap when he was startled\"}, {\"start\": 264.3, \"end\": 267.78, \"text\": \"and shot Diane in the back.\"}, {\"start\": 267.78, \"end\": 274.94, \"text\": \"Defense attorneys say it was an accidental shooting but prosecutors say McIver intentionally\"}, {\"start\": 274.94, \"end\": 277.76, \"text\": \"shot his wife for her money.\"}, {\"start\": 277.76, \"end\": 281.78, \"text\": \"McIver will be sentenced at a later date.\"}, {\"start\": 281.78, \"end\": 285.22, \"text\": \"He could be facing life in prison.\"}, {\"start\": 288.72, \"end\": 300.56, \"text\": \"Former NFL kicker Jay Feely has apologized for a photo of his daughter and her prom date\"}, {\"start\": 300.56, \"end\": 304.16, \"text\": \"that includes him holding a gun.\"}, {\"start\": 304.16, \"end\": 309.42, \"text\": \"The photo included the comment \\\"Wishing my beautiful daughter and her date a great time\"}, {\"start\": 309.42, \"end\": 313.56, \"text\": \"at prom. #badboys.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 313.56, \"end\": 319.68, \"text\": \"Some people thought the tweet played on a well-known joke about the cliched overprotective\"}, {\"start\": 319.68, \"end\": 322.66, \"text\": \"father stereotype.\"}, {\"start\": 322.66, \"end\": 328.78, \"text\": \"Others quickly criticized him for being in poor taste and representing irresponsible\"}, {\"start\": 328.78, \"end\": 330.72, \"text\": \"gun ownership.\"}, {\"start\": 330.72, \"end\": 337.06, \"text\": \"Feely tweeted Sunday the photo was obviously intended to be a joke.\"}, {\"start\": 337.06, \"end\": 343.26, \"text\": \"He went on to say he takes gun safety seriously and did not intend to be insensitive to the\"}, {\"start\": 343.26, \"end\": 345.1, \"text\": \"important issue.\"}, {\"start\": 349.24, \"end\": 360.419, \"text\": \"A white van collided with a crowd of pedestrians on a busy street in Toronto today.\"}, {\"start\": 360.42, \"end\": 365.44, \"text\": \"Toronto officials confirm nine people were killed and 16 injured.\"}, {\"start\": 365.44, \"end\": 371.58, \"text\": \"Witnesses say the driver appeared to do it intentionally because the van was moving at\"}, {\"start\": 371.58, \"end\": 377.26, \"text\": \"full speed down the sidewalk, mowing down anyone or anything in its path.\"}, {\"start\": 377.26, \"end\": 384.84, \"text\": \"Witnesses say the scene was horrific because the van covered between a half mile and a\"}, {\"start\": 384.84, \"end\": 388.16, \"text\": \"mile and left a lot of carnage in its path.\"}, {\"start\": 388.16, \"end\": 392.5, \"text\": \"Investigators later found the van and arrested the driver.\"}, {\"start\": 394.74, \"end\": 404.42, \"text\": \"Curious tourists are lining up at the botanical gardens of Tucson to catch a glimpse of \\\"Rosie,\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 404.42, \"end\": 410.66, \"text\": \"the ultra-rare and ultra-stinky corpse flower.\"}, {\"start\": 410.66, \"end\": 419.04, \"text\": \"The famous funky plant blooms once every 10 years and when it does, it gives off an awful\"}, {\"start\": 419.04, \"end\": 426.11, \"text\": \"stench that's been compared to rotting flesh.\"}, {\"start\": 426.11, \"end\": 432.22, \"text\": \"The garden is streaming the event live on YouTube for the whole world to witness.\"}, {\"start\": 432.22, \"end\": 436.88, \"text\": \"Over 160,000 have tuned in hoping to see the flowery debut.\"}, {\"start\": 436.88, \"end\": 444.14, \"text\": \"When the moment arrives, the bloom is only expected to last about 24 to 36 hours.\"}, {\"start\": 444.14, \"end\": 448.2, \"text\": \"So good luck catching a glimpse or getting a whiff.\"}, {\"start\": 450.8, \"end\": 453.1, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 453.1, \"end\": 454.28, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 454.28, \"end\": 456.22, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 456.22, \"end\": 459.98, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 459.98, \"end\": 461.32, \"text\": \"Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 461.32, \"end\": 462.32, \"text\": \"The life.\"}, {\"start\": 462.32, \"end\": 465.2, \"text\": \"Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "TyzULpKvSys": {
    "video_id": "TyzULpKvSys",
    "title": "Deadly Bronx fire (ASL 12.29.17)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171230",
    "duration": 53,
    "view_count": 210,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.16, \"end\": 9.8, \"text\": \"At least 12 people were killed in a fire Thursday night at an apartment building in the Bronx\"}, {\"start\": 9.8, \"end\": 12.86, \"text\": \"borough of New York City.\"}, {\"start\": 12.86, \"end\": 16.32, \"text\": \"Three of the 12 people killed were children.\"}, {\"start\": 16.32, \"end\": 21.48, \"text\": \"Fire officials say that the flame started in a first floor unit, where a three-year-old boy was playing\"}, {\"start\": 21.48, \"end\": 26.08, \"text\": \"with the burners on the stove.\"}, {\"start\": 26.08, \"end\": 29.72, \"text\": \"His mother noticed when the boy screamed.\"}, {\"start\": 29.72, \"end\": 32.3, \"text\": \"But when the mother fled the burning apartment with the boy, she made the mistake of leaving\"}, {\"start\": 32.3, \"end\": 34.3, \"text\": \"the apartment door open.\"}, {\"start\": 34.3, \"end\": 40.12, \"text\": \"That sucked the flames out of the apartment and quickly spread up the stairs of the building.\"}, {\"start\": 40.12, \"end\": 51.26, \"text\": \"New York Mayor Bill DeBlasio is calling this the worst fire tragedy in the city in at least 25 years.\"}]"
  },
  "5WSorhhDEsI": {
    "video_id": "5WSorhhDEsI",
    "title": "Sign1News 2.8.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180209",
    "duration": 565,
    "view_count": 1321,
    "description": "2.8.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).  \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Will you get paid more?\n-Gay Olympian turns down Pence meeting \n-Gerber spokesbaby has down syndrome\n-McDonald’s giving away cold “Bling Mac” ring\n-Apple watch can detect diabetes with 85% accuracy\n-“Pad Man” breaks stigma of menstruation in India\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign L",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 6.78, \"end\": 8.06, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 8.06, \"end\": 10.5, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.5, \"end\": 11.88, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 11.88, \"end\": 14.64, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 16.4, \"end\": 23.44, \"text\": \"Your paycheck may go up this month, thanks to the new tax law.\"}, {\"start\": 23.44, \"end\": 28.54, \"text\": \"The Congressional Budget Office estimates employees will likely withhold between 10\"}, {\"start\": 28.54, \"end\": 32.62, \"text\": \"to 15 billion dollars less from workers every month.\"}, {\"start\": 32.62, \"end\": 37.04, \"text\": \"That means more money for you.\"}, {\"start\": 37.04, \"end\": 45.22, \"text\": \"Payroll service ADP crunched the numbers.\"}, {\"start\": 45.3, \"end\": 54.04, \"text\": \"Let's say you are a single filer, getting paid twice a month, taking one withholding\"}, {\"start\": 54.04, \"end\": 60.54, \"text\": \"allowance, contributing 5 percent to a 401(k) and making 57,000 dollars a year.\"}, {\"start\": 60.54, \"end\": 63.92, \"text\": \"You can see 60 dollars more in your check.\"}, {\"start\": 63.92, \"end\": 70.56, \"text\": \"If you make about 162,000 dollars a year, expect to see about 190 dollars more.\"}, {\"start\": 70.56, \"end\": 80.3, \"text\": \"Let's look at married workers to file jointly, put 5 percent in a 401(k), get paid every\"}, {\"start\": 80.3, \"end\": 82.64, \"text\": \"two weeks but take two allowances.\"}, {\"start\": 82.64, \"end\": 89.16, \"text\": \"The joint filer making 61,000 dollars could see an extra 40 bucks a pay period.\"}, {\"start\": 89.2, \"end\": 95.84, \"text\": \"Remember your take-home pay depends on much more than just your salary and allowances.\"}, {\"start\": 95.84, \"end\": 99.36, \"text\": \"State and local taxes as well as health deductions may also impact your pay and could eat up\"}, {\"start\": 99.36, \"end\": 101.44, \"text\": \"any potential extra cash.\"}, {\"start\": 103.52, \"end\": 121.36, \"text\": \"U.S. Olympic figure skater Adam Rippon reportedly rejected a meeting with Vice President Mike\"}, {\"start\": 121.36, \"end\": 123.68, \"text\": \"Pence last month.\"}, {\"start\": 123.68, \"end\": 129.24, \"text\": \"USA Today reports that Pence's staff requested a meeting with Rippon after reading a January\"}, {\"start\": 129.48, \"end\": 137.96, \"text\": \"17th interview where he criticized the Vice President.\"}, {\"start\": 137.96, \"end\": 148.56, \"text\": \"The openly gay champion skater blasted the White House for tapping Pence to lead the\"}, {\"start\": 148.56, \"end\": 150.88, \"text\": \"Olympic delegation to Pyongyang.\"}, {\"start\": 150.88, \"end\": 167.28, \"text\": \"He said quote: \\\"The same Mike Pence that funded gay conversion therapy?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 167.44, \"end\": 178.12, \"text\": \"Pence's office claims it did not reach out to Rippon for a meeting and says Pence never\"}, {\"start\": 178.12, \"end\": 188.16, \"text\": \"funded gay conversion therapy.\"}, {\"start\": 188.2, \"end\": 196.08, \"text\": \"Pence's office says he supports all the U.S. athletes.\"}, {\"start\": 196.08, \"end\": 207.44, \"text\": \"Rippon and the only other openly gay Olympian, skier Gus Kenworthy, say they will not visit\"}, {\"start\": 207.44, \"end\": 210.76, \"text\": \"the White House after the games.\"}, {\"start\": 212.96, \"end\": 218.15, \"text\": \"This cute baby made history Wednesday.\"}, {\"start\": 218.16, \"end\": 234.24, \"text\": \"He's 18-month-old Lucas Warren and he is Gerber's \\\"Spokesbaby of the Year.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 234.24, \"end\": 244.72, \"text\": \"Gerber picked Lucas from more than 140,000 entries to its photo search contest.\"}, {\"start\": 244.72, \"end\": 254.64, \"text\": \"Lucas is the first child with Down Syndrome to take the title in the contest's 91 year history.\"}, {\"start\": 254.64, \"end\": 259.68, \"text\": \"The title means Lucas's parents will get a 50,000 dollar prize.\"}, {\"start\": 259.68, \"end\": 265.92, \"text\": \"Lucas will appear on Gerber's social media channels and he will be featured in Gerber\"}, {\"start\": 265.92, \"end\": 268.32, \"text\": \"ads throughout the year.\"}, {\"start\": 270.08, \"end\": 289.12, \"text\": \"McDonald's is giving away a seven-layer, 18 karat gold, gem-encrusted version of its classic\"}, {\"start\": 289.12, \"end\": 294.68, \"text\": \"Big Mac sandwich -- for free!\"}, {\"start\": 294.68, \"end\": 305.28, \"text\": \"It's called the \\\"Bling Mac\\\" and according to Cosmo it is worth about 12,000 dollars.\"}, {\"start\": 305.28, \"end\": 314.84, \"text\": \"For a chance to win it, social media users must tweet out their love for the Big Mac,\"}, {\"start\": 314.84, \"end\": 323.36, \"text\": \"using the hashtag #blingmaccontest.\"}, {\"start\": 323.36, \"end\": 331.8, \"text\": \"McDonald's new promotion comes with the launch of three different Big Mac sizes: Grand Big\"}, {\"start\": 331.8, \"end\": 337.08, \"text\": \"Mac, Big Mac and Mac Junior.\"}, {\"start\": 339.16, \"end\": 346.08, \"text\": \"The University of California-San Francisco conducted a study and found that the Apple\"}, {\"start\": 346.08, \"end\": 355.96, \"text\": \"watch can detect diabetes with 85 percent accuracy.\"}, {\"start\": 355.96, \"end\": 361.24, \"text\": \"The study used about 14,000 people to track results.\"}, {\"start\": 361.24, \"end\": 370.88, \"text\": \"Heart rate sensors in the watch can pick up on any irregularities that point to specific\"}, {\"start\": 370.88, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"conditions.\"}, {\"start\": 376.0, \"end\": 395.24, \"text\": \"And the mobile health app \\\"Cardiogram\\\" also found that hypertension, sleep apnea and atrial\"}, {\"start\": 395.24, \"end\": 402.96, \"text\": \"fibrillation can be detected.\"}, {\"start\": 406.04, \"end\": 420.44, \"text\": \"Arunachalam Murugantham is known as \\\"Pad Man.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 420.44, \"end\": 433.56, \"text\": \"And he is on a mission to break social taboos about women's menstruation in India.\"}, {\"start\": 433.56, \"end\": 445.96, \"text\": \"He is a welder from southern India who discovered his wife Shanthi using a dirty rag instead\"}, {\"start\": 445.96, \"end\": 447.48, \"text\": \"of a sanitary pad.\"}, {\"start\": 447.48, \"end\": 454.36, \"text\": \"She then told him it was either by rags or milk for the family.\"}, {\"start\": 454.56, \"end\": 466.24, \"text\": \"Sanitary pads are so expensive in India only 12 percent of women use them.\"}, {\"start\": 466.24, \"end\": 472.32, \"text\": \"That's when my Murugantham embarked on a quest to come up with an affordable solution.\"}, {\"start\": 472.32, \"end\": 480.48, \"text\": \"But because of entrenched taboos surrounding menstruation, he was called a pervert and\"}, {\"start\": 480.48, \"end\": 486.4, \"text\": \"a psycho and his wife eventually left him.\"}, {\"start\": 486.4, \"end\": 490.6, \"text\": \"He did not give up.\"}, {\"start\": 490.6, \"end\": 499.04, \"text\": \"He developed a machine to produce the pads at a fraction of the cost.\"}, {\"start\": 499.04, \"end\": 506.68, \"text\": \"Now \\\"Pad Man\\\" shares his story with audiences around the world showcasing his invention.\"}, {\"start\": 506.72, \"end\": 512.4, \"text\": \"Hundreds of pads are now being used in India.\"}, {\"start\": 512.4, \"end\": 519.47, \"text\": \"And he has created the hashtag #padmanchallenge, asking both women and men to take part to\"}, {\"start\": 519.48, \"end\": 524.92, \"text\": \"spread the message that there is no shame in women's menstruation.\"}, {\"start\": 524.92, \"end\": 532.36, \"text\": \"He hopes his story will empower women and educate men, not just in India, but around\"}, {\"start\": 532.36, \"end\": 534.6, \"text\": \"the world.\"}, {\"start\": 536.24, \"end\": 538.88, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 538.88, \"end\": 540.64, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 540.64, \"end\": 543.4, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 543.4, \"end\": 548.84, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 548.92, \"end\": 556.2, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "1gpNf32gGp8": {
    "video_id": "1gpNf32gGp8",
    "title": "Sign1News 12.13.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171214",
    "duration": 682,
    "view_count": 465,
    "description": "December 13, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-DEMOCRAT DOUG JONES WINS: NOW WHAT?\n-DEPUTY ATTORNEY GENERAL GRILLED ON CAPITOL HILL\n-BOMBING SUSPECT TO HAVE HEARING IN HOSPITAL\n-THOMAS FIRE RAGES IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA\n-THREE CHARGED IN SHARK DRAGGING\n-MEGHAN MARKLE TO SPEND HOLIDAYS WITH ROYAL FAMILY\n-OREO RELEASING 3 NEW COOKIE FLAVORS\n-HURRICANE PUPS SEEK HOMES FOR HOLIDAYS\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE Our talented staff work",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.86, \"end\": 10.5, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.6, \"end\": 11.66, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 11.72, \"end\": 13.86, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 15.92, \"end\": 23.32, \"text\": \"For weeks we've been watching Republican Roy Moore and Democrat Doug Jones battle it out\"}, {\"start\": 23.32, \"end\": 25.0, \"text\": \"in the race for the Alabama Senate seat.\"}, {\"start\": 25.08, \"end\": 29.02, \"text\": \"Moore had the full endorsement of President Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 29.1, \"end\": 36.0, \"text\": \"But Jones stunned the country and beat Moore to become the first Democrat in 25 years to\"}, {\"start\": 36.04, \"end\": 39.64, \"text\": \"win the Senate seat in Alabama.\"}, {\"start\": 39.68, \"end\": 44.1, \"text\": \"A source close to the White House says Moore's defeat is devastating for President Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 44.16, \"end\": 50.82, \"text\": \"Moore did not call Jones to congratulate him and he is refusing to concede.\"}, {\"start\": 50.84, \"end\": 56.7, \"text\": \"But now Trump is turning his attention to the upcoming tax reform vote.\"}, {\"start\": 56.8, \"end\": 70.48, \"text\": \"House and Senate negotiators struck a tentative deal on the tax bill today.\"}, {\"start\": 70.54, \"end\": 80.0, \"text\": \"Republicans are laser-focused on passing their tax bill over the next several days.\"}, {\"start\": 80.0, \"end\": 86.02, \"text\": \"But Democrats say it would be wrong for Republicans to jam through this tax bill without giving\"}, {\"start\": 86.02, \"end\": 91.52, \"text\": \"newly elected Senator Jones an opportunity to cast his vote.\"}, {\"start\": 91.56, \"end\": 103.36, \"text\": \"Political experts say it is not likely Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell\"}, {\"start\": 103.36, \"end\": 106.64, \"text\": \"will delay the vote.\"}, {\"start\": 108.5, \"end\": 128.36, \"text\": \"Rod Rosenstein, the top man overseeing Robert Mueller's Russia meddling investigation, was\"}, {\"start\": 128.4, \"end\": 133.92, \"text\": \"grilled for hours on Capitol Hill today by the House Judiciary Committee.\"}, {\"start\": 133.92, \"end\": 140.2, \"text\": \"Lawmakers are looking into Special Counsel Mueller's Russia investigative team and whether\"}, {\"start\": 140.26, \"end\": 149.9, \"text\": \"political bias is playing a role in the investigation of President Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 149.9, \"end\": 153.68, \"text\": \"The House Judiciary Committee said in a statement that they have serious concerns about the\"}, {\"start\": 153.74, \"end\": 156.86, \"text\": \"political motives of the members of Mueller's investigative team.\"}, {\"start\": 156.92, \"end\": 166.0, \"text\": \"Trump's lawyers have called for a second special counsel to investigate the Justice Department.\"}, {\"start\": 166.06, \"end\": 172.62, \"text\": \"Rosenstein assured the Committee that personal opinions of President Trump has not influenced\"}, {\"start\": 172.72, \"end\": 176.32, \"text\": \"the investigation.\"}, {\"start\": 179.12, \"end\": 189.2, \"text\": \"Akayed Ullah, the man accused in a failed terror attack in New York, appeared before\"}, {\"start\": 189.36, \"end\": 200.4, \"text\": \"a judge today from his bedside.\"}, {\"start\": 200.72, \"end\": 204.88, \"text\": \"Ullah is still recovering in the hospital.\"}, {\"start\": 204.88, \"end\": 216.8, \"text\": \"He set off a pipe bomb strapped to his body at the port authority bus terminal Monday\"}, {\"start\": 216.8, \"end\": 219.68, \"text\": \"but it didn't go off all the way.\"}, {\"start\": 219.84, \"end\": 226.32, \"text\": \"Ullah suffered burns and cuts in the blast.\"}, {\"start\": 226.64, \"end\": 229.44, \"text\": \"Five other people were injured.\"}, {\"start\": 229.44, \"end\": 239.04, \"text\": \"Investigators say Ullah admitted to the crime and said he was inspired by Isis.\"}, {\"start\": 239.36, \"end\": 245.84, \"text\": \"Ullah is facing numerous federal and state terrorism charges.\"}, {\"start\": 247.36, \"end\": 257.36, \"text\": \"Here's a dramatic look at the Thomas fire as it burns near Montecito, California.\"}, {\"start\": 257.36, \"end\": 265.92, \"text\": \"It looks more like a lava flow than a wildfire.\"}, {\"start\": 266.0, \"end\": 271.76, \"text\": \"It is one of six fires burning in Southern California.\"}, {\"start\": 272.0, \"end\": 276.8, \"text\": \"The Thomas fire is now the fifth largest wildfire in modern California history.\"}, {\"start\": 277.04, \"end\": 279.04, \"text\": \"The blaze is larger than New York City.\"}, {\"start\": 279.44, \"end\": 286.24, \"text\": \"We want to show you video shot by the Los Angeles County Fire Department from the ground\"}, {\"start\": 286.56, \"end\": 291.36, \"text\": \"as crews drive right through the flames.\"}, {\"start\": 296.48, \"end\": 305.12, \"text\": \"Firefighters have contained about 25% of the massive fire.\"}, {\"start\": 305.76, \"end\": 310.56, \"text\": \"It's a hopeful sign that crews are making headway as winds in the area decreased to\"}, {\"start\": 311.2, \"end\": 318.4, \"text\": \"15 to 25 miles per hour.\"}, {\"start\": 318.88, \"end\": 323.52, \"text\": \"The outlook for rain, however, remains grim.\"}, {\"start\": 323.84, \"end\": 331.68, \"text\": \"Meteorologists expect it to stay dry for at least the next seven days.\"}, {\"start\": 333.12, \"end\": 344.48, \"text\": \"Three Florida men have been charged with animal cruelty after this video went viral.\"}, {\"start\": 344.96, \"end\": 359.52, \"text\": \"It shows the men laughing and smiling as a shark gets dragged behind a boat at high speeds.\"}, {\"start\": 359.84, \"end\": 361.28, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 375.68, \"end\": 388.32, \"text\": \"Police later found out the men had shot the shark first then dragged it behind the boat --\"}, {\"start\": 388.32, \"end\": 391.2, \"text\": \"causing the shark to die.\"}, {\"start\": 391.2, \"end\": 395.52, \"text\": \"Florida wildlife officials began investigating after the video surfaced\"}, {\"start\": 395.84, \"end\": 404.8, \"text\": \"on social media  in July.\"}, {\"start\": 404.96, \"end\": 411.52, \"text\": \"The video racked up thousands of views on\"}, {\"start\": 411.68, \"end\": 415.04, \"text\": \"social media as well as thousands of comments, many of them expressing outrage.\"}, {\"start\": 415.36, \"end\": 421.6, \"text\": \"If convicted, the man could spent five years in prison\"}, {\"start\": 421.76, \"end\": 423.84, \"text\": \"and would have to pay a $10,000 fine.\"}, {\"start\": 425.6, \"end\": 432.96, \"text\": \"Meghan Markle has her Christmas plans finalized.\"}, {\"start\": 433.44, \"end\": 442.88, \"text\": \"Kensington Palace says Markle will join her fiance, Britain's Prince Harry and several\"}, {\"start\": 442.88, \"end\": 450.88, \"text\": \"other Royals for Christmas at Queen Elizabeth's country home.\"}, {\"start\": 451.2, \"end\": 456.88, \"text\": \"The move is not the norm for Britain's Royal family, who typically only extends invitations\"}, {\"start\": 456.88, \"end\": 461.28, \"text\": \"after a couple has already tied the knot.\"}, {\"start\": 461.36, \"end\": 470.4, \"text\": \"Prince Harry and Markle announced their engagement last month after dating for about a year.\"}, {\"start\": 470.4, \"end\": 472.96, \"text\": \"The two are expected to get married next May.\"}, {\"start\": 474.72, \"end\": 491.04, \"text\": \"Nabisco has unveiled the three finalists in its \\\"My Oreo Creation\\\" contest.\"}, {\"start\": 491.28, \"end\": 506.56, \"text\": \"Those flavors are pina colada, cherry cola and kettle corn.\"}, {\"start\": 506.72, \"end\": 512.88, \"text\": \"But wait -- you can't run to the stores to buy them yet.\"}, {\"start\": 513.04, \"end\": 520.08, \"text\": \"The new flavors will not be available until May.\"}, {\"start\": 520.4, \"end\": 532.4, \"text\": \"Once they are available, fans can vote on their favorite.\"}, {\"start\": 532.4, \"end\": 538.48, \"text\": \"The creator of the winning flavor gets a $500,000 prize.\"}, {\"start\": 540.56, \"end\": 549.84, \"text\": \"With the holidays approaching, animal rescue groups hope the spirit of the season will\"}, {\"start\": 550.0, \"end\": 554.56, \"text\": \"help them find homes for dogs --\"}, {\"start\": 554.64, \"end\": 560.08, \"text\": \"in particular the thousands of dogs displaced after an unprecedented\"}, {\"start\": 560.16, \"end\": 563.12, \"text\": \"Atlantic hurricane season.\"}, {\"start\": 563.36, \"end\": 570.8, \"text\": \"Several animal rescue groups went in after hurricanes Harvey, Irma and Maria\"}, {\"start\": 570.96, \"end\": 575.44, \"text\": \"to get animals to safer places.\"}, {\"start\": 575.44, \"end\": 585.76, \"text\": \"And with the number of affected animals this year, shelter and foster communities all over\"}, {\"start\": 586.08, \"end\": 591.68, \"text\": \"the country hope to match them with new homes quickly.\"}, {\"start\": 592.0, \"end\": 599.92, \"text\": \"With the holidays around the corner, rescue groups feel the timing is perfect to start\"}, {\"start\": 600.24, \"end\": 607.36, \"text\": \"a new relationship with a pet.\"}, {\"start\": 609.04, \"end\": 610.96, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 611.2, \"end\": 612.32, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 612.48, \"end\": 614.8, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 614.96, \"end\": 618.96, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 619.12, \"end\": 624.88, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "wMUpVZEaoQY": {
    "video_id": "wMUpVZEaoQY",
    "title": "Trump slams Oprah Winfrey’s “60 Minutes” segment (ASL - 2.19.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180220",
    "duration": 92,
    "view_count": 371,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.42, \"end\": 14.62, \"text\": \"Last fall Oprah Winfrey interviewed 14 Michigan voters, seven of whom voted for Donald Trump\"}, {\"start\": 14.62, \"end\": 18.42, \"text\": \"and seven who did not.\"}, {\"start\": 18.42, \"end\": 29.74, \"text\": \"Last night on \\\"60 Minutes,\\\" she sat down with the voters again to get their thoughts on\"}, {\"start\": 29.74, \"end\": 35.78, \"text\": \"Trump's first year.\"}, {\"start\": 35.78, \"end\": 44.58, \"text\": \"The discussion looked at whether pro-Trump supporters still backed Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 44.58, \"end\": 58.7, \"text\": \"Right after the program aired, Trump tweeted this:\"}, {\"start\": 58.7, \"end\": 70.54, \"text\": \"\\\"Just watched a very insecure Oprah Winfrey, who at one point I knew very well, interview\"}, {\"start\": 70.54, \"end\": 73.8, \"text\": \"a panel of people on \\\"60 Minutes.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 73.8, \"end\": 80.4, \"text\": \"Questions were biased and slanted, the facts incorrect.\"}, {\"start\": 80.4, \"end\": 90.18, \"text\": \"Hope Oprah runs [for president] so she can be exposed and defeated just like all of the others!\\\"\"}]"
  },
  "4jPSJl8BjT4": {
    "video_id": "4jPSJl8BjT4",
    "title": "Millions of Americans can’t afford rent (ASL - 1.2.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180103",
    "duration": 118,
    "view_count": 415,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.46, \"end\": 10.5, \"text\": \"According to a new Harvard University study, millions of Americans cannot afford their rent.\"}, {\"start\": 10.5, \"end\": 19.08, \"text\": \"Almost 21 million people were considered burdened by the price of their rent in 2016.\"}, {\"start\": 19.08, \"end\": 29.0, \"text\": \"That means more than 30% of the money they earn goes to housing and utilities.\"}, {\"start\": 29.0, \"end\": 36.76, \"text\": \"Some people are in even worse shape, with 50% of their income covering the cost of housing.\"}, {\"start\": 36.76, \"end\": 40.54, \"text\": \"Losing such a big chunk of your check can impact your savings.\"}, {\"start\": 40.54, \"end\": 42.96, \"text\": \"But there is some good news.\"}, {\"start\": 42.96, \"end\": 46.86, \"text\": \"There are ways to ease the financial strain of renting.\"}, {\"start\": 46.86, \"end\": 57.2, \"text\": \"You may be able to lower payments by switching cable providers every year.\"}, {\"start\": 57.2, \"end\": 63.56, \"text\": \"Call your cable company to see if you can negotiate a lower rate.\"}, {\"start\": 63.56, \"end\": 67.96, \"text\": \"Or cut the cord and switch to a  streaming service.\"}, {\"start\": 67.96, \"end\": 71.18, \"text\": \"Consider getting a roommate.\"}, {\"start\": 71.18, \"end\": 75.0, \"text\": \"A new person could help you cut costs in half.\"}, {\"start\": 75.0, \"end\": 86.14, \"text\": \"If you are good renter, negotiate with your landlord.\"}, {\"start\": 86.14, \"end\": 89.4, \"text\": \"Try to talk the landlord out of raising your rent when it comes time to renew.\"}, {\"start\": 89.4, \"end\": 101.4, \"text\": \"If an appliance breaks, ask your landlord about getting credit on your next rent statement.\"}, {\"start\": 101.4, \"end\": 107.86, \"text\": \"Especially if you have to spend money while you wait for that appliance to get fixed.\"}, {\"start\": 107.86, \"end\": 111.18, \"text\": \"Bottom line: it doesn't hurt to have a conversation.\"}, {\"start\": 111.18, \"end\": 116.82, \"text\": \"It may help keep your costs down.\"}]"
  },
  "k_LHeo6sXek": {
    "video_id": "k_LHeo6sXek",
    "title": "Sign1News 1.29.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180130",
    "duration": 464,
    "view_count": 1193,
    "description": "1.29.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-State of the Union preview\n-FBI deputy director steps down\n-Jennifer Hudson to star in Aretha Franklin biopic\n-Budweiser Super Bowl ad: \"Stand by Me\"\n-Grammys recap\n-High school freshman make 3/4 court winning shot\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.08, \"end\": 9.34, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.34, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 13.28, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 13.28, \"end\": 16.2, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.14, \"end\": 26.28, \"text\": \"President Trump will deliver his first State of the Union address to the nation and Congress\"}, {\"start\": 26.32, \"end\": 27.28, \"text\": \"Tuesday.\"}, {\"start\": 27.28, \"end\": 30.42, \"text\": \"At the forefront of his speech: immigration.\"}, {\"start\": 30.46, \"end\": 37.98, \"text\": \"The president tweeted late Saturday about his DACA plan.\"}, {\"start\": 37.98, \"end\": 43.96, \"text\": \"Trump tweeted: \\\"I have offered DACA a wonderful deal, including a doubling in the number of\"}, {\"start\": 43.96, \"end\": 49.68, \"text\": \"recipients and a 12 year pathway to citizenship, for two reasons: 1) because the Republicans\"}, {\"start\": 49.8, \"end\": 55.6, \"text\": \"want to fix a longtime terrible problem, 2) to show the Democrats do not want to solve\"}, {\"start\": 55.6, \"end\": 59.48, \"text\": \"DACA, only use it.\"}, {\"start\": 59.48, \"end\": 64.92, \"text\": \"Trump also attacked Democrats on border safety.\"}, {\"start\": 64.92, \"end\": 68.56, \"text\": \"He tweeted: \\\"Democrats are not interested in border safety and security or in the funding\"}, {\"start\": 68.56, \"end\": 72.76, \"text\": \"and rebuilding of our military.\"}, {\"start\": 72.76, \"end\": 76.52, \"text\": \"They are only interested in obstructions.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 79.64, \"end\": 87.32, \"text\": \"FBI Deputy Director Andrew McCabe is stepping down, effective today.\"}, {\"start\": 87.32, \"end\": 95.24, \"text\": \"The circumstances of his stepping down are unclear, but McCabe has come under public\"}, {\"start\": 95.24, \"end\": 107.08, \"text\": \"criticism by Trump in recent weeks over the FBI's handling of the Hillary Clinton email\"}, {\"start\": 107.08, \"end\": 113.04, \"text\": \"investigation as well as his connections to \\\"anti-Trump\\\" messages sent between two FBI\"}, {\"start\": 113.04, \"end\": 117.92, \"text\": \"employees during last year's presidential campaign.\"}, {\"start\": 117.92, \"end\": 124.48, \"text\": \"The White House confirmed McCabe's decision, adding that President Trump played no role\"}, {\"start\": 124.48, \"end\": 129.08, \"text\": \"in the process.\"}, {\"start\": 129.08, \"end\": 137.12, \"text\": \"McCabe was eligible to retire in March, but chose to step down earlier instead.\"}, {\"start\": 140.16, \"end\": 145.0, \"text\": \"A new movie is coming out about soul legend\"}, {\"start\": 145.0, \"end\": 146.96, \"text\": \"Aretha Franklin's life.\"}, {\"start\": 147.0, \"end\": 159.96, \"text\": \"Music producer Clive Davis made the announcement at his annual pre-Grammys party Saturday night.\"}, {\"start\": 159.96, \"end\": 169.4, \"text\": \"And he has picked Jennifer Hudson to portray Franklin.\"}, {\"start\": 169.4, \"end\": 177.84, \"text\": \"Hudson performed a medley of Franklin's songs at the event.\"}, {\"start\": 177.84, \"end\": 184.6, \"text\": \"On Instagram, Hudson tweeted: \\\"Aretha Franklin.\"}, {\"start\": 184.6, \"end\": 188.24, \"text\": \"You have no idea how humbled I am.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 191.04, \"end\": 199.76, \"text\": \"Fans of Budweiser's Super Bowl commercials may be in for a surprise this year.\"}, {\"start\": 199.76, \"end\": 213.72, \"text\": \"Instead of featuring the brand's iconic Clydesdale horses or talking frogs, the company's one\"}, {\"start\": 213.72, \"end\": 219.76, \"text\": \"minute ad will be about water.\"}, {\"start\": 219.76, \"end\": 226.6, \"text\": \"The ad brings attention to the brand helping areas victimized by natural disasters in the\"}, {\"start\": 226.6, \"end\": 230.52, \"text\": \"past year like Florida, California, Texas and Puerto Rico.\"}, {\"start\": 230.52, \"end\": 238.24, \"text\": \"Budweiser will air three other commercials to advertise its beer but no Clydesdales.\"}, {\"start\": 238.28, \"end\": 247.08, \"text\": \"The prancing horses are only being use on social media this time around.\"}, {\"start\": 249.56, \"end\": 259.6, \"text\": \"Here's a quick recap of last night's big Grammy winners and stunning performances.\"}, {\"start\": 259.6, \"end\": 275.76, \"text\": \"Rapper Kendrick Lamar won five trophies, including best rap album and best music video.\"}, {\"start\": 275.76, \"end\": 285.48, \"text\": \"Bruno Mars took home six Grammys, including best album, best record and song of the year.\"}, {\"start\": 285.48, \"end\": 295.84, \"text\": \"Chris Stapleton won three Grammys for best album, best song and best solo performance.\"}, {\"start\": 295.84, \"end\": 303.68, \"text\": \"Best new artist went to Alessia Cara.\"}, {\"start\": 303.88, \"end\": 308.0, \"text\": \"The performances spanned the spectrum.\"}, {\"start\": 308.0, \"end\": 320.48, \"text\": \"Elton John performed \\\"Tiny Dancer\\\" with Miley Cyrus.\"}, {\"start\": 320.48, \"end\": 333.08, \"text\": \"Luis Fonsi and Daddy Yankee sang their huge hit \\\"Despacito.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 333.08, \"end\": 352.84, \"text\": \"Maren Morris, Eric Church and Brothers Osborne performed \\\"Tears in Heaven\\\", a touching tribute\"}, {\"start\": 352.84, \"end\": 355.8, \"text\": \"to the Las Vegas shooting victims.\"}, {\"start\": 355.8, \"end\": 363.88, \"text\": \"And Janelle Monae introduced a show-stopping performance by Kesha, backed by an all-star\"}, {\"start\": 363.88, \"end\": 371.0, \"text\": \"women's choir, of her powerful song \\\"Praying.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 374.0, \"end\": 382.16, \"text\": \"Video of an Illinois high school basketball player's amazing three-quarter court, game-winning\"}, {\"start\": 382.16, \"end\": 385.28, \"text\": \"shot at the buzzer has gone viral.\"}, {\"start\": 385.28, \"end\": 394.92, \"text\": \"Evanston Township freshman Blake Peters ended up with the ball in his hands with eight seconds\"}, {\"start\": 394.92, \"end\": 398.44, \"text\": \"left in the game.\"}, {\"start\": 398.44, \"end\": 400.44, \"text\": \"He had to shuffle around players from the opposing team just to get a clear shot at\"}, {\"start\": 400.44, \"end\": 402.8, \"text\": \"the basket, which was 80 feet away.\"}, {\"start\": 402.8, \"end\": 407.04, \"text\": \"He heaved the ball sidearmed and he made it!\"}, {\"start\": 407.04, \"end\": 407.96, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 422.2, \"end\": 427.32, \"text\": \"Peter's team won 45-44.\"}, {\"start\": 427.36, \"end\": 435.04, \"text\": \"Video of the buzzer-beating shot has been viewed more than 2 million times on social\"}, {\"start\": 435.04, \"end\": 437.38, \"text\": \"media.\"}, {\"start\": 440.16, \"end\": 442.68, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 442.68, \"end\": 444.5, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 444.5, \"end\": 446.76, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 446.76, \"end\": 451.86, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 451.86, \"end\": 456.58, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "u7es5azGhCs": {
    "video_id": "u7es5azGhCs",
    "title": "Official NAD video announcement on White House lawsuit (8.4.20)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20200804",
    "duration": 189,
    "view_count": 811,
    "description": "",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en-US",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.46, \"end\": 5.22, \"text\": \"The NAD filed a lawsuit to ask U.S. President Donald J. Trump and the White House\"}, {\"start\": 5.22, \"end\": 7.4, \"text\": \"to immediately begin providing American Sign Language (ASL) interpreters during\"}, {\"start\": 7.4, \"end\": 9.82, \"text\": \"television broadcasts of their COVID-19 press conferences and briefings\"}, {\"start\": 9.82, \"end\": 12.82, \"text\": \"to make them accessible to deaf and hard of hearing people.\"}, {\"start\": 13.1, \"end\": 20.36, \"text\": \"Joining the NAD as counsel for the case is an international law firm, Arnold &amp; Porter,\"}, {\"start\": 20.36, \"end\": 30.0, \"text\": \"that is dedicated to pro bono litigation and equal access issues.\"}, {\"start\": 30.0, \"end\": 33.14, \"text\": \"Together, we are representing the plaintiffs in this lawsuit.\"}, {\"start\": 33.14, \"end\": 38.72, \"text\": \"The NAD is an organizational plaintiff along with five deaf people who are also plaintiffs:\"}, {\"start\": 38.72, \"end\": 55.62, \"text\": \"Carlton Strail, Graham Forsey, Debra Fleetwood, John Rivera Jr., and Corey Axelrod.\"}, {\"start\": 55.94, \"end\": 60.98, \"text\": \"The reason for this lawsuit is to make sure deaf and hard of hearing people get same access\"}, {\"start\": 60.98, \"end\": 70.28, \"text\": \"to important COVID information and health related news from\"}, {\"start\": 70.28, \"end\": 73.24, \"text\": \"the White House and the President as everyone else.\"}, {\"start\": 73.24, \"end\": 76.82, \"text\": \"Such information is not accessible to us, with nothing available in ASL.\"}, {\"start\": 76.82, \"end\": 82.44, \"text\": \"And this access should not just be captioning, which is sometimes delayed\"}, {\"start\": 82.44, \"end\": 88.16, \"text\": \"and not always accurate, but also in ASL.\"}, {\"start\": 88.46, \"end\": 96.66, \"text\": \"Since March, 2020, the NAD, the National Council on Disability, and several legislators from Congress\"}, {\"start\": 96.66, \"end\": 104.94, \"text\": \"sent letters to the White House asking for ASL interpreters, but there has been no response yet.\"}, {\"start\": 105.36, \"end\": 116.64, \"text\": \"All 50 state governors have provided interpreters, although some have been not been consistent\"}, {\"start\": 116.64, \"end\": 122.5, \"text\": \"while others have always provided interpreters.\"}, {\"start\": 122.9, \"end\": 130.38, \"text\": \"The White House has never provided an ASL interpreter for COVID-19 even though the law,\"}, {\"start\": 130.38, \"end\": 135.62, \"text\": \"Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act, requires that the White House make its communications accessible\"}, {\"start\": 135.62, \"end\": 139.5, \"text\": \"to all including in ASL for deaf and hard of hearing people.\"}, {\"start\": 140.3, \"end\": 153.88, \"text\": \"More than 4.7 million Americans have been infected with coronavirus with more than 150,000 dead.\"}, {\"start\": 154.36, \"end\": 159.76, \"text\": \"Deaf and hard of hearing people are more at risk to being affected with the coronavirus because we do not\"}, {\"start\": 159.76, \"end\": 165.4, \"text\": \"get the same updates and information at the same time as everyone else.\"}, {\"start\": 165.4, \"end\": 173.92, \"text\": \"That is why this lawsuit was filed, to make sure the highest levels of government provide ASL access\"}, {\"start\": 173.92, \"end\": 176.58, \"text\": \"for health information to deaf and hard of hearing people.\"}, {\"start\": 177.32, \"end\": 182.52, \"text\": \"We will bring further updates when there is progress in this case.\"}]"
  },
  "WA3ZLFQrSf4": {
    "video_id": "WA3ZLFQrSf4",
    "title": "Sign1News 1.19.18 - News in American Sign Language (ASL)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180120",
    "duration": 664,
    "view_count": 561,
    "description": "1.19.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Torture house kids only allowed to look at food\n-Thousands gather in D.C. for pro-life rally\n-Arizona man accused of at least 9 murders\n-Deadly storms strike Western Europe\n-Apple makes big promises to American economy\n-Most Americans can’t cover $1,000 emergency\n-Over 1,600 LBS of cocaine hidden pineapples\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader ",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.98, \"end\": 8.66, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 8.66, \"end\": 10.42, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.42, \"end\": 11.46, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 11.46, \"end\": 14.28, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 16.54, \"end\": 30.38, \"text\": \"We're learning more disturbing details about the physical and emotional abuse 13 children\"}, {\"start\": 30.38, \"end\": 38.12, \"text\": \"suffered at the hands of their parents.\"}, {\"start\": 38.12, \"end\": 44.06, \"text\": \"Officials in California say the children, ages 2 to 29, were not allowed to shower more\"}, {\"start\": 44.06, \"end\": 56.0, \"text\": \"than once a year, they were chained and padlocked to their beds and there were unopened toys\"}, {\"start\": 56.0, \"end\": 60.94, \"text\": \"in the house the children were not allowed to play with.\"}, {\"start\": 60.94, \"end\": 69.9, \"text\": \"The parents would buy food like apple or pumpkin pie and leave them on the counter for the\"}, {\"start\": 69.9, \"end\": 75.42, \"text\": \"children to look at but not eat.\"}, {\"start\": 75.42, \"end\": 88.72, \"text\": \"The 12 older children were so malnourished and small, doctors were shocked at their actual\"}, {\"start\": 88.72, \"end\": 89.88, \"text\": \"ages.\"}, {\"start\": 89.88, \"end\": 96.46, \"text\": \"The children lacked even the most basic life knowledge.\"}, {\"start\": 96.46, \"end\": 106.44, \"text\": \"Many of them didn't know what a police officer was or what medicine looked like.\"}, {\"start\": 106.44, \"end\": 117.2, \"text\": \"Police also learned the 17-year-old girl that escaped had been working on an escape plan\"}, {\"start\": 117.2, \"end\": 121.48, \"text\": \"with her siblings for more than two years.\"}, {\"start\": 121.48, \"end\": 141.3, \"text\": \"On Thursday the parents, David and Louise Turpin, pleaded not guilty to all charges,\"}, {\"start\": 141.3, \"end\": 145.44, \"text\": \"including 12 counts of false imprisonment and 12 counts of torture.\"}, {\"start\": 145.44, \"end\": 153.04, \"text\": \"They are each being held on $12 million bail.\"}, {\"start\": 155.54, \"end\": 161.02, \"text\": \"Hundreds of thousands of people converged on the National Mall in Washington, DC for\"}, {\"start\": 161.04, \"end\": 167.28, \"text\": \"to the 45th annual \\\"March for Life\\\" anti-abortion rally.\"}, {\"start\": 167.92, \"end\": 173.28, \"text\": \"President Trump made history today by becoming the first sitting US president to speak directly\"}, {\"start\": 173.28, \"end\": 174.6, \"text\": \"at a pro-life rally.\"}, {\"start\": 174.6, \"end\": 182.24, \"text\": \"Trump spoke to the activists via video feed from the Rose Garden.\"}, {\"start\": 182.24, \"end\": 193.6, \"text\": \"He declared January 19th \\\"National Sanctity of Life Day\\\" and promised to defend the very\"}, {\"start\": 193.6, \"end\": 201.52, \"text\": \"first right in the Declaration of Independence -- and that is a right to life.\"}, {\"start\": 201.52, \"end\": 212.56, \"text\": \"Earlier the Department of Health and Human Services announced it is removing a Medicaid\"}, {\"start\": 212.56, \"end\": 239.68, \"text\": \"guideline that limits how states can take action against providers that perform abortions.\"}, {\"start\": 242.56, \"end\": 255.04, \"text\": \"Phoenix police say this man, Cleophus Cooksey, is likely a serial killer.\"}, {\"start\": 255.04, \"end\": 263.76, \"text\": \"On December 17th he was arrested and charged with killing his mother and stepfather.\"}, {\"start\": 263.76, \"end\": 270.64, \"text\": \"But after additional forensic analysis, police now believe he killed seven other people in\"}, {\"start\": 270.66, \"end\": 272.62, \"text\": \"the three weeks leading up to that double murder.\"}, {\"start\": 272.62, \"end\": 279.6, \"text\": \"The victims were all killed in the Phoenix area in different places -- an alley, apartment\"}, {\"start\": 279.6, \"end\": 282.36, \"text\": \"complexes and grassy fields.\"}, {\"start\": 282.36, \"end\": 289.62, \"text\": \"Police say the victims are all different ages and races and there is no pattern in the killings.\"}, {\"start\": 289.62, \"end\": 295.5, \"text\": \"One victim was the brother of Cooksey's former girlfriend.\"}, {\"start\": 295.5, \"end\": 311.22, \"text\": \"Other victims appear to be random and were fatally shot during meetings arranged online.\"}, {\"start\": 311.22, \"end\": 318.08, \"text\": \"Cooksey was charged with two counts of first-degree murder in the death of his mother and stepfather.\"}, {\"start\": 318.08, \"end\": 326.08, \"text\": \"A decision on what charges Cooksey will face in the seven additional death is expected\"}, {\"start\": 326.08, \"end\": 328.8, \"text\": \"in the next few weeks.\"}, {\"start\": 331.74, \"end\": 344.1, \"text\": \"A massive windstorm in Western Europe has killed eight people -- two in the Netherlands\"}, {\"start\": 344.1, \"end\": 349.5, \"text\": \"and six in Germany.\"}, {\"start\": 349.5, \"end\": 362.74, \"text\": \"The wind is so strong it is flipping trucks off the road, ripping roofs off buildings\"}, {\"start\": 362.74, \"end\": 367.0, \"text\": \"and pulling trees up from the roots.\"}, {\"start\": 367.0, \"end\": 368.16, \"text\": \"Here's video showing the destructive force of the wind.\"}, {\"start\": 394.24, \"end\": 402.96, \"text\": \"Conditions are so bad Amsterdam was forced to close its airport, leaving thousands of\"}, {\"start\": 402.96, \"end\": 405.64, \"text\": \"passengers stranded.\"}, {\"start\": 408.2, \"end\": 418.78, \"text\": \"Apple just made many big promises to the American economy.\"}, {\"start\": 418.78, \"end\": 421.4, \"text\": \"Here is how the company plans on investing in the United States:\"}, {\"start\": 421.4, \"end\": 427.52, \"text\": \"It promises to bring $215 billion in foreign profits home.\"}, {\"start\": 427.52, \"end\": 436.66, \"text\": \"That's $38 billion in taxes that goes right to the Treasury Department.\"}, {\"start\": 436.66, \"end\": 445.18, \"text\": \"Apple promises to use some of the money to create 20,000 jobs and invest $30 billion\"}, {\"start\": 445.24, \"end\": 447.48, \"text\": \"in US facilities over the next five years.\"}, {\"start\": 447.48, \"end\": 453.92, \"text\": \"That includes a new corporate campus and several data centers.\"}, {\"start\": 453.92, \"end\": 462.54, \"text\": \"Apple also says its giving its employees a $2,500 bonus.\"}, {\"start\": 462.54, \"end\": 474.12, \"text\": \"Apple CEO Tim Cook released a statement that said: \\\"We have a deep sense of responsibility\"}, {\"start\": 474.12, \"end\": 481.58, \"text\": \"to give back to our country and the people who help make our success possible.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 481.58, \"end\": 492.62, \"text\": \"President Trump responded by saying \\\"I promised that my policies would allow companies like\"}, {\"start\": 492.62, \"end\": 494.8, \"text\": \"Apple to bring massive amounts of money back to United States.\"}, {\"start\": 494.8, \"end\": 499.939, \"text\": \"Great to see Apple follow through as a result of tax cuts.\"}, {\"start\": 499.94, \"end\": 506.32, \"text\": \"Huge win for American workers and the USA.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 509.58, \"end\": 516.58, \"text\": \"If you were hit with a $1,000 emergency, would you be able to cover it?\"}, {\"start\": 516.58, \"end\": 521.34, \"text\": \"The majority of Americans can't.\"}, {\"start\": 521.34, \"end\": 535.48, \"text\": \"A new report from BankRate.com found that only 39% would be able to pay a bill that\"}, {\"start\": 535.48, \"end\": 538.16, \"text\": \"size out of savings.\"}, {\"start\": 538.16, \"end\": 552.48, \"text\": \"Among those who say they couldn't pay, 36% said they would need to borrow the money or\"}, {\"start\": 552.48, \"end\": 556.16, \"text\": \"put it on a credit card.\"}, {\"start\": 556.18, \"end\": 567.66, \"text\": \"The report also found younger millennials aged 18 to 27 were the most likely of all\"}, {\"start\": 567.66, \"end\": 573.3, \"text\": \"age groups to borrow from family or friends in an emergency situation, while older millennials\"}, {\"start\": 573.3, \"end\": 583.44, \"text\": \"aged 28 to 37 were those most likely to reduce spending on other things.\"}, {\"start\": 586.38, \"end\": 600.52, \"text\": \"On Wednesday The Spanish national police announced on Twitter they had seized 1,642 pounds of\"}, {\"start\": 600.52, \"end\": 603.3, \"text\": \"cocaine.\"}, {\"start\": 603.3, \"end\": 614.36, \"text\": \"The cocaine was hidden inside pineapples shipped from South America.\"}, {\"start\": 614.36, \"end\": 624.16, \"text\": \"Nine people were arrested in a joint operation the Portuguese police to seize the pineapples.\"}, {\"start\": 624.16, \"end\": 636.62, \"text\": \"The investigation took 10 months and it broke up an international smuggling ring led by\"}, {\"start\": 636.62, \"end\": 638.28, \"text\": \"Colombians.\"}, {\"start\": 640.52, \"end\": 643.26, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 643.26, \"end\": 644.62, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 644.62, \"end\": 646.84, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 646.84, \"end\": 650.66, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 650.7, \"end\": 655.18, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "TGsw9tqUA4w": {
    "video_id": "TGsw9tqUA4w",
    "title": "How to defend yourself against the flu (ASL - 1.26.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180127",
    "duration": 107,
    "view_count": 171,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.8, \"end\": 16.28, \"text\": \"The flu is hitting people really hard this year.\"}, {\"start\": 16.28, \"end\": 27.3, \"text\": \"Some places are even running short of the drug that helps minimize flu symptoms.\"}, {\"start\": 27.3, \"end\": 31.92, \"text\": \"So your best defense is you.\"}, {\"start\": 31.92, \"end\": 33.82, \"text\": \"Here are some suggestions on how to protect yourself.\"}, {\"start\": 33.82, \"end\": 46.22, \"text\": \"Stay away from too much sugar and alcohol.\"}, {\"start\": 46.22, \"end\": 62.29, \"text\": \"It can suppress your immune system.\"}, {\"start\": 62.29, \"end\": 76.96, \"text\": \"Disinfect common areas in your home because the flu virus can live on surfaces for several\"}, {\"start\": 76.96, \"end\": 79.8, \"text\": \"hours.\"}, {\"start\": 79.8, \"end\": 89.74, \"text\": \"Wash those bedsheets, blankets, towels and your hands.\"}, {\"start\": 89.74, \"end\": 99.04, \"text\": \"And even though the flu season is well underway, it's not too late to get vaccinated.\"}, {\"start\": 99.04, \"end\": 105.82, \"text\": \"Experts recommend everyone six months of age and older get a flu shot.\"}]"
  },
  "-tHAb1yPEVM": {
    "video_id": "-tHAb1yPEVM",
    "title": "Mass shooting at Florida high school (ASL - 2.14.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180215",
    "duration": 69,
    "view_count": 250,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.42, \"end\": 9.94, \"text\": \"Broward County police say a lone gunman opened fire at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School today.\"}, {\"start\": 9.94, \"end\": 18.86, \"text\": \"Authorities say the shooting started just before 3 PM.\"}, {\"start\": 18.86, \"end\": 23.32, \"text\": \"Dozens of law-enforcement agencies -- police, fire, ambulances, ATF – responded.\"}, {\"start\": 23.32, \"end\": 30.72, \"text\": \"The suspect was captured a few hours later at a home not far from the school.\"}, {\"start\": 30.72, \"end\": 40.68, \"text\": \"Police say they were able to track the shooter down quickly because several students recognized\"}, {\"start\": 40.68, \"end\": 44.8, \"text\": \"him immediately as a former student.\"}, {\"start\": 44.8, \"end\": 50.8, \"text\": \"Law enforcement officials say there were numerous fatalities, however at the time of this recording,\"}, {\"start\": 50.8, \"end\": 62.56, \"text\": \"officials had not release exact number of people killed or injured but it is at least 16.\"}, {\"start\": 62.56, \"end\": 68.48, \"text\": \"Officials say this is the worst mass shooting in Broward County history.\"}]"
  },
  "UJTMSNJzjYE": {
    "video_id": "UJTMSNJzjYE",
    "title": "Shelter pets enjoy donated furniture (ASL - 3.8.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180309",
    "duration": 57,
    "view_count": 136,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.3, \"end\": 7.4, \"text\": \"Shelter dogs and cats are animals without a home.\"}, {\"start\": 7.4, \"end\": 19.04, \"text\": \"But the Knox County Humane Society in Illinois came up with the bright idea to make the animals\"}, {\"start\": 19.04, \"end\": 22.94, \"text\": \"feel right at home.\"}, {\"start\": 22.94, \"end\": 32.52, \"text\": \"They are asking people to donate old chairs so the animals will feel comfortable while\"}, {\"start\": 32.52, \"end\": 37.36, \"text\": \"they wait to meet potential owners.\"}, {\"start\": 37.36, \"end\": 39.28, \"text\": \"And it is working!\"}, {\"start\": 39.28, \"end\": 50.38, \"text\": \"A video posted to Facebook of the pets enjoying chairs racked up more than 14 million views.\"}, {\"start\": 50.38, \"end\": 56.52, \"text\": \"Since then donations have been rolling in from all over the country.\"}]"
  },
  "fMCfJqqVZSI": {
    "video_id": "fMCfJqqVZSI",
    "title": "Fleeing suspect gets run over by his own car (ASL - 3.8.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180308",
    "duration": 49,
    "view_count": 119,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.84, \"end\": 5.88, \"text\": \"A suspect in Virginia trying to flee from a police pursuit runs himself over with his\"}, {\"start\": 5.92, \"end\": 8.24, \"text\": \"own car.\"}, {\"start\": 8.24, \"end\": 16.44, \"text\": \"Thirty-year-old Isaac Bonsu took off in his car when police tried to pull him over.\"}, {\"start\": 16.44, \"end\": 23.24, \"text\": \"But when he drove down a dead-end street, he jumped out and tried to run.\"}, {\"start\": 23.24, \"end\": 31.12, \"text\": \"One problem: He forgot to put the car in park and it runs him over.\"}, {\"start\": 31.12, \"end\": 32.36, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 42.52, \"end\": 45.44, \"text\": \"Bonsu was not injured.\"}, {\"start\": 45.44, \"end\": 47.36, \"text\": \"He was charged with DWI.\"}]"
  },
  "rxgzdsivPs4": {
    "video_id": "rxgzdsivPs4",
    "title": "Sign1News 11.8.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171109",
    "duration": 482,
    "view_count": 89,
    "description": "November 8, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-DEMOCRATS SWEEP ELECTION!\n-PENCE VISITS WITH VICTIMS OF CHURCH SHOOTING \n-TEXAS SHOOTER: NEW DETAILS\n-KEVIN SPACEY ACCUSED AGAIN\n-KEVIN SPACEY MOVIE EXITS FILM FESTIVAL \n-WIN A NIGHT IN A LIFE-SIZED LEGO HOUSE\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds from notable organizations such as GALLAUDET UNIVERSITY",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.0, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I'm Crystal Cousineau\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 14.0, \"text\": \"and here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.0, \"end\": 23.0, \"text\": \"Democrats across the country claimed\"}, {\"start\": 23.0, \"end\": 28.0, \"text\": \"big victories Tuesday night. The biggest win was\"}, {\"start\": 29.0, \"end\": 34.0, \"text\": \"in Virginia's governor's race. Democrat Ralph\"}, {\"start\": 35.0, \"end\": 40.0, \"text\": \"Northam beat Republican\"}, {\"start\": 40.0, \"end\": 45.0, \"text\": \"Ed Gillespie in a race that was\"}, {\"start\": 45.0, \"end\": 49.0, \"text\": \"considered a close one. Members of both\"}, {\"start\": 49.0, \"end\": 54.0, \"text\": \"parties view the results as an indicator of what's to come\"}, {\"start\": 55.0, \"end\": 60.0, \"text\": \"in the 2018 elections in a divisive\"}, {\"start\": 60.0, \"end\": 65.0, \"text\": \"political climate where President Trump's approval ratings\"}, {\"start\": 65.0, \"end\": 69.0, \"text\": \"are historically low.\"}, {\"start\": 72.0, \"end\": 77.0, \"text\": \"Vice president Mike Pence is visiting Sutherland\"}, {\"start\": 77.0, \"end\": 81.0, \"text\": \"Springs, Texas to honor those\"}, {\"start\": 82.0, \"end\": 88.0, \"text\": \"killed and wounded in this past weekend 's church shooting.\"}, {\"start\": 88.0, \"end\": 91.0, \"text\": \"Attorney General Jeff Sessions\"}, {\"start\": 93.0, \"end\": 100.0, \"text\": \"is joining him on the trip.\"}, {\"start\": 101.0, \"end\": 106.0, \"text\": \"Pence and his wife are expected\"}, {\"start\": 106.0, \"end\": 111.0, \"text\": \"to visit shooting victims in area hospitals\"}, {\"start\": 111.0, \"end\": 116.0, \"text\": \"as well as meet with families of victims. They will\"}, {\"start\": 116.0, \"end\": 121.0, \"text\": \"later join Texas Governor Greg\"}, {\"start\": 122.0, \"end\": 127.0, \"text\": \"Abbott at a prayer service\"}, {\"start\": 127.001, \"end\": 128.099, \"text\": \"for the victims\"}, {\"start\": 128.1, \"end\": 130.1, \"text\": \"at an area\"}, {\"start\": 130.124, \"end\": 138.024, \"text\": \"high school.\"}, {\"start\": 140.0, \"end\": 144.0, \"text\": \"Today we know more about the gunman who opened\"}, {\"start\": 145.0, \"end\": 150.0, \"text\": \"fire in a Texas church over the weekend. Texas church\"}, {\"start\": 150.0, \"end\": 154.0, \"text\": \"killer Devin Kelley briefly escaped\"}, {\"start\": 155.0, \"end\": 158.0, \"text\": \"a New Mexico mental health facility.\"}, {\"start\": 159.0, \"end\": 164.0, \"text\": \"Months before, the shooter pleaded guilty to assaulting his ex-wife and infant\"}, {\"start\": 165.0, \"end\": 170.0, \"text\": \"stepson in 2012.\"}, {\"start\": 171.0, \"end\": 175.0, \"text\": \"A police report shows that while Kelley\"}, {\"start\": 176.0, \"end\": 181.0, \"text\": \"was stationed at Holloman Air\"}, {\"start\": 181.0, \"end\": 185.0, \"text\": \"Force Base he was\"}, {\"start\": 185.0, \"end\": 190.0, \"text\": \"institutionalized for trying to make threats on his commanding\"}, {\"start\": 190.0, \"end\": 194.0, \"text\": \"officer and he was caught trying to\"}, {\"start\": 194.0, \"end\": 198.0, \"text\": \"sneak guns onto the base.\"}, {\"start\": 199.0, \"end\": 204.0, \"text\": \"Separate court documents show that Kelley\"}, {\"start\": 204.0, \"end\": 209.0, \"text\": \"was investigated for sexual assault and rape the following year but\"}, {\"start\": 209.0, \"end\": 213.0, \"text\": \"charges were never filed. Investigators say they have\"}, {\"start\": 214.0, \"end\": 219.0, \"text\": \"been unable to access the shooter's cell phone\"}, {\"start\": 220.0, \"end\": 224.0, \"text\": \"but his social media shows what he was thinking\"}, {\"start\": 225.0, \"end\": 229.0, \"text\": \"before the massacre.\"}, {\"start\": 229.0, \"end\": 234.0, \"text\": \"Kelley also posted a picture of a rifle similar\"}, {\"start\": 235.0, \"end\": 238.0, \"text\": \"to the one used to carry out the attack.\"}, {\"start\": 240.0, \"end\": 246.0, \"text\": \"Today former TV news anchor\"}, {\"start\": 246.0, \"end\": 251.0, \"text\": \"Heather Unruh came\"}, {\"start\": 251.0, \"end\": 256.0, \"text\": \"forward with allegations that actor Kevin Spacey\"}, {\"start\": 256.0, \"end\": 261.0, \"text\": \"sexually assaulted her son. The alleged\"}, {\"start\": 261.0, \"end\": 266.0, \"text\": \"assault took place in July of 2016. She said Spacey\"}, {\"start\": 266.0, \"end\": 269.0, \"text\": \"sexually assaulted her son when he was 18 years old.\"}, {\"start\": 269.0, \"end\": 275.0, \"text\": \"Unruh claims the assault happened in a bar\"}, {\"start\": 275.0, \"end\": 280.0, \"text\": \"in Nantucket, Maine.\"}, {\"start\": 281.0, \"end\": 286.0, \"text\": \"She said Spacey put his hand down her son's\"}, {\"start\": 286.0, \"end\": 291.0, \"text\": \"pants and grabbed his genitals. Unruh said that her son, whose name she never\"}, {\"start\": 291.0, \"end\": 295.0, \"text\": \"mentioned, did not report the crime to the police but\"}, {\"start\": 295.0, \"end\": 300.0, \"text\": \"he did tell her and other family members about the\"}, {\"start\": 301.0, \"end\": 303.0, \"text\": \"assault immediately after it happened.\"}, {\"start\": 304.0, \"end\": 311.0, \"text\": \"The film titled \\\"All the\"}, {\"start\": 311.0, \"end\": 315.0, \"text\": \"Money in the World\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 316.0, \"end\": 320.0, \"text\": \"featuring Kevin Spacey\"}, {\"start\": 321.0, \"end\": 324.0, \"text\": \"as J. Paul Getty\"}, {\"start\": 324.0, \"end\": 328.0, \"text\": \"has pulled out of its top\"}, {\"start\": 328.0, \"end\": 333.0, \"text\": \"spot at the American Film Institute festival after growing sexual harassment\"}, {\"start\": 333.0, \"end\": 336.0, \"text\": \"allegations against Spacey. Deadline.com\"}, {\"start\": 336.0, \"end\": 341.0, \"text\": \"posted a statement from\"}, {\"start\": 341.0, \"end\": 346.0, \"text\": \"Tristar pictures saying it would be\"}, {\"start\": 347.0, \"end\": 353.0, \"text\": \"inappropriate to celebrate at a gala right now.\"}, {\"start\": 353.0, \"end\": 358.0, \"text\": \"However more than 800 people other than Spacey worked\"}, {\"start\": 358.0, \"end\": 363.0, \"text\": \"on the movie and it wouldn't be fair to punish all of them.\"}, {\"start\": 363.0, \"end\": 369.0, \"text\": \"Therefore the movie will open as planned on December 22nd.\"}, {\"start\": 371.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"Would you like to live in a\"}, {\"start\": 376.024, \"end\": 380.024, \"text\": \"life sized Lego house?\"}, {\"start\": 381.0, \"end\": 385.0, \"text\": \"Families can try to win a free overnight stay\"}, {\"start\": 386.0, \"end\": 391.0, \"text\": \"at the new Lego house in Denmark.\"}, {\"start\": 391.0, \"end\": 396.0, \"text\": \"The structure is filled with 25 million\"}, {\"start\": 396.0, \"end\": 401.0, \"text\": \"Lego bricks. The contest is a\"}, {\"start\": 401.0, \"end\": 405.0, \"text\": \"partnership between Lego and Air BnB.\"}, {\"start\": 406.0, \"end\": 407.0, \"text\": \"To enter\"}, {\"start\": 408.0, \"end\": 413.0, \"text\": \"you just have to answer one question.\"}, {\"start\": 413.0, \"end\": 417.0, \"text\": \"If you had an unlimited supply of Lego bricks\"}, {\"start\": 418.0, \"end\": 422.0, \"text\": \"what would you build?\"}, {\"start\": 422.0, \"end\": 428.0, \"text\": \"Answers will be judged on\"}, {\"start\": 428.0, \"end\": 436.0, \"text\": \"originality and creativity.\"}, {\"start\": 436.0, \"end\": 440.0, \"text\": \"The winning family will be flown to the Lego house on\"}, {\"start\": 440.0, \"end\": 445.0, \"text\": \"November 24th. While there they will be treated\"}, {\"start\": 445.0, \"end\": 452.0, \"text\": \"to a personal tour, special meal and other fun events.\"}, {\"start\": 456.0, \"end\": 459.0, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today. I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 459.0, \"end\": 465.0, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News. Remember to like us on Facebook\"}, {\"start\": 465.0, \"end\": 467.0, \"text\": \"and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 467.0, \"end\": 474.0, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "2xqV9Ttjmmg": {
    "video_id": "2xqV9Ttjmmg",
    "title": "Package explodes at Fedex facility in Texas (ASL - 3.20.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180321",
    "duration": 50,
    "view_count": 281,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.44, \"end\": 6.9, \"text\": \"There have been four package explosions in Austin, Texas this month.\"}, {\"start\": 6.9, \"end\": 12.54, \"text\": \"Today a fifth package exploded, this time at a FedEx sorting facility near San Antonio.\"}, {\"start\": 12.54, \"end\": 16.32, \"text\": \"Investigators say the package was traveling along the automated conveyor belt when it exploded.\"}, {\"start\": 16.32, \"end\": 18.12, \"text\": \"One FedEx worker was injured.\"}, {\"start\": 18.12, \"end\": 25.16, \"text\": \"Investigators say they found a second package with explosives packed inside and both packages\"}, {\"start\": 25.2, \"end\": 31.92, \"text\": \"were sent using a private delivery service.\"}, {\"start\": 31.92, \"end\": 36.96, \"text\": \"Authorities are trying to figure out if all the blasts are connected and if it is\"}, {\"start\": 36.96, \"end\": 41.52, \"text\": \"the work of a serial bomber.\"}, {\"start\": 41.52, \"end\": 49.68, \"text\": \"Until they get answers, police are warning everyone in the area to stay on high alert.\"}]"
  },
  "-qkSHWi0ANU": {
    "video_id": "-qkSHWi0ANU",
    "title": "Sign1News Live 2.22.20",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20200223",
    "duration": 950,
    "view_count": 748,
    "description": "TODAY’S HEADLINES:\n\n-Sign1News Black history month: Tour of Atlanta HBCU's\n-Agencies told to look out for staffers disloyal to Trump\n-Police increase reward for missing baby\n-Harry and Meghan to drop 'Sussex Royal' brand\n-Disney unveils long awaited baby Yoda toys\n-Boy leaves puppy at shelter to protect it from abuse",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 9.0, \"end\": 11.48, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 11.48, \"end\": 14.52, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News live.\"}, {\"start\": 14.52, \"end\": 16.64, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 16.66, \"end\": 18.92, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 24.5, \"end\": 35.22, \"text\": \"Today Sign1News wraps up its month-long series of stories in honor of Black History Month.\"}, {\"start\": 35.22, \"end\": 42.56, \"text\": \"Atlanta is considered the cradle of the civil rights movement.\"}, {\"start\": 42.56, \"end\": 52.94, \"text\": \"Sign1News anchor Crystal Cousineau takes us on a tour of Atlanta's five historically black\"}, {\"start\": 52.94, \"end\": 63.94, \"text\": \"colleges and universities (HBCU), whose famous alumni like Martin Luther King Junior led\"}, {\"start\": 63.94, \"end\": 72.66, \"text\": \"the charge in the civil rights movement in the 1960s and whose students today continue\"}, {\"start\": 72.96, \"end\": 76.8, \"text\": \"to carry the torch of equality.\"}, {\"start\": 395.18, \"end\": 406.58, \"text\": \"Sources tell CNN President Trump's new personnel chief John McEntee is trying to root out staff\"}, {\"start\": 406.58, \"end\": 412.16, \"text\": \"who might be disloyal to the President.\"}, {\"start\": 412.169, \"end\": 419.36, \"text\": \"Two years ago McEntee was escorted out of the White House for a clearance issue.\"}, {\"start\": 419.36, \"end\": 427.32, \"text\": \"But now he's among the Trump loyalists brought back to the White House after Trump was acquitted\"}, {\"start\": 427.32, \"end\": 429.86, \"text\": \"in the impeachment trial.\"}, {\"start\": 429.86, \"end\": 437.56, \"text\": \"McEntee runs the personnel office in the West Wing and he's on the lookout for staffers\"}, {\"start\": 437.56, \"end\": 439.86, \"text\": \"seen as disloyal to Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 439.86, \"end\": 448.74, \"text\": \"McEntee reportedly told Cabinet officials to name names, to report to him if they are\"}, {\"start\": 448.74, \"end\": 455.38, \"text\": \"suspicious about people in their agencies and departments and warning changes may be made.\"}, {\"start\": 455.38, \"end\": 462.06, \"text\": \"McEntee is expected to focus on the State and Defense Departments, both at the center\"}, {\"start\": 462.06, \"end\": 464.22, \"text\": \"of Trump's impeachment.\"}, {\"start\": 464.22, \"end\": 477.08, \"text\": \"The decision comes after Trump fired Lieutenant Colonel Alexander Vindman and ambassador to\"}, {\"start\": 477.08, \"end\": 484.1, \"text\": \"the EU Gordon Sondland who were both key impeachment witnesses.\"}, {\"start\": 484.1, \"end\": 494.54, \"text\": \"Trump also named Ric Grenell as the new acting director of national intelligence.\"}, {\"start\": 494.54, \"end\": 504.56, \"text\": \"Grenell is a vocal Trump supporter with little intelligence experience.\"}, {\"start\": 504.56, \"end\": 511.7, \"text\": \"Trump pushed Joseph McGuire out of the job after intelligence officials warned lawmakers\"}, {\"start\": 511.7, \"end\": 521.9, \"text\": \"that Russia is at it again, interfering in the 2020 election, which angered the President,\"}, {\"start\": 521.9, \"end\": 524.84, \"text\": \"who found out about the briefing later.\"}, {\"start\": 524.84, \"end\": 536.26, \"text\": \"Trump dismissed their findings as \\\"another misinformation campaign being launched by\"}, {\"start\": 536.26, \"end\": 541.56, \"text\": \"Democrats\\\" despite that information coming from his own officials.\"}, {\"start\": 546.32, \"end\": 556.38, \"text\": \"Florida officials are offering a bigger reward for finding a baby who went missing after\"}, {\"start\": 556.38, \"end\": 559.06, \"text\": \"a triple homicide.\"}, {\"start\": 559.06, \"end\": 567.66, \"text\": \"The Miami Dade police are looking for baby Andrew Caballerio.\"}, {\"start\": 567.66, \"end\": 575.1, \"text\": \"Wednesday they released this flyer.\"}, {\"start\": 575.11, \"end\": 582.19, \"text\": \"It states the reward for information leading to the child's whereabouts has increased from\"}, {\"start\": 582.19, \"end\": 587.42, \"text\": \"$1,000 to $8,000.\"}, {\"start\": 587.42, \"end\": 592.57, \"text\": \"Baby Andrew disappeared last month.\"}, {\"start\": 592.57, \"end\": 601.773, \"text\": \"Police say Andrew's father Ernesto Caballerio killed his son's mother, grandmother\"}, {\"start\": 601.78, \"end\": 608.3, \"text\": \"and great-grandmother before abducting the baby.\"}, {\"start\": 608.31, \"end\": 612.8, \"text\": \"The baby was one week old at the time.\"}, {\"start\": 612.8, \"end\": 621.08, \"text\": \"Caballerio was later found dead from a self-inflicted gunshot wound in Pasco County.\"}, {\"start\": 626.42, \"end\": 636.32, \"text\": \"Ever since it was agreed that Prince Harry and his wife Meghan would step down as working\"}, {\"start\": 636.32, \"end\": 639.92, \"text\": \"members of the Royal family, questions have swelled as to what they would do about the\"}, {\"start\": 639.92, \"end\": 643.36, \"text\": \"word \\\"Royal\\\" in their brand-name.\"}, {\"start\": 643.36, \"end\": 651.24, \"text\": \"The website they launched only weeks ago is SussexRoyal.com, the instagram handle is\"}, {\"start\": 651.24, \"end\": 654.36, \"text\": \"@SussexRoyal\"}, {\"start\": 654.44, \"end\": 660.16, \"text\": \"and they made trademark applications for the same brand name internationally.\"}, {\"start\": 660.16, \"end\": 670.08, \"text\": \"Now the couple have announced their intention to drop the word Royal from their Sussex Royal brand.\"}, {\"start\": 670.08, \"end\": 675.52, \"text\": \"The decision will be effective after spring 2020.\"}, {\"start\": 675.52, \"end\": 682.0, \"text\": \"That means the couple's new nonprofit organization which is expected to launch in the coming\"}, {\"start\": 682.0, \"end\": 687.6, \"text\": \"weeks will no longer have the word Royal in it.\"}, {\"start\": 687.6, \"end\": 695.6, \"text\": \"And the couple have removed their Sussex Royal trademark application already.\"}, {\"start\": 695.6, \"end\": 704.32, \"text\": \"The rebrand will allow the Duke and Duchess of Sussex to pursue the next chapter in their\"}, {\"start\": 704.32, \"end\": 708.08, \"text\": \"lives and the financial independence to support it.\"}, {\"start\": 711.68, \"end\": 718.08, \"text\": \"Rejoice Star Wars fans!\"}, {\"start\": 718.08, \"end\": 724.46, \"text\": \"The lack of baby Yoda merchandise will soon be a memory.\"}, {\"start\": 724.46, \"end\": 732.2, \"text\": \"Friday Disney revealed a slew of new products in the form of the adorable baby alien called\"}, {\"start\": 732.2, \"end\": 734.76, \"text\": \"\\\"The Child.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 734.76, \"end\": 748.02, \"text\": \"Get ready for action figures, plush dolls, Lego sets, board games and even an animatronic\"}, {\"start\": 748.03, \"end\": 754.92, \"text\": \"baby Yoda that moves, blinks and giggles.\"}, {\"start\": 754.92, \"end\": 762.55, \"text\": \"All this merchandise will fill a void that's been lingering since \\\"The Mandalorian\\\" debuted\"}, {\"start\": 762.55, \"end\": 765.78, \"text\": \"on Disney Plus in November.\"}, {\"start\": 765.78, \"end\": 782.88, \"text\": \"Show runners John Favreau and Dave Filoni had convinced Disney not to produce any toys\"}, {\"start\": 782.88, \"end\": 785.8, \"text\": \"before the show was released so the character could be kept secret.\"}, {\"start\": 785.8, \"end\": 791.4, \"text\": \"That decision was not popular with investors.\"}, {\"start\": 791.4, \"end\": 798.06, \"text\": \"The company experienced flat toy sales during the holiday season.\"}, {\"start\": 798.06, \"end\": 803.68, \"text\": \"The toys are now available for preorder on Disney's website.\"}, {\"start\": 807.7, \"end\": 814.32, \"text\": \"This next story is heartbreaking but it has a happy ending.\"}, {\"start\": 814.32, \"end\": 823.3, \"text\": \"A little boy dropped his pitbull puppy off at a Mexican animal rescue shelter with a\"}, {\"start\": 823.3, \"end\": 825.76, \"text\": \"toy and note attached.\"}, {\"start\": 825.76, \"end\": 833.769, \"text\": \"The note said \\\"My name is Andres and I am 12 years old. I decided to leave my dog in\"}, {\"start\": 833.769, \"end\": 840.14, \"text\": \"your hands, hiding it from my dad because he mistreats and kicks him. One day he kicked\"}, {\"start\": 840.16, \"end\": 845.76, \"text\": \"him so hard that he hurt his tail. I hope you can help and take care of him.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 845.76, \"end\": 850.48, \"text\": \"Andres says he left the toy so the dog would not forget him.\"}, {\"start\": 850.48, \"end\": 857.12, \"text\": \"The rescue group named the dog Rene and posted the letter on its Facebook page.\"}, {\"start\": 857.12, \"end\": 863.0, \"text\": \"As soon as the story was posted the shelter received more than 300 requests to adopt Rene\"}, {\"start\": 863.0, \"end\": 865.2, \"text\": \"from all over the country.\"}, {\"start\": 865.2, \"end\": 871.44, \"text\": \"The puppy is still getting medical attention but will be looking for forever home soon.\"}, {\"start\": 871.44, \"end\": 879.04, \"text\": \"Meanwhile the rescue group was quick to remind people it has 120 other dogs that need a welcoming\"}, {\"start\": 879.04, \"end\": 881.36, \"text\": \"family too.\"}, {\"start\": 885.36, \"end\": 887.72, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 887.72, \"end\": 889.28, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 889.28, \"end\": 891.32, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News live.\"}, {\"start\": 891.32, \"end\": 899.12, \"text\": \"Remember to follow us on all of our social media platforms and be sure to download our app too.\"}, {\"start\": 899.2, \"end\": 904.0, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "09Qc0feFdxE": {
    "video_id": "09Qc0feFdxE",
    "title": "Sign1News 11.15.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171116",
    "duration": 759,
    "view_count": 499,
    "description": "November 15, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-TEHAMA SHOOTING UPDATE\n-UCLA PLAYERS APOLOGIZE, THANK TRUMP\n-REVISED GOP TAX PLAN TARGETS OBAMACARE \n-POLICE SEARCH FOR POWERSAW ROBBERS\n-AUSTRALIA CELEBRATES SAME-SEX MARRIAGE VOTE\n-BLAKE SHELTON PEOPLE'S SEXIEST MAN ALIVE\n-FDA APPROVES FIRST DIGITAL PILL\n-NATIONAL CLEAN OUT YOUR REFRIGERATOR DAY\n-GREAT AMERICAN SMOKEOUT\n-POSSIBLE METEOR SHOOTS ACROSS PHOENIX SKY\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS ",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.0, \"end\": 11.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 11.0, \"end\": 14.0, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 16.0, \"end\": 21.0, \"text\": \"Police continue to search for a motive in the deadly shooting\"}, {\"start\": 22.0, \"end\": 26.0, \"text\": \"rampage Tuesday in northern California.\"}, {\"start\": 27.0, \"end\": 32.0, \"text\": \"Authorities have identified the shooter as\"}, {\"start\": 32.0, \"end\": 37.0, \"text\": \"Kevin Neal. They believe the violence\"}, {\"start\": 37.0, \"end\": 41.0, \"text\": \"may have started the night before when Neal shot\"}, {\"start\": 42.0, \"end\": 47.0, \"text\": \"and killed his wife and then buried her body\"}, {\"start\": 48.0, \"end\": 52.0, \"text\": \"under the floor of their house.\"}, {\"start\": 53.0, \"end\": 56.0, \"text\": \"Police say he shot and killed a neighbor too.\"}, {\"start\": 57.0, \"end\": 60.0, \"text\": \"The next day he stole a pickup truck\"}, {\"start\": 62.0, \"end\": 66.0, \"text\": \"and started firing randomly at people's homes as he\"}, {\"start\": 67.0, \"end\": 72.0, \"text\": \"drove. He rammed the pickup truck into\"}, {\"start\": 72.0, \"end\": 78.0, \"text\": \"a locked gate at Rancho Tehama elementary school.\"}, {\"start\": 79.0, \"end\": 84.0, \"text\": \"The suspect tried to enter the school after spraying the walls and classroom\"}, {\"start\": 84.0, \"end\": 88.0, \"text\": \"with bullets. But thankfully the school\"}, {\"start\": 89.0, \"end\": 93.0, \"text\": \"went into lockdown mode immediately after hearing the shots.\"}, {\"start\": 93.0, \"end\": 98.0, \"text\": \"Neal became frustrated when he couldn't get into the\"}, {\"start\": 98.0, \"end\": 103.0, \"text\": \"school and he left. Then he crashed the\"}, {\"start\": 103.0, \"end\": 108.0, \"text\": \"truck on purpose, stole another car and started shooting again.\"}, {\"start\": 108.0, \"end\": 113.0, \"text\": \"The shooting spree ended after the suspect was shot dead\"}, {\"start\": 113.0, \"end\": 116.0, \"text\": \"during a gun battle with deputies.\"}, {\"start\": 119.0, \"end\": 124.0, \"text\": \"Last week UCLA basketball players\"}, {\"start\": 125.0, \"end\": 129.0, \"text\": \"LiAngelo Ball, Cody\"}, {\"start\": 130.0, \"end\": 135.0, \"text\": \"Riley and Jalen Hill were arrested\"}, {\"start\": 136.0, \"end\": 140.0, \"text\": \"for shoplifting while their team was\"}, {\"start\": 141.0, \"end\": 147.0, \"text\": \"playing a game in China.\"}, {\"start\": 147.0, \"end\": 151.0, \"text\": \"Today the three held a press conference\"}, {\"start\": 152.0, \"end\": 157.0, \"text\": \"to apologize for the shame and embarrassment\"}, {\"start\": 158.0, \"end\": 163.0, \"text\": \"they caused their family, their school and their country.\"}, {\"start\": 164.0, \"end\": 169.0, \"text\": \"They also thanked President Trump and the U.S.\"}, {\"start\": 169.0, \"end\": 173.0, \"text\": \"government for the help they provided in resolving the\"}, {\"start\": 173.0, \"end\": 177.0, \"text\": \"situation and getting them back home safely.\"}, {\"start\": 178.0, \"end\": 183.0, \"text\": \"UCLA head coach Steve Alford\"}, {\"start\": 184.0, \"end\": 189.0, \"text\": \"announced all three players are suspended\"}, {\"start\": 189.0, \"end\": 193.0, \"text\": \"indefinitely. They will not be allowed to travel with the team\"}, {\"start\": 194.0, \"end\": 198.0, \"text\": \"nor will they suit up for home games.\"}, {\"start\": 198.0, \"end\": 203.0, \"text\": \"Alford said at some point they will be able to\"}, {\"start\": 203.0, \"end\": 210.0, \"text\": \"rejoin the team but that timeline has not  been determined.\"}, {\"start\": 213.0, \"end\": 217.0, \"text\": \"On Tuesday night Senate Republicans revealed the latest\"}, {\"start\": 217.0, \"end\": 222.0, \"text\": \"version of their new reform bill.\"}, {\"start\": 222.0, \"end\": 226.0, \"text\": \"Republicans say this one will accomplish two things --\"}, {\"start\": 227.0, \"end\": 231.0, \"text\": \"reduce taxes and repeal the Obamacare\"}, {\"start\": 231.0, \"end\": 236.0, \"text\": \"individual mandate. The individual\"}, {\"start\": 236.0, \"end\": 240.0, \"text\": \"mandate requires individuals to have health insurance\"}, {\"start\": 241.0, \"end\": 246.0, \"text\": \"or pay a penalty.\"}, {\"start\": 246.0, \"end\": 250.0, \"text\": \"By repealing that part of Obamacare Republicans say it will\"}, {\"start\": 250.0, \"end\": 255.0, \"text\": \"free up 338 billion dollars to pay for tax\"}, {\"start\": 255.0, \"end\": 260.0, \"text\": \"cuts. That money would be used to\"}, {\"start\": 260.0, \"end\": 265.0, \"text\": \"modestly reduce income tax rates for middle income taxpayers\"}, {\"start\": 266.0, \"end\": 270.0, \"text\": \"and boost the child tax credit from\"}, {\"start\": 270.0, \"end\": 275.0, \"text\": \"$1650 to $2000. But the\"}, {\"start\": 275.0, \"end\": 279.0, \"text\": \"Congressional Budget Office estimates that repealing the\"}, {\"start\": 279.0, \"end\": 283.0, \"text\": \"mandate would also result in\"}, {\"start\": 284.0, \"end\": 288.0, \"text\": \"13 million fewer people having insurance and\"}, {\"start\": 288.0, \"end\": 293.0, \"text\": \"drive up insurance costs by roughly 10 percent.\"}, {\"start\": 293.0, \"end\": 298.0, \"text\": \"The House begins debate on its bill today.\"}, {\"start\": 298.0, \"end\": 301.0, \"text\": \"A vote is expected tomorrow.\"}, {\"start\": 304.0, \"end\": 308.0, \"text\": \"Police in Houston are looking for two suspects\"}, {\"start\": 309.0, \"end\": 314.0, \"text\": \"that used a power saw to pull\"}, {\"start\": 314.0, \"end\": 318.0, \"text\": \"off a heist.\"}, {\"start\": 318.0, \"end\": 323.0, \"text\": \"A surveillance camera captured the two men\"}, {\"start\": 323.0, \"end\": 327.0, \"text\": \"breaking into a car dealership.\"}, {\"start\": 328.0, \"end\": 333.0, \"text\": \"Sparks flew as the men\"}, {\"start\": 333.0, \"end\": 339.0, \"text\": \"used the power saw on a safe\"}, {\"start\": 339.0, \"end\": 347.0, \"text\": \"for almost an hour.\"}, {\"start\": 347.0, \"end\": 349.0, \"text\": \"To make matters worse\"}, {\"start\": 349.0, \"end\": 357.0, \"text\": \"the robbery took place during Hurricane Harvey\"}, {\"start\": 357.0, \"end\": 365.0, \"text\": \"and police were unable to respond because of the flooding.\"}, {\"start\": 366.0, \"end\": 371.0, \"text\": \"The suspects eventually made off\"}, {\"start\": 371.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"with an undisclosed amount of money.\"}, {\"start\": 376.0, \"end\": 381.0, \"text\": \"If caught they will face stiffer punishment\"}, {\"start\": 381.0, \"end\": 387.0, \"text\": \"for breaking in during a natural disaster.\"}, {\"start\": 390.024, \"end\": 393.999, \"text\": \"Yesterday Australians waited anxiously to hear the results\"}, {\"start\": 394.0, \"end\": 398.0, \"text\": \"of a two month national survey regarding legalizing\"}, {\"start\": 399.0, \"end\": 404.0, \"text\": \"same sex marriage.\"}, {\"start\": 404.0, \"end\": 408.0, \"text\": \"The country tuned in to hear the Prime\"}, {\"start\": 408.0, \"end\": 412.0, \"text\": \"Minister Malcolm Turnbull\"}, {\"start\": 412.024, \"end\": 417.924, \"text\": \"deliver the results.\"}, {\"start\": 420.1, \"end\": 423.1, \"text\": \"When he announced that at least 61 percent of\"}, {\"start\": 423.1, \"end\": 427.0, \"text\": \"Australians voted in favor of marriage equality\"}, {\"start\": 427.0, \"end\": 434.0, \"text\": \"celebrations erupted in every capital city.\"}, {\"start\": 434.024, \"end\": 436.024, \"text\": \"Prime Minister Turnbull says\"}, {\"start\": 437.0, \"end\": 442.0, \"text\": \"parliament will approve the measure and passed legislation\"}, {\"start\": 442.0, \"end\": 448.0, \"text\": \"by the end of the year.\"}, {\"start\": 451.0, \"end\": 458.0, \"text\": \"Congratulations to country music star Blake Shelton.\"}, {\"start\": 459.0, \"end\": 464.0, \"text\": \"He was voted People magazine's 2017\"}, {\"start\": 464.024, \"end\": 471.024, \"text\": \"sexiest man alive.\"}, {\"start\": 471.1, \"end\": 475.0, \"text\": \"Shelton said he was shocked by the news\"}, {\"start\": 475.0, \"end\": 481.0, \"text\": \"and joked that they must be running out of people.\"}, {\"start\": 482.0, \"end\": 486.0, \"text\": \"Shelton said his girlfriend Gwen Stefani\"}, {\"start\": 487.0, \"end\": 493.0, \"text\": \"convinced him to embrace the honor.\"}, {\"start\": 493.001, \"end\": 496.901, \"text\": \"Now Shelton says he'll be able\"}, {\"start\": 497.0, \"end\": 502.0, \"text\": \"to brag about it to Adam Levine, his fellow\"}, {\"start\": 502.0, \"end\": 507.0, \"text\": \"judge on \\\"The Voice\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 507.0, \"end\": 514.0, \"text\": \"and the 2013 sexiest man alive.\"}, {\"start\": 517.024, \"end\": 519.024, \"text\": \"The Food and Drug Administration\"}, {\"start\": 519.1, \"end\": 525.1, \"text\": \"has approved its first digital\"}, {\"start\": 525.1, \"end\": 530.0, \"text\": \"pill. It's called\"}, {\"start\": 530.0, \"end\": 535.0, \"text\": \"Abilify Mycite.\"}, {\"start\": 535.0, \"end\": 539.0, \"text\": \"The pill has a built-in tracking\"}, {\"start\": 540.0, \"end\": 545.0, \"text\": \"device that records when the medication is taken.\"}, {\"start\": 545.001, \"end\": 548.001, \"text\": \"The sensor is activated\"}, {\"start\": 548.1, \"end\": 553.0, \"text\": \"when it comes in contact with fluids in the stomach and\"}, {\"start\": 553.0, \"end\": 559.0, \"text\": \"sends a message to a patch worn on the skin.\"}, {\"start\": 559.0, \"end\": 562.0, \"text\": \"Then the sensor is digested and eliminated from the body.\"}, {\"start\": 563.0, \"end\": 567.0, \"text\": \"The medication system is intended to treat adults\"}, {\"start\": 568.0, \"end\": 573.0, \"text\": \"with schizophrenia, bipolar disease and depression.\"}, {\"start\": 575.001, \"end\": 578.001, \"text\": \"Today is national \\\"Clean Out\"}, {\"start\": 578.1, \"end\": 582.0, \"text\": \"Your Refrigerator\\\" day.\"}, {\"start\": 582.0, \"end\": 587.0, \"text\": \"The day was invented in 1999 to get people\"}, {\"start\": 587.0, \"end\": 590.0, \"text\": \"to clean up their fridges before the Thanksgiving holiday.\"}, {\"start\": 590.024, \"end\": 592.024, \"text\": \"Here are some easy tips\"}, {\"start\": 593.0, \"end\": 597.0, \"text\": \"to get you started.\"}, {\"start\": 597.0, \"end\": 602.0, \"text\": \"Throw away all moldy and expired food,\"}, {\"start\": 603.0, \"end\": 607.0, \"text\": \"completely wipe down the inside\"}, {\"start\": 608.0, \"end\": 612.0, \"text\": \"and get rid of anything you\"}, {\"start\": 612.024, \"end\": 617.924, \"text\": \"have not used in a while.\"}, {\"start\": 620.048, \"end\": 623.048, \"text\": \"Tomorrow is the\"}, {\"start\": 623.1, \"end\": 627.0, \"text\": \"Great American Smokeout.\"}, {\"start\": 627.0, \"end\": 632.0, \"text\": \"Since the 1970s the American Cancer Society\"}, {\"start\": 632.0, \"end\": 635.0, \"text\": \"has dedicated the day to help\"}, {\"start\": 635.024, \"end\": 639.024, \"text\": \"people kick the habit.\"}, {\"start\": 640.025, \"end\": 642.025, \"text\": \"According to the American Cancer Society\"}, {\"start\": 642.1, \"end\": 647.0, \"text\": \"about 36.5 million people in the\"}, {\"start\": 647.0, \"end\": 652.0, \"text\": \"U.S. still smoke.\"}, {\"start\": 652.0, \"end\": 657.0, \"text\": \"Smoking is associated with at least 12 cancers.\"}, {\"start\": 657.0, \"end\": 663.0, \"text\": \"And according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention\"}, {\"start\": 663.0, \"end\": 667.0, \"text\": \"smoking kills 480-thousand\"}, {\"start\": 668.0, \"end\": 675.0, \"text\": \"people in the U.S. every year.\"}, {\"start\": 676.0, \"end\": 681.0, \"text\": \"But experts at the Cancer Society say quitting,\"}, {\"start\": 681.024, \"end\": 687.024, \"text\": \"even for one day, will help improve your health.\"}, {\"start\": 689.0, \"end\": 694.0, \"text\": \"A possible meteor shower lit up the skies over Phoenix\"}, {\"start\": 696.0, \"end\": 703.0, \"text\": \"Tuesday night and it was caught on camera.\"}, {\"start\": 703.0, \"end\": 708.0, \"text\": \"One resident caught this image on camera.\"}, {\"start\": 708.0, \"end\": 713.0, \"text\": \"The streaks of light have not been officially identified but\"}, {\"start\": 714.0, \"end\": 718.0, \"text\": \"all signs point to a meteor show. The latest\"}, {\"start\": 718.0, \"end\": 723.0, \"text\": \"streak of light comes right after the\"}, {\"start\": 724.0, \"end\": 731.0, \"text\": \"Taurid meteor shower which was visible last week.\"}, {\"start\": 734.0, \"end\": 737.0, \"text\": \"Those are your top stories for today. I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 737.024, \"end\": 740.024, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 740.048, \"end\": 745.048, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 745.2, \"end\": 749.2, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "h-0xl-v2Bv4": {
    "video_id": "h-0xl-v2Bv4",
    "title": "New Year's Eve security at all-time high in LV and NY (ASL 12.28.17)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171229",
    "duration": 85,
    "view_count": 64,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.38, \"end\": 4.56, \"text\": \"New Year's Eve is three days away!\"}, {\"start\": 4.56, \"end\": 12.34, \"text\": \"And security preparations are underway in some of the country's most popular party spots right now.\"}, {\"start\": 12.34, \"end\": 21.78, \"text\": \"There will be more than 300 National Guard troops in Las Vegas this New Year's Eve,\"}, {\"start\": 21.78, \"end\": 27.14, \"text\": \"doubling the amount typically on hand.\"}, {\"start\": 27.14, \"end\": 35.02, \"text\": \"And mobile command posts will be staged throughout the city.\"}, {\"start\": 35.02, \"end\": 43.32, \"text\": \"Roughly 1,500 police officers will be patrolling the Las Vegas area over the three-day holiday weekend.\"}, {\"start\": 43.32, \"end\": 50.9, \"text\": \"Security in New York's Time Square will reach unprecedented levels this New Year's Eve.\"}, {\"start\": 50.9, \"end\": 58.76, \"text\": \"This after the city had two terror attacks within the last three months.\"}, {\"start\": 58.76, \"end\": 69.1, \"text\": \"More than 1 million people are expected to ring in the New Year in the Big Apple.\"}, {\"start\": 69.1, \"end\": 83.88, \"text\": \"Despite the increase in police, officials remind the public to report anything suspicious.\"}]"
  },
  "sd_r54bUfQU": {
    "video_id": "sd_r54bUfQU",
    "title": "Sign1News 4.13.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180414",
    "duration": 445,
    "view_count": 1050,
    "description": "4.13.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-Trump calls Comey ‘weak and untruthful slime ball’\n-Madoff victims to receive $504 million in payouts\n-TV producer arrested for the murder of her sister\n-The first black female Marine Corps general nominee\n-Actor Will Ferrell is injured in a car crash\n-Schwarzenegger says he’s feeling much better after heart surgery\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each day to delive",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.02, \"end\": 9.02, \"text\": \"Hello everyone!\"}, {\"start\": 9.02, \"end\": 11.34, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 11.34, \"end\": 12.94, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 12.96, \"end\": 16.4, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 18.72, \"end\": 26.72, \"text\": \"President Trump commented on Twitter about former FBI director James Comey's new book,\"}, {\"start\": 26.72, \"end\": 36.32, \"text\": \"\\\"A Higher Loyalty: Truth, Lies and Leadership.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 36.32, \"end\": 45.38, \"text\": \"The book describes Trump as a compulsive liar who is quote: \\\"unethical and untethered to\"}, {\"start\": 45.38, \"end\": 47.68, \"text\": \"truth.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 47.68, \"end\": 55.92, \"text\": \"The President goes on to say Comey is a proven \\\"leaker and a liar.\"}, {\"start\": 55.92, \"end\": 62.88, \"text\": \"Virtually everyone in Washington thought he should be fired for the terrible job he did\"}, {\"start\": 62.96, \"end\": 66.28, \"text\": \"until he was, in fact, fired.\"}, {\"start\": 66.28, \"end\": 71.76, \"text\": \"He leaked classified information, for which he should be prosecuted.\"}, {\"start\": 71.76, \"end\": 76.24, \"text\": \"He lied to Congress under oath.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 76.24, \"end\": 85.68, \"text\": \"Trump continued, quote: \\\"He is a weak and untruthful slimeball who was, as time has\"}, {\"start\": 85.68, \"end\": 94.56, \"text\": \"proven, a terrible director of the FBI.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 94.56, \"end\": 102.72, \"text\": \"\\\"His handling of the crooked Hillary case, and the events surrounding it, will go down\"}, {\"start\": 102.72, \"end\": 105.76, \"text\": \"as one of the worst botch jobs of history.\"}, {\"start\": 105.76, \"end\": 110.48, \"text\": \"It was my great honor to fire James Comey!\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 113.44, \"end\": 134.56, \"text\": \"People defrauded by Bernie Madoff's company will see a payout of $504 million.\"}, {\"start\": 134.56, \"end\": 144.0, \"text\": \"It is the second payment in a series of payments from the \\\"Madoff Victims Fund.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 144.0, \"end\": 153.12, \"text\": \"Federal officials have recovered $4 billion total through asset seizures which will also\"}, {\"start\": 153.12, \"end\": 155.04, \"text\": \"be returned to victims.\"}, {\"start\": 155.04, \"end\": 165.12, \"text\": \"Madoff pleaded guilty to 11 felonies in 2009.\"}, {\"start\": 165.12, \"end\": 173.36, \"text\": \"He was sentenced to 150 years in prison and ordered to forfeit over $170 billion.\"}, {\"start\": 175.24, \"end\": 186.96, \"text\": \"Police in Los Angeles have arrested a producer because they believe she killed her sister.\"}, {\"start\": 186.96, \"end\": 195.2, \"text\": \"Jill Blackstone produced for TV talk shows like \\\"The Jerry Springer Show.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 195.2, \"end\": 204.96, \"text\": \"According to the LAPD, she was arrested by Baltimore police on charges of murder and\"}, {\"start\": 204.96, \"end\": 208.32, \"text\": \"animal cruelty.\"}, {\"start\": 208.32, \"end\": 214.8, \"text\": \"The police believe that in March 2015 she drugged her sister and placed her in the garage\"}, {\"start\": 214.8, \"end\": 219.44, \"text\": \"of the home they shared in north Hollywood.\"}, {\"start\": 219.44, \"end\": 222.88, \"text\": \"Police also say Blackstone stagged the scene to look like an accident and then set the\"}, {\"start\": 222.88, \"end\": 227.2, \"text\": \"garage on fire.\"}, {\"start\": 227.2, \"end\": 232.72, \"text\": \"Her sister died along with two of her three dogs.\"}, {\"start\": 232.72, \"end\": 236.64, \"text\": \"Detectives say they believe the motive was Blackstone's frustration with the demands\"}, {\"start\": 236.64, \"end\": 243.68, \"text\": \"of providing long-term care to her sister, who was disabled.\"}, {\"start\": 245.52, \"end\": 261.76, \"text\": \"President Trump has nominated Col. Lorna Mahlock to be Brigadier General of the Marine Corps.\"}, {\"start\": 262.0, \"end\": 266.96, \"text\": \"If approved, Mahlock will be the first black female to serve in that position.\"}, {\"start\": 266.96, \"end\": 273.92, \"text\": \"Mahlock is currently a Deputy Director at Corp Headquarters in Washington.\"}, {\"start\": 273.92, \"end\": 284.8, \"text\": \"Previously she served in Okinawa, Japan as a commanding officer where she was in charge\"}, {\"start\": 284.8, \"end\": 290.32, \"text\": \"of 1,300 troops and civilian personnel.\"}, {\"start\": 290.32, \"end\": 294.88, \"text\": \"Women make up just 8 percent of the Marines.\"}, {\"start\": 294.88, \"end\": 302.16, \"text\": \"In 2012 the Marine Corps officials launched a diversity campaign and expect to see an\"}, {\"start\": 302.16, \"end\": 307.28, \"text\": \"increase in the female ranks.\"}, {\"start\": 308.64, \"end\": 318.96, \"text\": \"Former SNL comedian actor Will Ferrell was injured in a rollover car crash in Mission Viejo,\"}, {\"start\": 318.96, \"end\": 322.56, \"text\": \"California.\"}, {\"start\": 322.56, \"end\": 326.5, \"text\": \"The SUV he was riding in was sideswiped by another car causing the vehicle to spin and\"}, {\"start\": 326.54, \"end\": 328.76, \"text\": \"flip over.\"}, {\"start\": 328.92, \"end\": 334.48, \"text\": \"After the crash he was sitting up and talking to emergency crews.\"}, {\"start\": 334.56, \"end\": 337.32, \"text\": \"A total of four people riding in SUV were transported to the hospital.\"}, {\"start\": 337.32, \"end\": 341.08, \"text\": \"Their injuries are unknown.\"}, {\"start\": 341.1, \"end\": 350.16, \"text\": \"Ferrell's rep tells TMZ the actor has been released from the hospital and is doing well.\"}, {\"start\": 351.36, \"end\": 367.2, \"text\": \"Arnold Schwarzenegger updated fans following his recent heart surgery.\"}, {\"start\": 367.2, \"end\": 377.36, \"text\": \"The 70-year-old actor posted a video on Twitter saying he was feeling \\\"good\\\" but not yet \\\"great.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 377.36, \"end\": 386.24, \"text\": \"The former governor of California was released from Cedars-Sinai Hospital last week.\"}, {\"start\": 386.24, \"end\": 396.6, \"text\": \"He got a new pulmonic valve in his heart to replace one doctors put in more than 20 years ago.\"}, {\"start\": 396.6, \"end\": 405.76, \"text\": \"Schwarzenegger explains in the video he is playing chess to keep his mind sharp.\"}, {\"start\": 405.76, \"end\": 413.52, \"text\": \"He should have plenty of time to recover before shooting a sixth Terminator movie, due out\"}, {\"start\": 413.52, \"end\": 415.36, \"text\": \"at the end of next year.\"}, {\"start\": 416.96, \"end\": 419.52, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 419.52, \"end\": 421.84, \"text\": \"I'm Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 421.84, \"end\": 424.88, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 424.88, \"end\": 430.4, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 430.4, \"end\": 432.56, \"text\": \"Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 432.56, \"end\": 434.4, \"text\": \"Your life.\"}, {\"start\": 434.4, \"end\": 438.08, \"text\": \"Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "Tk2RStE3HwM": {
    "video_id": "Tk2RStE3HwM",
    "title": "Florida passes historic gun law (ASL - 3.10.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180310",
    "duration": 74,
    "view_count": 116,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.16, \"end\": 6.78, \"text\": \"Three weeks after the Florida high school massacre, the state passed gun-control restrictions\"}, {\"start\": 6.78, \"end\": 8.52, \"text\": \"into law.\"}, {\"start\": 8.52, \"end\": 13.52, \"text\": \"Under the new law you must be 21 to buy a gun.\"}, {\"start\": 13.54, \"end\": 23.22, \"text\": \"Buying or possessing bump stocks is illegal.\"}, {\"start\": 23.22, \"end\": 33.68, \"text\": \"And law enforcement has more power to seize weapons and ammunition from those deemed mentally\"}, {\"start\": 33.68, \"end\": 36.56, \"text\": \"unfit.\"}, {\"start\": 36.56, \"end\": 42.28, \"text\": \"A controversial portion of the law allows some teachers to be armed but only if the\"}, {\"start\": 42.28, \"end\": 51.46, \"text\": \"local school district and Sheriff's Department agree.\"}, {\"start\": 51.46, \"end\": 62.16, \"text\": \"What isn't included in the legislation is an assault weapons ban.\"}, {\"start\": 62.16, \"end\": 69.28, \"text\": \"The law is named after the school where a 19-year-old opened fire and killed 17 people:\"}, {\"start\": 69.28, \"end\": 73.6, \"text\": \"Marjory Stoneman Douglas high school.\"}]"
  },
  "34wDu7ZhsXs": {
    "video_id": "34wDu7ZhsXs",
    "title": "Sign1News 11.11.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171112",
    "duration": 539,
    "view_count": 318,
    "description": "November 11, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-MOORE SPEAKS OUT AMID SEX ABUSE ALLEGATIONS\n-PROTESTERS CHANT “NO MOORE!”\n-TRUMP TRAVELS TO VIETNAM\n-PUTIN DENIES MEDDLING IN 2016 ELECTIONS\n-TEXAS CHURCH SHOOTING SITE OPENS TO PUBLIC\n-TWIN PEAKS MISTRIAL\n-WALMART UNVEILS BLACK FRIDAY PLANS\n-VETERANS DAY HONORS\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds f",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.0, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 12.0, \"end\": 15.0, \"text\": \"And here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 18.0, \"end\": 23.0, \"text\": \"The sexual abuse allegations against Alabama\"}, {\"start\": 23.0, \"end\": 27.0, \"text\": \"Republican Senate candidate Roy Moore continue to send\"}, {\"start\": 27.0, \"end\": 32.0, \"text\": \"shock waves through Washington D.C. According to a Washington\"}, {\"start\": 32.0, \"end\": 37.0, \"text\": \"Post article when Moore was in his 30s\"}, {\"start\": 37.0, \"end\": 41.0, \"text\": \"he initiated a sexual encounter\"}, {\"start\": 41.0, \"end\": 46.0, \"text\": \"with a 14 year old\"}, {\"start\": 46.0, \"end\": 51.0, \"text\": \"and pursued relationships with three young women between the ages of\"}, {\"start\": 51.0, \"end\": 56.0, \"text\": \"16 and 18. Moore emphatically\"}, {\"start\": 56.0, \"end\": 60.0, \"text\": \"denies the allegations. He says the\"}, {\"start\": 60.0, \"end\": 68.0, \"text\": \"allegations are politically motivated.\"}, {\"start\": 68.0, \"end\": 72.0, \"text\": \"But Moore is not getting a lot of support from fellow Republicans.\"}, {\"start\": 72.0, \"end\": 76.0, \"text\": \"Some Republicans say he needs to drop out of the Senate race if the\"}, {\"start\": 77.0, \"end\": 82.0, \"text\": \"allegations are true. And the National Republican\"}, {\"start\": 82.0, \"end\": 87.0, \"text\": \"Senatorial Committee has ended its fund\"}, {\"start\": 87.0, \"end\": 90.0, \"text\": \"raising arrangement with his campaign.\"}, {\"start\": 91.0, \"end\": 96.0, \"text\": \"Moore shows no indication he plans to drop out of the race.\"}, {\"start\": 97.0, \"end\": 102.0, \"text\": \"This weekend Moore spoke at a Veterans Day\"}, {\"start\": 102.0, \"end\": 110.0, \"text\": \"program in Birmingham Alabama.\"}, {\"start\": 111.0, \"end\": 115.0, \"text\": \"It was his first public speaking event since the sexual abuse allegations.\"}, {\"start\": 116.0, \"end\": 120.0, \"text\": \"As Moore was arriving to walk in the building a few\"}, {\"start\": 120.0, \"end\": 124.0, \"text\": \"protesters were waiting outside.\"}, {\"start\": 124.0, \"end\": 129.0, \"text\": \"They were chanting \\\"No Moore! \\\"No Moore!\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 132.0, \"end\": 136.0, \"text\": \"President Trump is just about to wrap up his\"}, {\"start\": 136.0, \"end\": 141.0, \"text\": \"12 day tour of Asia.\"}, {\"start\": 141.0, \"end\": 145.0, \"text\": \"Today he was in Hanoi Vietnam.\"}, {\"start\": 145.0, \"end\": 150.0, \"text\": \"He would only stay there for a short time to attend a state dinner.\"}, {\"start\": 150.0, \"end\": 157.0, \"text\": \"During the dinner he praised Vietnam. He called the country the greatest\"}, {\"start\": 157.0, \"end\": 163.0, \"text\": \"miracle in the world for its decades of economic reform.\"}, {\"start\": 169.0, \"end\": 173.0, \"text\": \"While President Trump was in Da Nang\"}, {\"start\": 174.0, \"end\": 179.0, \"text\": \"he and Russia's leader Vladimir Putin\"}, {\"start\": 179.0, \"end\": 184.0, \"text\": \"briefly met during the Asia Pacific\"}, {\"start\": 184.0, \"end\": 189.0, \"text\": \"Economic Cooperation summit.\"}, {\"start\": 189.024, \"end\": 190.999, \"text\": \"Trump told reporters that he and\"}, {\"start\": 191.0, \"end\": 196.0, \"text\": \"Putin discussed the issue of Russian meddling in the U.S. elections.\"}, {\"start\": 196.0, \"end\": 200.0, \"text\": \"According to Trump, Putin said that he\"}, {\"start\": 200.0, \"end\": 204.0, \"text\": \"absolutely did not interfere in last year's presidential race.\"}, {\"start\": 204.024, \"end\": 205.999, \"text\": \"Trump said he took\"}, {\"start\": 206.0, \"end\": 212.0, \"text\": \"Putin at his word and said the Russian leader felt insulted by the question.\"}, {\"start\": 212.0, \"end\": 215.0, \"text\": \"But the U.S. intelligence community\"}, {\"start\": 216.0, \"end\": 221.0, \"text\": \"concluded in January that\"}, {\"start\": 221.0, \"end\": 228.0, \"text\": \"Putin himself ordered an influence campaign into the election.\"}, {\"start\": 229.0, \"end\": 234.0, \"text\": \"Intelligence officials say they have high\"}, {\"start\": 234.0, \"end\": 241.0, \"text\": \"confidence that Russia tried to help Trump win the race.\"}, {\"start\": 245.0, \"end\": 249.0, \"text\": \"First Baptist Church in Sutherland\"}, {\"start\": 249.0, \"end\": 254.0, \"text\": \"Springs Texas opened its doors to the public today,\"}, {\"start\": 256.0, \"end\": 263.0, \"text\": \"a week after the shooting that killed 26 people.\"}, {\"start\": 263.001, \"end\": 265.975, \"text\": \"The scene has been turned into a memorial.\"}, {\"start\": 266.0, \"end\": 270.0, \"text\": \"Officials say visitors will be allowed to see a memorial\"}, {\"start\": 270.0, \"end\": 275.0, \"text\": \"that pays tribute to the victims.\"}, {\"start\": 275.0, \"end\": 280.0, \"text\": \"The church says the memorial was put up by volunteers as part of a\"}, {\"start\": 280.0, \"end\": 286.0, \"text\": \"healing process for the community.\"}, {\"start\": 286.0, \"end\": 291.0, \"text\": \"However the church will not be there for long.\"}, {\"start\": 291.0, \"end\": 294.0, \"text\": \"Recently the pastor announced he is tearing the church down.\"}, {\"start\": 295.0, \"end\": 300.0, \"text\": \"He says the church is a stark reminder of the violence that happened there.\"}, {\"start\": 300.0, \"end\": 302.0, \"text\": \"Tearing it down is the best way to move forward.\"}, {\"start\": 302.024, \"end\": 307.024, \"text\": \"He plans on planting a prayer garden on the land once the church is gone.\"}, {\"start\": 309.0, \"end\": 313.0, \"text\": \"The trial of biker gang leader Jake Carrizal\"}, {\"start\": 314.0, \"end\": 320.0, \"text\": \"has ended in a mistrial.\"}, {\"start\": 320.0, \"end\": 324.0, \"text\": \"Carrizall was charged with\"}, {\"start\": 324.0, \"end\": 329.0, \"text\": \"organizing a brawl in May of 2015 against a\"}, {\"start\": 329.0, \"end\": 334.0, \"text\": \"rival biker gang. The brawl turned into\"}, {\"start\": 334.0, \"end\": 340.0, \"text\": \"a deadly gun battle. Nine people were killed, 20 others wounded.\"}, {\"start\": 340.0, \"end\": 344.0, \"text\": \"Carrizall was charged with engaging\"}, {\"start\": 344.0, \"end\": 349.0, \"text\": \"in organized crime activity and\"}, {\"start\": 349.0, \"end\": 353.0, \"text\": \"directing the actions of a criminal gang.\"}, {\"start\": 353.0, \"end\": 357.0, \"text\": \"After hours of deliberation the jury\"}, {\"start\": 358.0, \"end\": 362.0, \"text\": \"was unable to reach a unanimous verdict on any of the counts.\"}, {\"start\": 362.0, \"end\": 367.0, \"text\": \"So the judge declared a mistrial. That means prosecutors\"}, {\"start\": 368.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"will have to start over again with a new trial.\"}, {\"start\": 379.024, \"end\": 383.924, \"text\": \"Wal-Mart has announced\"}, {\"start\": 384.0, \"end\": 389.0, \"text\": \"it will be open on Thanksgiving Day. That means eager shoppers\"}, {\"start\": 389.0, \"end\": 393.0, \"text\": \"will be able to get a head start on holiday discounts\"}, {\"start\": 394.0, \"end\": 398.0, \"text\": \"whether they're shopping online or headed to the store.\"}, {\"start\": 398.0, \"end\": 403.0, \"text\": \"If you're shopping online sale prices will begin at\"}, {\"start\": 403.0, \"end\": 407.0, \"text\": \"12:01 a.m. Thanksgiving morning.\"}, {\"start\": 407.0, \"end\": 412.0, \"text\": \"If you're going to a store discounts will be available starting at 6:00 p.m.\"}, {\"start\": 412.0, \"end\": 417.0, \"text\": \"Target and Toys R Us will also open early\"}, {\"start\": 417.0, \"end\": 425.0, \"text\": \"for people who would rather shop than eat turkey.\"}, {\"start\": 425.0, \"end\": 427.4, \"text\": \"It turns out there are plenty of folks who want just that.\"}, {\"start\": 427.524, \"end\": 429.524, \"text\": \"A recent survey found that\"}, {\"start\": 430.0, \"end\": 435.0, \"text\": \"58 percent of people want to shop on the holiday.\"}, {\"start\": 435.0, \"end\": 442.0, \"text\": \"In 2016 only 40 percent of those surveyed say they'd shop on Thanksgiving day.\"}, {\"start\": 445.024, \"end\": 446.999, \"text\": \"Today is the 64th annual National\"}, {\"start\": 447.0, \"end\": 452.0, \"text\": \"Veterans Day observance.\"}, {\"start\": 453.0, \"end\": 458.0, \"text\": \"People around the world honored and celebrated\"}, {\"start\": 458.024, \"end\": 464.024, \"text\": \"those who are willing to sacrifice their lives for freedom.\"}, {\"start\": 464.1, \"end\": 471.0, \"text\": \"In Washington D.C. Vice President Mike Pence\"}, {\"start\": 471.0, \"end\": 476.0, \"text\": \"observed the day by volunteering to help clean\"}, {\"start\": 476.0, \"end\": 481.0, \"text\": \"the wall at the Vietnam Veterans Memorial and he participated in a\"}, {\"start\": 481.0, \"end\": 489.0, \"text\": \"wreath laying ceremony at the tomb of the unknown soldier.\"}, {\"start\": 490.0, \"end\": 494.0, \"text\": \"In New York one of the nation's largest\"}, {\"start\": 494.0, \"end\": 499.0, \"text\": \"Veterans Day parades commemorated the 100 year anniversary of\"}, {\"start\": 499.0, \"end\": 507.0, \"text\": \"America's entry into the first World War in 1917.\"}, {\"start\": 510.001, \"end\": 512.001, \"text\": \"Those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 512.1, \"end\": 517.1, \"text\": \"I am Crystal Cousineau. Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 518.0, \"end\": 523.0, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 523.0, \"end\": 531.0, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "1zk5fa3SqOY": {
    "video_id": "1zk5fa3SqOY",
    "title": "Adorable puppies go to Disneyland! (ASL - 4.4.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180405",
    "duration": 56,
    "view_count": 192,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.7, \"end\": 9.56, \"text\": \"A group of service dogs took a field trip to the happiest place on earth -- Disneyland.\"}, {\"start\": 9.56, \"end\": 16.1, \"text\": \"And the images are going viral on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 16.1, \"end\": 25.7, \"text\": \"Meet Essie, Aryssa, Ortega and Chekov.\"}, {\"start\": 25.7, \"end\": 30.72, \"text\": \"They are a group of service dogs in training as canine companions to enhance the lives\"}, {\"start\": 30.72, \"end\": 35.28, \"text\": \"of people with disabilities.\"}, {\"start\": 35.28, \"end\": 42.28, \"text\": \"The trip to Disneyland was designed to improve their social skills.\"}, {\"start\": 42.28, \"end\": 49.12, \"text\": \"The fun-loving pups nosed their way around the park and even made new friends.\"}, {\"start\": 49.12, \"end\": 54.86, \"text\": \"They also patiently pose for photos until they were dog-gone tired.\"}]"
  },
  "oocYh8NQAKQ": {
    "video_id": "oocYh8NQAKQ",
    "title": "Sign1News 3.7.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180308",
    "duration": 510,
    "view_count": 793,
    "description": "3.7.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-GVRA proposed policy change infuriates deaf community\n-Florida school shooter indicted on 34 counts\n-Dwyane Wade surprises Stoneman Douglas students\n-Porn star sues Trump\n-Nor’easter round 2\n-Fleeing suspect gets run over by his own car\n-10-year old runs to school as punishment\n-Fans to decide which M&M flavor will stay\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world ",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.38, \"end\": 8.64, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 8.64, \"end\": 10.44, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.44, \"end\": 12.32, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 12.32, \"end\": 16.06, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 21.62, \"end\": 27.42, \"text\": \"If you live in Georgia, we have some important information to share with you regarding the\"}, {\"start\": 27.42, \"end\": 31.28, \"text\": \"Georgia Vocational Rehabilitation Agency (GVRA).\"}, {\"start\": 31.28, \"end\": 43.62, \"text\": \"The agency is proposing a change to remove Gallaudet University and National Technical\"}, {\"start\": 43.62, \"end\": 46.84, \"text\": \"Institute for the Deaf from its list of approved schools for college funding.\"}, {\"start\": 46.84, \"end\": 54.62, \"text\": \"Instead the agency wants to expand in-state college options and use interpreters.\"}, {\"start\": 54.62, \"end\": 59.5, \"text\": \"The proposed change will impact the Deaf community and it is urging people to let their voices\"}, {\"start\": 59.5, \"end\": 63.88, \"text\": \"be heard and fight by showing up in mass at the upcoming public hearings.\"}, {\"start\": 63.88, \"end\": 68.38, \"text\": \"Here are the dates, times and locations:\"}, {\"start\": 68.38, \"end\": 81.04, \"text\": \"March 13th, March 15th, March 20th, March 21st, March 22nd and April 19th.\"}, {\"start\": 81.04, \"end\": 90.0, \"text\": \"If you cannot make the public hearings, you can complete a comment form on the GVRA website.\"}, {\"start\": 90.0, \"end\": 91.86, \"text\": \"Here is the address.\"}, {\"start\": 93.2, \"end\": 104.86, \"text\": \"Today a grand jury indicted Florida school shooter Nikolas Cruz on 34 counts, 17 counts\"}, {\"start\": 104.88, \"end\": 109.66, \"text\": \"of premeditated murder and 17 counts of attempted murder.\"}, {\"start\": 109.66, \"end\": 116.92, \"text\": \"The 19-year-old is accused of gunning down students and teachers at Marjory Stoneman\"}, {\"start\": 116.92, \"end\": 120.78, \"text\": \"Douglas high school on February 14th.\"}, {\"start\": 120.78, \"end\": 130.04, \"text\": \"Cruz's lawyer says he is on suicide watch in a single-man jail cell, isolated from everyone else.\"}, {\"start\": 130.12, \"end\": 138.2, \"text\": \"His lawyer also said he's willing to plead guilty to avoid the death penalty.\"}, {\"start\": 139.84, \"end\": 151.76, \"text\": \"Last week NBA star Dwyane Wade was overcome with emotions when he found out one of the victims of the\"}, {\"start\": 151.76, \"end\": 161.6, \"text\": \"Marjory Stoneman Douglas high school shooting was buried in his NBA jersey.\"}, {\"start\": 161.92, \"end\": 166.4, \"text\": \"Today Wade paid a surprise visit to the students.\"}, {\"start\": 166.4, \"end\": 173.28, \"text\": \"This was the first full day of school since the shooting last month.\"}, {\"start\": 173.36, \"end\": 177.84, \"text\": \"Wade posed for pictures and just hung out.\"}, {\"start\": 177.84, \"end\": 181.36, \"text\": \"He said he was looking forward to the important and impactful things the students have planned\"}, {\"start\": 181.36, \"end\": 183.28, \"text\": \"and he wants to be a part of it.\"}, {\"start\": 185.68, \"end\": 196.8, \"text\": \"Porn star Stormy Daniels is suing President Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 196.8, \"end\": 202.88, \"text\": \"She wants to invalidate the non-disclosure agreement she signed days before the 2016\"}, {\"start\": 202.96, \"end\": 206.18, \"text\": \"election that prevented her from talking about their alleged sexual encounter.\"}, {\"start\": 206.18, \"end\": 217.06, \"text\": \"The lawsuit argues that the agreement not to disclose the relationship is null and void\"}, {\"start\": 217.12, \"end\": 220.0, \"text\": \"because it was not signed by Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 220.0, \"end\": 227.8, \"text\": \"According to the complaint, Daniels had an intimate relationship with Trump that began\"}, {\"start\": 227.84, \"end\": 232.02, \"text\": \"in the summer of 2006 and continued well into 2007.\"}, {\"start\": 232.08, \"end\": 242.0, \"text\": \"Daniel's lawyer said Trump purposely did not sign the agreement so he could later, if need\"}, {\"start\": 242.0, \"end\": 252.12, \"text\": \"be, publicly deny any knowledge of the contract and Miss Daniels.\"}, {\"start\": 252.12, \"end\": 258.68, \"text\": \"The White House did not immediately respond to CNN's request for a comment and President\"}, {\"start\": 258.68, \"end\": 264.58, \"text\": \"Trump has vehemently denied any sexual encounter.\"}, {\"start\": 266.94, \"end\": 274.12, \"text\": \"For the second time in a week a nor'easter is dumping snow across parts of the East Coast.\"}, {\"start\": 274.12, \"end\": 281.22, \"text\": \"More than 50 million people from Maryland to Maine are under winter storm warnings and watches.\"}, {\"start\": 281.22, \"end\": 284.15, \"text\": \"And more than 2,000 flights have been canceled.\"}, {\"start\": 284.15, \"end\": 288.98, \"text\": \"Many companies are sending their employees home early.\"}, {\"start\": 288.98, \"end\": 293.68, \"text\": \"Transportation officials say if you don't have to be on the road, stay home.\"}, {\"start\": 293.68, \"end\": 304.18, \"text\": \"Officials in Massachusetts say they've had to use drones to assess beach damage because\"}, {\"start\": 304.18, \"end\": 309.44, \"text\": \"of the continuous high tides.\"}, {\"start\": 309.54, \"end\": 319.26, \"text\": \"Some residents are now in a race against time to rebuild the seawall to protect their homes\"}, {\"start\": 319.3, \"end\": 321.18, \"text\": \"from the storm surge.\"}, {\"start\": 323.0, \"end\": 328.26, \"text\": \"A suspect in Virginia trying to flee from a police pursuit runs himself over with his\"}, {\"start\": 328.3, \"end\": 330.46, \"text\": \"own car.\"}, {\"start\": 330.46, \"end\": 339.2, \"text\": \"Thirty-year-old Isaac Bonsu took off in his car when police tried to pull him over.\"}, {\"start\": 339.2, \"end\": 345.94, \"text\": \"But when he drove down a dead-end street, he jumped out and tried to run.\"}, {\"start\": 345.94, \"end\": 353.22, \"text\": \"One problem: He forgot to put the car in park and it runs him over.\"}, {\"start\": 353.22, \"end\": 354.58, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 364.42, \"end\": 367.58, \"text\": \"Bonsu was not injured.\"}, {\"start\": 367.58, \"end\": 369.4, \"text\": \"He was charged with DWI.\"}, {\"start\": 374.34, \"end\": 383.42, \"text\": \"Ten-year-old Hayden Thornhill was kicked off his school bus for bullying other children.\"}, {\"start\": 383.42, \"end\": 393.62, \"text\": \"His dad says he does not tolerate bullying so he punished Hayden by making him run a\"}, {\"start\": 393.62, \"end\": 401.66, \"text\": \"mile to school for all three days of his suspension.\"}, {\"start\": 401.66, \"end\": 405.96, \"text\": \"And he documented the punishment by posting the video on Facebook.\"}, {\"start\": 405.96, \"end\": 410.34, \"text\": \"The video has already gotten more than 25 million views.\"}, {\"start\": 410.34, \"end\": 416.38, \"text\": \"Some are applauding the Dad's approach; others say the dad is being a bully himself.\"}, {\"start\": 416.5, \"end\": 418.48, \"text\": \"Tell us what you think.\"}, {\"start\": 418.48, \"end\": 424.74, \"text\": \"Do you agree with the punishment or is it abusive?\"}, {\"start\": 428.5, \"end\": 435.32, \"text\": \"On Wednesday the candy company M&amp;Ms announced that it was introducing three new flavors.\"}, {\"start\": 435.32, \"end\": 440.96, \"text\": \"But only one flavor will stay on the shelves.\"}, {\"start\": 440.96, \"end\": 456.02, \"text\": \"Crunchy Espresso, Crunchy Raspberry and Crunchy Mint will be a part of a flavor vote campaign.\"}, {\"start\": 456.02, \"end\": 461.1, \"text\": \"People who try the candies can vote on whether they like snacking on chocolates that taste\"}, {\"start\": 461.1, \"end\": 469.56, \"text\": \"like a morning cup of coffee, something tart or something minty fresh.\"}, {\"start\": 469.56, \"end\": 476.7, \"text\": \"Fans can cast their vote by text or on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 479.76, \"end\": 482.72, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 482.72, \"end\": 484.28, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 484.28, \"end\": 487.32, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 487.32, \"end\": 493.42, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 493.42, \"end\": 500.86, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "dbFMTM6uXMw": {
    "video_id": "dbFMTM6uXMw",
    "title": "Dr. G answers your questions: Is there a cure for coronavirus? (4.27.20)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20200427",
    "duration": 98,
    "view_count": 349,
    "description": "",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en-US",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.3, \"end\": 10.8, \"text\": \"Many people are wondering when will this be over, will there be a vaccine or cure and\"}, {\"start\": 10.8, \"end\": 13.98, \"text\": \"if someone can get it again.\"}, {\"start\": 14.12, \"end\": 21.84, \"text\": \"I want to tell you that what we know right now, and everything is changing rapidly, but\"}, {\"start\": 21.84, \"end\": 25.58, \"text\": \"right now we know there is no cure.\"}, {\"start\": 25.589, \"end\": 30.64, \"text\": \"Maybe we're hoping research will start discovering different medicines but right now we don't\"}, {\"start\": 30.64, \"end\": 34.269, \"text\": \"see one to help cure this.\"}, {\"start\": 34.269, \"end\": 42.6, \"text\": \"Secondly there will be a vaccine in the future but not right now.\"}, {\"start\": 42.6, \"end\": 52.539, \"text\": \"Starting today they are learning about and developing new vaccines where I live in Pittsburgh\"}, {\"start\": 52.54, \"end\": 61.04, \"text\": \"but it still needs more testing, study and research to be sure it's safe.\"}, {\"start\": 61.04, \"end\": 68.44, \"text\": \"They are still researching how the virus develops and spread and what it can and cannot do.\"}, {\"start\": 68.44, \"end\": 73.18, \"text\": \"I want a fast vaccine too but we have to wait.\"}, {\"start\": 73.18, \"end\": 77.58, \"text\": \"And thirdly, if someone gets sick, can they become sick again?\"}, {\"start\": 77.58, \"end\": 85.76, \"text\": \"Right now they're starting to see that people who became sick and got better do have some\"}, {\"start\": 85.76, \"end\": 87.96, \"text\": \"protect themselves for a few months.\"}, {\"start\": 87.96, \"end\": 94.8, \"text\": \"We don't know if that protection lasts forever, until next year or six months.\"}, {\"start\": 94.82, \"end\": 96.26, \"text\": \"We just don't know yet.\"}]"
  },
  "BakdKfSMj1M": {
    "video_id": "BakdKfSMj1M",
    "title": "9-1-1 calls reveal Florida shooter’s troubled life (ASL - 2.24.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180224",
    "duration": 154,
    "view_count": 109,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.78, \"end\": 12.74, \"text\": \"In the days since the massacre at Marjory Stoneman Douglas high school, more information\"}, {\"start\": 12.74, \"end\": 18.64, \"text\": \"is coming out about the shooter Nikolas Cruz.\"}, {\"start\": 18.64, \"end\": 24.76, \"text\": \"Newly released 911 calls reveal a troubled young man who was\"}, {\"start\": 24.76, \"end\": 27.74, \"text\": \"often at odds with law enforcement.\"}, {\"start\": 27.74, \"end\": 35.88, \"text\": \"From 2008 to 2016, there were at least 39 calls for service at Cruz's home.\"}, {\"start\": 35.88, \"end\": 39.56, \"text\": \"Many of the calls were made by Cruz's mother.\"}, {\"start\": 39.56, \"end\": 49.42, \"text\": \"Additional calls came from other family members he stayed with following her death last November.\"}, {\"start\": 49.42, \"end\": 55.0, \"text\": \"Here is the transcript of one of those 911 calls:\"}, {\"start\": 55.0, \"end\": 58.06, \"text\": \"\\\"911 emergency how can I help you?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 58.06, \"end\": 62.52, \"text\": \"\\\"Yeah there was a fight in my house a kid and my son.\"}, {\"start\": 62.52, \"end\": 69.88, \"text\": \"I need someone here because I'm afraid he comes back and he has a lot of weapons.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 69.88, \"end\": 72.5, \"text\": \"\\\"What kind of weapon ma'am?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 72.5, \"end\": 74.16, \"text\": \"\\\"Let me ask my son.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 74.16, \"end\": 77.28, \"text\": \"\\\"What kind of weapon did he get?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 77.34, \"end\": 79.98, \"text\": \"\\\"A Remington.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 79.98, \"end\": 83.5, \"text\": \"\\\"Oh... and who did this?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 83.5, \"end\": 87.4, \"text\": \"\\\"Nikolas Cruz.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 87.4, \"end\": 96.44, \"text\": \"As Cruz got older his behavior became more alarming.\"}, {\"start\": 96.44, \"end\": 104.38, \"text\": \"Callers told 911 dispatchers they were scared he would hurt them or himself, especially once\"}, {\"start\": 104.38, \"end\": 108.5, \"text\": \"he was old enough to purchase weapons.\"}, {\"start\": 108.5, \"end\": 114.62, \"text\": \"Here's a transcript from another 911 call:\"}, {\"start\": 114.62, \"end\": 120.2, \"text\": \"\\\"He also dug in the backyard because he knew he was not allowed to bring it here and we\"}, {\"start\": 120.2, \"end\": 121.84, \"text\": \"found that he did.\"}, {\"start\": 121.84, \"end\": 124.66, \"text\": \"He was going to bury the gun there.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 124.66, \"end\": 132.74, \"text\": \"Then last month another call came, this time to the FBI tip line.\"}, {\"start\": 132.74, \"end\": 141.74, \"text\": \"A woman close to Cruz called saying she feared Cruz was at a breaking point and worried about\"}, {\"start\": 141.74, \"end\": 147.34, \"text\": \"him getting into a school and just shooting the place up.\"}, {\"start\": 147.34, \"end\": 152.4, \"text\": \"The FBI later admitted it failed to investigate that tip.\"}]"
  },
  "yxagowRBBvU": {
    "video_id": "yxagowRBBvU",
    "title": "Sign1News 12.5.2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171206",
    "duration": 611,
    "view_count": 387,
    "description": "December 5, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-NEW WILDFIRES BREAK OUT IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA\n-SUPREME COURT HEARS SAME-SEX WEDDING CAKE CASE\n-IOC BANS RUSSIA FROM 2018 OLYMPICS\n-NEARLY $7M SPENT ON RUSSIA INVESTIGATION\n-REP. CONYERS RESIGNS\n-OPRAH SELLS MAJORITY STAKE IN \"OWN\" TO DISCOVERY\n-KROGER RECALLS WATER FOR INFANTS DUE TO MOLD\n-CAUGHT ON CAMERA: OFFICER SAVES BABY'S LIFE\n-CHEESECAKE FACTORY GIVING AWAY 10K FREE SLICES",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.98, \"end\": 11.78, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 11.82, \"end\": 12.92, \"text\": \"I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 13.02, \"end\": 15.02, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 15.64, \"end\": 25.26, \"text\": \"Officials in Southern California are going door-to-door telling everyone to get out!\"}, {\"start\": 25.26, \"end\": 33.44, \"text\": \"A fast-moving fire forced 27,000 people to evacuate their homes.\"}, {\"start\": 33.5, \"end\": 42.16, \"text\": \"Howling Santa Ana winds are fueling the raging fire.\"}, {\"start\": 42.2, \"end\": 56.18, \"text\": \"The fires are spreading from Southern California's rural hills into populated neighborhoods.\"}, {\"start\": 56.18, \"end\": 61.46, \"text\": \"Within minutes some neighborhoods went up in flames.\"}, {\"start\": 61.5, \"end\": 68.08, \"text\": \"In Los Angeles County 11,000 acres are scorched.\"}, {\"start\": 68.14, \"end\": 76.98, \"text\": \"In Ventura 45,000 acres and 150 buildings are destroyed.\"}, {\"start\": 77.0, \"end\": 81.98, \"text\": \"Firefighters have not said what started the fire.\"}, {\"start\": 84.12, \"end\": 99.34, \"text\": \"Five years ago Charlie Craig and David Mullins went to Masterpiece Cakeshop\"}, {\"start\": 99.4, \"end\": 101.54, \"text\": \"in Lakewood, Colorado.\"}, {\"start\": 101.56, \"end\": 114.16, \"text\": \"They wanted one of Jack Phillips' cakes for their wedding.\"}, {\"start\": 114.18, \"end\": 125.7, \"text\": \"Phillips told them \\\"Sorry I don't do cakes for same-sex weddings.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 125.78, \"end\": 128.22, \"text\": \"The couple sued Phillips.\"}, {\"start\": 128.26, \"end\": 135.04, \"text\": \"Now the case has made it all the way to the Supreme Court.\"}, {\"start\": 135.06, \"end\": 141.8, \"text\": \"The issue: whether Phillips had the legal right to turn away the couple.\"}, {\"start\": 141.9, \"end\": 151.1, \"text\": \"Phillips said making the cake for them went against his Christian faith.\"}, {\"start\": 151.12, \"end\": 155.76, \"text\": \"Craig and Mullins argue it's discrimination.\"}, {\"start\": 155.8, \"end\": 162.24, \"text\": \"Today the Supreme Court heard both sides of the case.\"}, {\"start\": 162.26, \"end\": 167.48, \"text\": \"The Trump administration sides with Phillips.\"}, {\"start\": 167.58, \"end\": 171.56, \"text\": \"If the Supreme Court rules in favor of Phillips\"}, {\"start\": 171.58, \"end\": 175.68, \"text\": \"it will widen how religious liberty is applied to other businesses.\"}, {\"start\": 175.68, \"end\": 182.32, \"text\": \"LGBT rights advocates fear the outcome could overshadow the court's 2015 ruling legalizing\"}, {\"start\": 182.36, \"end\": 187.8, \"text\": \"same-sex marriage nationwide.\"}, {\"start\": 190.6, \"end\": 203.52, \"text\": \"The International Olympic Committee has banned Russia from competing in the 2018 Winter Olympics.\"}, {\"start\": 203.52, \"end\": 209.66, \"text\": \"After a lengthy investigation the IOC determined Russian athletes were cheating\"}, {\"start\": 209.7, \"end\": 216.14, \"text\": \"via a state-sponsored doping system.\"}, {\"start\": 216.14, \"end\": 223.7, \"text\": \"Athletes who have clean drug tests will be allowed to compete\"}, {\"start\": 223.78, \"end\": 230.08, \"text\": \"but under the Olympic flag -- not the Russian flag.\"}, {\"start\": 230.08, \"end\": 235.64, \"text\": \"Some Russian officials say the punishment is unfair and are calling for a\"}, {\"start\": 235.66, \"end\": 237.38, \"text\": \"complete boycott of the Olympic Games.\"}, {\"start\": 237.44, \"end\": 249.96, \"text\": \"The Winter Olympics will take place in Pyeongchang, South Korea in two months.\"}, {\"start\": 251.4, \"end\": 260.12, \"text\": \"Today the Justice Department revealed the amount of money that has been spent investigating\"}, {\"start\": 260.16, \"end\": 263.54, \"text\": \"Russian meddling in the presidential election.\"}, {\"start\": 263.6, \"end\": 269.0, \"text\": \"The amount: nearly $7 million over five months.\"}, {\"start\": 269.06, \"end\": 281.84, \"text\": \"Special Counsel Robert Mueller spent $3.2 million between May and September.\"}, {\"start\": 281.85, \"end\": 289.629, \"text\": \"Another $3.5 million has been spent by law enforcement personnel working on the investigation\"}, {\"start\": 289.629, \"end\": 292.58, \"text\": \"but who do not directly report to Mueller.\"}, {\"start\": 292.6, \"end\": 303.2, \"text\": \"Mueller was appointed in May to lead the investigation into Russian meddling into the 2016 election.\"}, {\"start\": 305.12, \"end\": 315.66, \"text\": \"Representative John Conyers Jr., the longest-serving current member of the House of Representatives\"}, {\"start\": 315.68, \"end\": 325.28, \"text\": \"and the longest-serving African-American in history, says he will retire from Congress.\"}, {\"start\": 325.36, \"end\": 331.48, \"text\": \"He made the announcement on a Detroit radio show today.\"}, {\"start\": 331.48, \"end\": 336.3, \"text\": \"The announcement comes as several women have come forward in the past few weeks accusing\"}, {\"start\": 336.3, \"end\": 339.319, \"text\": \"him of sexual harassment.\"}, {\"start\": 339.32, \"end\": 342.68, \"text\": \"Conyers denies the allegations and maintains his innocence.\"}, {\"start\": 344.36, \"end\": 362.86, \"text\": \"Oprah Winfrey is selling part of her stake in the Oprah Winfrey Network to Discovery.\"}, {\"start\": 362.94, \"end\": 370.58, \"text\": \"Currently \\\"OWN\\\" is a 50-50 joint venture between Winfrey and Discovery.\"}, {\"start\": 370.62, \"end\": 383.04, \"text\": \"But Discovery announced Monday it would pay $70 million to increase its stake to 75%.\"}, {\"start\": 383.06, \"end\": 391.38, \"text\": \"Winfrey will remain chief executive and will work exclusively for the channel through 2025.\"}, {\"start\": 394.56, \"end\": 408.14, \"text\": \"Kroger is recalling Comforts for Baby purified water after mold was discovered.\"}, {\"start\": 408.22, \"end\": 417.82, \"text\": \"The purified water with fluoride was sold in 1 gallon clear containers.\"}, {\"start\": 417.82, \"end\": 425.02, \"text\": \"After receiving customer complaints, the grocery store chain tested the water\"}, {\"start\": 425.1, \"end\": 427.68, \"text\": \"and identified the mold.\"}, {\"start\": 427.68, \"end\": 436.7, \"text\": \"But the Food and Drug Administration says the mold is not visible to the naked eye.\"}, {\"start\": 436.7, \"end\": 445.02, \"text\": \"The FDA says exposure can cause skin and respiratory irritation.\"}, {\"start\": 445.08, \"end\": 451.34, \"text\": \"According to officials, infants with an already compromised immune system\"}, {\"start\": 451.38, \"end\": 453.78, \"text\": \"may be at an increased risk.\"}, {\"start\": 453.82, \"end\": 458.74, \"text\": \"Kroger has pulled the product from its shelves.\"}, {\"start\": 458.84, \"end\": 465.52, \"text\": \"If you've purchased the water, you can return it to the store for a refund.\"}, {\"start\": 465.6, \"end\": 471.96, \"text\": \"More details about the recall can be found on FDA.gov.\"}, {\"start\": 474.48, \"end\": 483.44, \"text\": \"On December 1st a Savannah, Georgia police officer's action saved a one-month-old baby\"}, {\"start\": 483.48, \"end\": 493.48, \"text\": \"who was choking -- and his body camera captured everything!\"}, {\"start\": 493.6, \"end\": 497.04, \"text\": \"Take a look.\"}, {\"start\": 497.2, \"end\": 504.32, \"text\": \"Officer William Eng responded to a call about a non-responsive infant on the third floor\"}, {\"start\": 504.56, \"end\": 508.24, \"text\": \"of an apartment complex.\"}, {\"start\": 508.4, \"end\": 517.12, \"text\": \"After administering chest compressions for about a minute, the baby began to cry.\"}, {\"start\": 517.12, \"end\": 521.44, \"text\": \"The officer's quick actions saved the infant's life.\"}, {\"start\": 521.52, \"end\": 533.52, \"text\": \"Officer Eng and the family were later reunited at police headquarters.\"}, {\"start\": 536.16, \"end\": 548.64, \"text\": \"The Cheesecake Factory is in the holiday spirit.\"}, {\"start\": 548.96, \"end\": 552.96, \"text\": \"Starting Wednesday you can get a free slice of cheesecake.\"}, {\"start\": 552.96, \"end\": 557.92, \"text\": \"To take advantage of this deal, customers must place the delivery order through Doordash\"}, {\"start\": 558.24, \"end\": 561.28, \"text\": \"and enter a special code at checkout.\"}, {\"start\": 561.44, \"end\": 568.8, \"text\": \"Only one slice per household, so there will likely be some sharing.\"}, {\"start\": 569.76, \"end\": 576.32, \"text\": \"More information on the promotion is posted on the Doordash website.\"}, {\"start\": 576.8, \"end\": 580.0, \"text\": \"This promotion ends December 12th.\"}, {\"start\": 582.24, \"end\": 584.72, \"text\": \"And those your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 584.78, \"end\": 586.32, \"text\": \"I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 586.32, \"end\": 589.08, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 589.16, \"end\": 594.48, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 594.64, \"end\": 601.88, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "12V41Um9QS4": {
    "video_id": "12V41Um9QS4",
    "title": "Sign1News 2.21.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180222",
    "duration": 570,
    "view_count": 1144,
    "description": "2.21.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).  \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-Students walk out of school across the country\n-Trump hosts listening session with shooting survivors\n-Billy Graham passes away\n-Wendy Williams taking show hiatus for health reasons\n-Dog attacked by moose in backyard\n-Alcohol could help you live past 90\n-“Hobby Lobby Challenge” takes over Twitter\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to of",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.08, \"end\": 9.78, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.78, \"end\": 12.24, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 12.24, \"end\": 13.62, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 13.62, \"end\": 17.0, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.34, \"end\": 28.46, \"text\": \"Thousands of students across the country walked out of their schools to protest gun laws and\"}, {\"start\": 28.46, \"end\": 30.58, \"text\": \"demand school safety.\"}, {\"start\": 30.58, \"end\": 36.42, \"text\": \"These are images from Tallahassee, Florida.\"}, {\"start\": 36.42, \"end\": 42.66, \"text\": \"Students stormed the state Capitol rotunda, demanding to be heard.\"}, {\"start\": 42.66, \"end\": 47.6, \"text\": \"Some students said they were turned away from legislators' offices.\"}, {\"start\": 47.6, \"end\": 51.48, \"text\": \"They were told meetings were \\\"by appointment\\\" only.\"}, {\"start\": 51.48, \"end\": 55.72, \"text\": \"That's when students started shouting \\\"Vote them out!\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 55.72, \"end\": 64.74, \"text\": \"This was the scene in Washington, DC as hundreds of teens walked out of their schools in support\"}, {\"start\": 64.74, \"end\": 69.06, \"text\": \"of the students at Marjory Stoneman Douglas high school.\"}, {\"start\": 69.06, \"end\": 78.38, \"text\": \"They boarded a train at Union Station and marched to the Capitol to call for action\"}, {\"start\": 78.38, \"end\": 82.2, \"text\": \"on gun violence.\"}, {\"start\": 82.2, \"end\": 89.2, \"text\": \"Students at Coral Springs high school in Florida walked out and sent a message of peace by\"}, {\"start\": 89.2, \"end\": 97.12, \"text\": \"forming a giant heart in the middle of the football field.\"}, {\"start\": 100.26, \"end\": 112.3, \"text\": \"A few hours after the school walkouts, President Trump hosted a listening session at the White\"}, {\"start\": 112.3, \"end\": 120.98, \"text\": \"House with people affected by high profile mass shootings across the country.\"}, {\"start\": 120.98, \"end\": 127.3, \"text\": \"All of the survivors urged President Trump to do something now to prevent shootings like\"}, {\"start\": 127.31, \"end\": 132.59, \"text\": \"the one in Parkland, Florida from ever happening again.\"}, {\"start\": 132.59, \"end\": 143.359, \"text\": \"Many suggested banning the sale of the AR-15 rifle, improving gun sale background checks\"}, {\"start\": 143.36, \"end\": 146.98, \"text\": \"as well as addressing the problem of mental health.\"}, {\"start\": 146.98, \"end\": 156.98, \"text\": \"Trump said he would be closely looking at the idea of secretly arming teachers and coaches\"}, {\"start\": 156.98, \"end\": 164.08, \"text\": \"so they can stop school shooters before first responders arrived on the scene.\"}, {\"start\": 167.48, \"end\": 175.8, \"text\": \"Reverend Billy Graham died this morning at his home in North Carolina.\"}, {\"start\": 175.8, \"end\": 177.56, \"text\": \"He was 99 years old.\"}, {\"start\": 177.56, \"end\": 188.7, \"text\": \"Graham has been referred to as \\\"America's Pastor\\\" who provided hope to millions during\"}, {\"start\": 188.72, \"end\": 190.2, \"text\": \"times of tragedy.\"}, {\"start\": 190.2, \"end\": 194.62, \"text\": \"He worked tirelessly to preach his inclusive brand of evangelical Christianity to hundreds\"}, {\"start\": 194.62, \"end\": 196.84, \"text\": \"of millions in 185 countries.\"}, {\"start\": 196.84, \"end\": 202.6, \"text\": \"His influence even extended to the White House where he ministered to every president since\"}, {\"start\": 202.6, \"end\": 208.82, \"text\": \"Harry Truman, Republican and Democrat.\"}, {\"start\": 208.82, \"end\": 216.16, \"text\": \"His message broke down cultural and racial barriers.\"}, {\"start\": 216.16, \"end\": 222.0, \"text\": \"He served as a model and influence for Christians around the world.\"}, {\"start\": 222.0, \"end\": 229.12, \"text\": \"And even though his life has ended, his legacy will be lasting.\"}, {\"start\": 231.84, \"end\": 242.36, \"text\": \"Talk show host Wendy Williams is taking a break from her show.\"}, {\"start\": 242.36, \"end\": 250.25, \"text\": \"The 53-year-old announced on Wednesday's show that she has been diagnosed with Graves' disease\"}, {\"start\": 250.25, \"end\": 255.78, \"text\": \"and will be taking three weeks off to focus on her health.\"}, {\"start\": 255.78, \"end\": 268.02, \"text\": \"Graves' disease is an autoimmune disorder that causes overstimulation of the thyroid.\"}, {\"start\": 268.02, \"end\": 278.14, \"text\": \"A representative for Williams says they will run old episodes during her absence.\"}, {\"start\": 278.14, \"end\": 290.34, \"text\": \"The TV personality joked on Wednesday saying \\\"I'll be back. I'm not an heiress.\"}, {\"start\": 290.34, \"end\": 292.82, \"text\": \"Who is going to pay my bills?\"}, {\"start\": 292.82, \"end\": 295.02, \"text\": \"Are you serious?\"}, {\"start\": 295.02, \"end\": 300.72, \"text\": \"I'm just saying, I come from working class.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 304.22, \"end\": 313.44, \"text\": \"A dog named Daisy is recovering after a frightening attack by angry moose.\"}, {\"start\": 313.44, \"end\": 325.18, \"text\": \"It happened in Kim Mahosky's backyard in Anchorage, Alaska.\"}, {\"start\": 325.18, \"end\": 333.18, \"text\": \"Mahosky says she wasn't aware of the moose when she let her dogs outside to play.\"}, {\"start\": 333.18, \"end\": 335.96, \"text\": \"That's when she heard a commotion.\"}, {\"start\": 335.96, \"end\": 343.54, \"text\": \"A mama moose had jumped over the fence and started attacking Daisy.\"}, {\"start\": 343.54, \"end\": 346.88, \"text\": \"The other dog was able to get away.\"}, {\"start\": 346.88, \"end\": 352.86, \"text\": \"The whole thing was caught on a surveillance camera.\"}, {\"start\": 352.86, \"end\": 359.42, \"text\": \"A warning, some viewers may find this video a little unsettling.\"}, {\"start\": 368.86, \"end\": 376.86, \"text\": \"Daisy suffered a 4 inch gash across her back and had to undergo surgery but she is on the\"}, {\"start\": 376.86, \"end\": 378.62, \"text\": \"road to recovery.\"}, {\"start\": 378.62, \"end\": 389.26, \"text\": \"Mahosky is hoping her story will warn others of the dangers moose can pose.\"}, {\"start\": 391.82, \"end\": 401.58, \"text\": \"Dr. Claudia Kawas, a researcher from the University of California, says reaching for a wine glass\"}, {\"start\": 401.58, \"end\": 409.76, \"text\": \"rather than a dumbbell may help you live longer.\"}, {\"start\": 409.76, \"end\": 417.94, \"text\": \"Kawas studied 1,700 people who lived until at least 90 and found that the people who\"}, {\"start\": 417.94, \"end\": 425.96, \"text\": \"drank two glasses of wine or beer a night reduced their chances of dying prematurely\"}, {\"start\": 425.96, \"end\": 430.28, \"text\": \"by 18 percent.\"}, {\"start\": 430.28, \"end\": 441.12, \"text\": \"But before you cancel your gym membership, the study also found that 15 to 40 minutes\"}, {\"start\": 441.12, \"end\": 447.08, \"text\": \"of daily physical activity reduce the risk of early death by 11 percent.\"}, {\"start\": 447.08, \"end\": 457.08, \"text\": \"And people who spend two hours a day on a hobby are 21 percent less likely to die early.\"}, {\"start\": 457.08, \"end\": 465.34, \"text\": \"Dr. Kawas admits she does not know why modest drinking seems to help people live longer\"}, {\"start\": 465.34, \"end\": 473.56, \"text\": \"but she firmly believes it improves longevity.\"}, {\"start\": 476.98, \"end\": 493.12, \"text\": \"A new viral photo trend is blowing up twitter but it's ticking off Hobby Lobby employees.\"}, {\"start\": 493.12, \"end\": 504.42, \"text\": \"It's called the \\\"Hobby Lobby Challenge\\\" where people take impromptu photo shoots in Hobby\"}, {\"start\": 504.42, \"end\": 507.5, \"text\": \"Lobby's plastic flower aisle.\"}, {\"start\": 507.5, \"end\": 515.24, \"text\": \"The internet is loving it but Hobby Lobby employees are complaining the trend is disrupting\"}, {\"start\": 515.24, \"end\": 517.22, \"text\": \"their workplace.\"}, {\"start\": 517.22, \"end\": 535.16, \"text\": \"Anyway, like the Mannequin Challenge and the Cinnamon Challenge, it looks like the Hobby\"}, {\"start\": 535.16, \"end\": 543.5, \"text\": \"Lobby Challenge is here to stay...for now.\"}, {\"start\": 546.52, \"end\": 549.08, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 549.08, \"end\": 550.84, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 550.84, \"end\": 553.06, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 553.06, \"end\": 557.2, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 557.2, \"end\": 562.22, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "Pn8OOeENZOw": {
    "video_id": "Pn8OOeENZOw",
    "title": "First Lady spokesperson tweets on Stormy interview (ASL - 3.26.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180327",
    "duration": 40,
    "view_count": 144,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.62, \"end\": 9.02, \"text\": \"First Lady Melania Trump's communications director did respond via twitter but did not\"}, {\"start\": 9.02, \"end\": 14.46, \"text\": \"directly address the Stormy Daniels' interview.\"}, {\"start\": 14.46, \"end\": 29.72, \"text\": \"It said: \\\"While I know the media is enjoying speculation and salacious gossip, I'd like\"}, {\"start\": 29.72, \"end\": 36.54, \"text\": \"to remind people there is a minor child whose name should be kept out of news stories when\"}, {\"start\": 36.64, \"end\": 38.88, \"text\": \"at all possible.\\\"\"}]"
  },
  "Jw6U4Wkcjxg": {
    "video_id": "Jw6U4Wkcjxg",
    "title": "Democrats push for release of second memo (ASL - 2.5.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180206",
    "duration": 71,
    "view_count": 82,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.92, \"end\": 15.88, \"text\": \"The second chapter of Washington DC's memo saga could be coming soon.\"}, {\"start\": 15.88, \"end\": 19.8, \"text\": \"There is a push among Democrats, and some Republicans, to release a memo that rebuts\"}, {\"start\": 19.8, \"end\": 23.22, \"text\": \"allegations of FBI surveillance abuses.\"}, {\"start\": 23.22, \"end\": 25.22, \"text\": \"Democrats on the House Intelligence Committee may call for a vote Monday to release their\"}, {\"start\": 25.22, \"end\": 26.72, \"text\": \"memo on the FBI.\"}, {\"start\": 26.72, \"end\": 28.92, \"text\": \"This report is expected to contradict claims made in the Republican-led memo that was released\"}, {\"start\": 28.92, \"end\": 31.36, \"text\": \"Friday.\"}, {\"start\": 31.36, \"end\": 36.88, \"text\": \"Republicans blocked the release of the Democratic memo last week but have since said they'd\"}, {\"start\": 36.96, \"end\": 39.12, \"text\": \"vote to released the memo.\"}, {\"start\": 39.12, \"end\": 48.0, \"text\": \"Senator Chuck Schumer is calling on President Trump to back the release of the second memo,\"}, {\"start\": 48.0, \"end\": 54.04, \"text\": \"saying it is \\\"a matter of fundamental fairness.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 54.04, \"end\": 57.76, \"text\": \"And some Republicans are on board.\"}, {\"start\": 57.76, \"end\": 61.08, \"text\": \"If the committee votes in favor of putting out the memo, the issue then goes to President\"}, {\"start\": 61.08, \"end\": 63.56, \"text\": \"Trump.\"}, {\"start\": 63.56, \"end\": 69.72, \"text\": \"He would have five days to make a decision on the release.\"}]"
  },
  "KeFFF9SeFd0": {
    "video_id": "KeFFF9SeFd0",
    "title": "October 9, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171010",
    "duration": 525,
    "view_count": 129,
    "description": "October 9, 2017\nNews for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).\n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-CALIFORNIA WILDFIRES\n-HURRICANE NATE CLEAN UP\n-COAST GUARD AIRLIFTS SUPPLIES TO PUERTO RICO\n-TROPICAL STORM OPHELIA\n-POLICE BODY CAM SHOOTING\n-HARVEY WEINSTEIN FIRED\n-DOVE APOLOGIZES\n-MAN BRING SHEEP TO PROTEST\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have backgrounds from notable organizations such as GALLAUDET UNIVERSITY, CN",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.0, \"end\": 12.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News. I am Candace\"}, {\"start\": 13.0, \"end\": 17.0, \"text\": \"Jones. Here are your top stories of the day.\"}, {\"start\": 20.0, \"end\": 25.0, \"text\": \"In California's Napa County\"}, {\"start\": 26.0, \"end\": 29.0, \"text\": \"fire crews are battling\"}, {\"start\": 30.0, \"end\": 33.0, \"text\": \"several wildfires.\"}, {\"start\": 35.0, \"end\": 39.0, \"text\": \"One fire spread has to more than\"}, {\"start\": 40.0, \"end\": 44.0, \"text\": \"200 acres. That's because strong\"}, {\"start\": 45.0, \"end\": 50.0, \"text\": \"gusty winds causing the fire to spread.\"}, {\"start\": 50.0, \"end\": 55.0, \"text\": \"There are reports of at least three structures in that\"}, {\"start\": 55.0, \"end\": 60.0, \"text\": \"area suffering some damage.\"}, {\"start\": 60.0, \"end\": 65.0, \"text\": \"Mandatory evacuations are in place for some\"}, {\"start\": 65.0, \"end\": 68.0, \"text\": \"spots. So far there have been no deaths reported.\"}, {\"start\": 71.0, \"end\": 75.0, \"text\": \"Yesterday hurricane Nate hit Alabama,\"}, {\"start\": 75.0, \"end\": 80.0, \"text\": \"Mississippi and Louisiana. Today was\"}, {\"start\": 80.0, \"end\": 84.0, \"text\": \"cleanup day for the people living along the Gulf\"}, {\"start\": 84.0, \"end\": 86.0, \"text\": \"Coast.\"}, {\"start\": 86.0, \"end\": 91.0, \"text\": \"Luckily the storm only caused\"}, {\"start\": 91.0, \"end\": 96.0, \"text\": \"minor damage -- mostly fallen trees and\"}, {\"start\": 96.0, \"end\": 100.0, \"text\": \"flooding. About ten thousand people\"}, {\"start\": 100.0, \"end\": 105.0, \"text\": \"across the southeast don't have electricity.\"}, {\"start\": 105.0, \"end\": 109.0, \"text\": \"That means there may be possible travel\"}, {\"start\": 110.0, \"end\": 114.0, \"text\": \"delays. However many stores and\"}, {\"start\": 114.0, \"end\": 120.0, \"text\": \"casinos already back open for business.\"}, {\"start\": 123.0, \"end\": 128.0, \"text\": \"In Puerto Rico work continues to get\"}, {\"start\": 128.0, \"end\": 133.0, \"text\": \"much needed aid to the hardest hit areas.\"}, {\"start\": 133.0, \"end\": 139.0, \"text\": \"This is video from the U.S. Coast Guard.\"}, {\"start\": 140.0, \"end\": 144.0, \"text\": \"It shows a rescuer being lowered\"}, {\"start\": 145.0, \"end\": 150.0, \"text\": \"from a helicopter to deliver food\"}, {\"start\": 150.0, \"end\": 154.0, \"text\": \"and water to residents. The Coast Guard\"}, {\"start\": 155.0, \"end\": 159.0, \"text\": \"has to use a helicopter because many\"}, {\"start\": 159.0, \"end\": 164.0, \"text\": \"people are stranded in areas where the\"}, {\"start\": 164.0, \"end\": 167.0, \"text\": \"roads are washed out.\"}, {\"start\": 169.0, \"end\": 174.0, \"text\": \"Take a look at this. Can you believe it?\"}, {\"start\": 174.0, \"end\": 178.0, \"text\": \"Another tropical storm has\"}, {\"start\": 178.0, \"end\": 183.0, \"text\": \"formed. This storm is named Ophelia.\"}, {\"start\": 183.0, \"end\": 188.0, \"text\": \"This morning the storm strengthened from a depression\"}, {\"start\": 189.0, \"end\": 193.0, \"text\": \"to a tropical storm. Later this week forecasters believe\"}, {\"start\": 193.0, \"end\": 197.0, \"text\": \"Ophelia could become a\"}, {\"start\": 198.0, \"end\": 203.0, \"text\": \"hurricane. The good news\"}, {\"start\": 203.0, \"end\": 208.0, \"text\": \"is it won't be much of a threat to land.\"}, {\"start\": 208.0, \"end\": 212.0, \"text\": \"The storm is far east of the U.S. mainland\"}, {\"start\": 213.0, \"end\": 218.0, \"text\": \"and continues to move in that direction.\"}, {\"start\": 220.0, \"end\": 225.0, \"text\": \"This is a picture of a police officer's body cam video.\"}, {\"start\": 225.0, \"end\": 230.0, \"text\": \"The video is frozen. You can\"}, {\"start\": 230.0, \"end\": 234.0, \"text\": \"clearly see a man with his hands in the air.\"}, {\"start\": 234.0, \"end\": 239.0, \"text\": \"Officers in North Carolina ended up shooting and killing\"}, {\"start\": 239.0, \"end\": 243.0, \"text\": \"this man. Police in Charlotte\"}, {\"start\": 244.0, \"end\": 248.0, \"text\": \"say on September 9th a man\"}, {\"start\": 248.0, \"end\": 253.0, \"text\": \"called 911 and said he was drinking alcohol and\"}, {\"start\": 253.0, \"end\": 258.0, \"text\": \"wanted to be picked up. 911 operators said the man\"}, {\"start\": 258.0, \"end\": 263.0, \"text\": \"was incoherent at times and they asked him several times\"}, {\"start\": 263.0, \"end\": 268.0, \"text\": \"why he was calling. The man repeatedly said the gun was not\"}, {\"start\": 268.0, \"end\": 269.0, \"text\": \"loaded.\"}, {\"start\": 271.0, \"end\": 276.0, \"text\": \"Officers arrived and yelled at the man in English\"}, {\"start\": 276.0, \"end\": 281.0, \"text\": \"and Spanish to put his hands up.\"}, {\"start\": 281.0, \"end\": 286.0, \"text\": \"They ended up shooting and killing him. Again in the picture\"}, {\"start\": 286.0, \"end\": 291.0, \"text\": \"you can see both of the man's hands are in the air. It's not\"}, {\"start\": 291.0, \"end\": 296.0, \"text\": \"clear if the man was holding a gun.\"}, {\"start\": 296.0, \"end\": 301.0, \"text\": \"Both officers are on administrative leave pending\"}, {\"start\": 301.0, \"end\": 303.0, \"text\": \"the outcome of two\"}, {\"start\": 304.0, \"end\": 309.0, \"text\": \"investigations.\"}, {\"start\": 310.0, \"end\": 315.0, \"text\": \"Yesterday the board of directors at the\"}, {\"start\": 316.0, \"end\": 321.0, \"text\": \"Weinstein Company announced that they were firing the\"}, {\"start\": 321.0, \"end\": 324.0, \"text\": \"man who started the company --\"}, {\"start\": 324.0, \"end\": 329.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood film executive Harvey Weinstein.\"}, {\"start\": 331.0, \"end\": 335.0, \"text\": \"Weinstein has been accused by\"}, {\"start\": 335.0, \"end\": 340.0, \"text\": \"several women of sexual harassment.\"}, {\"start\": 340.0, \"end\": 345.0, \"text\": \"An article in the New York Times says the allegations of sexual\"}, {\"start\": 345.0, \"end\": 350.0, \"text\": \"misconduct go back almost 30 years.\"}, {\"start\": 350.0, \"end\": 355.0, \"text\": \"Weinstein denied some of\"}, {\"start\": 355.0, \"end\": 360.0, \"text\": \"those allegations but he admitted sometimes\"}, {\"start\": 360.0, \"end\": 364.0, \"text\": \"he behaved improperly during his career and\"}, {\"start\": 365.0, \"end\": 371.0, \"text\": \"he apologized for causing pain.\"}, {\"start\": 371.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"On Sunday night he did not comment any further after news of\"}, {\"start\": 376.0, \"end\": 381.0, \"text\": \"his termination.\"}, {\"start\": 381.0, \"end\": 385.0, \"text\": \"The soap company Dove is apologizing after complaints\"}, {\"start\": 386.0, \"end\": 390.0, \"text\": \"about an ad it released over the weekend.\"}, {\"start\": 390.0, \"end\": 395.0, \"text\": \"On Friday a three second ad appeared on the company's\"}, {\"start\": 395.0, \"end\": 400.0, \"text\": \"Facebook page. The beginning of it showed a black woman\"}, {\"start\": 400.0, \"end\": 406.0, \"text\": \"taking off a brown shirt to reveal a white woman.\"}, {\"start\": 406.0, \"end\": 411.0, \"text\": \"Screenshots of the ad went viral\"}, {\"start\": 415.0, \"end\": 419.0, \"text\": \"on Facebook and Twitter with many complaints. The company tweeted\"}, {\"start\": 420.0, \"end\": 427.0, \"text\": \"an apology saying it had missed the mark in representing women of color.\"}, {\"start\": 428.0, \"end\": 431.0, \"text\": \"Yesterday dove issued a statement saying it did not represent the\"}, {\"start\": 431.0, \"end\": 436.0, \"text\": \"diversity of real beauty.\"}, {\"start\": 439.0, \"end\": 443.0, \"text\": \"An Australian shoe maker and\"}, {\"start\": 443.0, \"end\": 448.0, \"text\": \"several sheep traveled to California to protest\"}, {\"start\": 448.5, \"end\": 456.5, \"text\": \"outside of Dekker's brands global headquarters.\"}, {\"start\": 457.0, \"end\": 461.0, \"text\": \"The man wanted to demonstrate how the company is\"}, {\"start\": 462.0, \"end\": 468.0, \"text\": \"\\\"pulling the wool\\\" over the eyes of customers and\"}, {\"start\": 468.2, \"end\": 472.2, \"text\": \"\\\"fleecing\\\" Australian Ugg bootmaker\"}, {\"start\": 472.6, \"end\": 479.6, \"text\": \"Eddie Oygur. The bootmaker says Decker is\"}, {\"start\": 480.0, \"end\": 485.0, \"text\": \"suing him for making Ugg boots.\"}, {\"start\": 485.1, \"end\": 489.0, \"text\": \"The company says Oygur stole\"}, {\"start\": 489.0, \"end\": 495.0, \"text\": \"their trademark.\"}, {\"start\": 498.0, \"end\": 502.0, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for the day. I am Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 502.0, \"end\": 507.0, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News. And remember to \\\"Like\\\" us on Facebook.\"}, {\"start\": 509.0, \"end\": 512.0, \"text\": \"Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 512.024, \"end\": 516.024, \"text\": \"Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "-5H_8K2k7-4": {
    "video_id": "-5H_8K2k7-4",
    "title": "Rallies, protests break out all over the country (ASL - 2.26.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180227",
    "duration": 85,
    "view_count": 109,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.36, \"end\": 8.06, \"text\": \"Rallies and protests have sprung up all over the country.\"}, {\"start\": 8.06, \"end\": 19.58, \"text\": \"Today in Florida, thousands of protesters marched on the Capitol steps in Tallahassee\"}, {\"start\": 19.58, \"end\": 22.7, \"text\": \"demanding gun law reform.\"}, {\"start\": 22.7, \"end\": 31.48, \"text\": \"Every public school in West Virginia has been shut down for three days because of a massive\"}, {\"start\": 31.48, \"end\": 33.7, \"text\": \"teacher walkout.\"}, {\"start\": 33.7, \"end\": 42.24, \"text\": \"Today thousands of teachers and school service employees protested at the state Capitol,\"}, {\"start\": 42.24, \"end\": 47.38, \"text\": \"demanding better pay and benefits.\"}, {\"start\": 47.38, \"end\": 58.6, \"text\": \"And \\\"Day of Action\\\" rallies took place in several cities over the weekend, including\"}, {\"start\": 58.6, \"end\": 65.76, \"text\": \"New York, Chicago, Phoenix and Columbus, Ohio.\"}, {\"start\": 65.76, \"end\": 74.22, \"text\": \"Union workers orchestrated the rallies to protest a Supreme Court case currently under\"}, {\"start\": 74.22, \"end\": 83.58, \"text\": \"review that would force non-union workers to pay union dues.\"}]"
  },
  "l0_D2ZgkE7o": {
    "video_id": "l0_D2ZgkE7o",
    "title": "Sign1News 1.12.18 - News in American Sign Language (ASL)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180113",
    "duration": 559,
    "view_count": 1709,
    "description": "1.12.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Trump ignores reporters at MLK, Jr. ceremony\n-Cadaver dogs search for mudslide victims\n-Funeral of 14-year old bully victim\n-Highway shootout caught on camera\n-Jeff Bezos donating $33M to Dreamers for College\n-Video of hospital patient left out on cold street\n-Carrie Underwood & Ludacris team up for Super Bowl\n-Barking dog saves family’s life\n\nSign1News is the first and only digital networ",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 5.98, \"end\": 6.98, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 6.98, \"end\": 8.54, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 8.54, \"end\": 9.96, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 9.96, \"end\": 12.98, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 14.44, \"end\": 26.86, \"text\": \"President Trump is still being slammed by people around the world for using vulgar language\"}, {\"start\": 26.86, \"end\": 33.38, \"text\": \"while discussing Haitian and African immigrants coming into the US.\"}, {\"start\": 33.38, \"end\": 46.08, \"text\": \"Today Trump attended a ceremony honoring civil rights icon Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.\"}, {\"start\": 46.08, \"end\": 52.5, \"text\": \"Reporters shouted questions like \\\"Will you give an apology for the statement yesterday?\"}, {\"start\": 52.5, \"end\": 55.5, \"text\": \"and \\\"Are you a racist?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 55.5, \"end\": 57.74, \"text\": \"Trump ignored them.\"}, {\"start\": 57.74, \"end\": 65.84, \"text\": \"But later, in a series of tweets, Trump denied using profanity.\"}, {\"start\": 65.84, \"end\": 79.4, \"text\": \"However Illinois Senator Dick Durbin was in the room and he said Trump used those hate-filled\"}, {\"start\": 79.4, \"end\": 82.16, \"text\": \"words and he said them repeatedly.\"}, {\"start\": 82.16, \"end\": 91.4, \"text\": \"The comments have been condemned by members of both parties.\"}, {\"start\": 93.34, \"end\": 99.16, \"text\": \"In Southern California rescue teams and cadaver dogs dig through knee-deep mud looking for\"}, {\"start\": 99.16, \"end\": 101.96, \"text\": \"people who have not been seen in days.\"}, {\"start\": 101.96, \"end\": 109.24, \"text\": \"On Thursday the Sheriff's office said 8 people were missing.\"}, {\"start\": 109.28, \"end\": 114.64, \"text\": \"Authorities confirm at least 17 people were killed by the storm.\"}, {\"start\": 114.66, \"end\": 120.82, \"text\": \"The areas where the victims were found remain under mandatory evacuation.\"}, {\"start\": 120.82, \"end\": 129.0, \"text\": \"But some Californias fear there could be more storms like this in the future.\"}, {\"start\": 130.78, \"end\": 145.14, \"text\": \"Today in Australia family and friends gathered for the funeral of Amy \\\"Dolly\\\" Everett.\"}, {\"start\": 145.14, \"end\": 154.4, \"text\": \"She is the 14-year-old girl who took her own life last week after being bullied online\"}, {\"start\": 154.4, \"end\": 157.36, \"text\": \"for eight years.\"}, {\"start\": 157.36, \"end\": 165.28, \"text\": \"Dolly was well known as the face of the Australian hat brand Akubra.\"}, {\"start\": 165.28, \"end\": 168.98, \"text\": \"She was featured in several of their commercials.\"}, {\"start\": 168.98, \"end\": 180.8, \"text\": \"Dolly's father invited the bullies who tormented his daughter to the funeral.\"}, {\"start\": 180.86, \"end\": 188.68, \"text\": \"He said he wanted them to witness the complete devastation they created.\"}, {\"start\": 188.68, \"end\": 197.78, \"text\": \"He says he also plans to establish a trust fund with the name \\\"Dolly's Dream\\\" to raise\"}, {\"start\": 197.78, \"end\": 201.1, \"text\": \"awareness about bullying.\"}, {\"start\": 202.52, \"end\": 216.44, \"text\": \"Police in Utah release this dashcam video of a violent shoot out and chase.\"}, {\"start\": 216.44, \"end\": 218.2, \"text\": \"It happened on December 20.\"}, {\"start\": 218.2, \"end\": 223.58, \"text\": \"The suspect was spotted on the I-15 highway wearing body armor.\"}, {\"start\": 223.58, \"end\": 230.88, \"text\": \"When the car was pulled over, the suspect fired three shots at officers.\"}, {\"start\": 230.88, \"end\": 238.14, \"text\": \"The officers responded, firing nearly 50 rounds in less than six seconds.\"}, {\"start\": 238.14, \"end\": 242.12, \"text\": \"The shoot out set off the chase.\"}, {\"start\": 242.16, \"end\": 246.34, \"text\": \"At one point, an officer drove ahead and fired at the driver, causing him to crash.\"}, {\"start\": 246.34, \"end\": 249.94, \"text\": \"The suspect, who was injured in the shooting, surrendered.\"}, {\"start\": 249.94, \"end\": 260.94, \"text\": \"He was charged with attempted aggravated murder, theft and other charges.\"}, {\"start\": 261.0, \"end\": 268.84, \"text\": \"And police later discovered the suspect was wanted for attempted murder in Colorado.\"}, {\"start\": 270.06, \"end\": 282.34, \"text\": \"The Washington Post reports Amazon founder Jeff Bezos and his wife are donating $33 million\"}, {\"start\": 282.34, \"end\": 288.78, \"text\": \"to fund scholarships for undocumented immigrants called \\\"Dreamers.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 288.78, \"end\": 295.62, \"text\": \"That term refers to people who were brought into the US illegally as children.\"}, {\"start\": 295.62, \"end\": 311.76, \"text\": \"The move comes as the White House rejected a bipartisan deal to keep them in the country.\"}, {\"start\": 311.76, \"end\": 320.53, \"text\": \"Bezos said his adopted father came to the United States from Cuba unable to speak English.\"}, {\"start\": 320.53, \"end\": 336.66, \"text\": \"Earlier this week Bezos joined Facebook founder Mark Zuckerberg and Apple CEO Tim Cook in\"}, {\"start\": 336.66, \"end\": 347.32, \"text\": \"co-signing a letter to Congress demanding protection for dreamers.\"}, {\"start\": 347.32, \"end\": 353.02, \"text\": \"They consider the deportation of young immigrants a threat to their workforces.\"}, {\"start\": 354.48, \"end\": 361.36, \"text\": \"The University of Maryland Medical System says they're shocked after a discharged hospital\"}, {\"start\": 361.42, \"end\": 364.0, \"text\": \"patient was left out on the cold streets of Baltimore Tuesday night.\"}, {\"start\": 364.0, \"end\": 376.0, \"text\": \"The Imamu Baraka posted this video of the situation on Facebook.\"}, {\"start\": 376.0, \"end\": 385.02, \"text\": \"He says he saw the unidentified patient wearing only a hospital gown and socks.\"}, {\"start\": 385.02, \"end\": 393.28, \"text\": \"Baraka condemned the medical system saying \\\"You can do better. You must do better.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 393.28, \"end\": 396.86, \"text\": \"The system issued a response saying that they're taking this matter very seriously and that\"}, {\"start\": 396.86, \"end\": 398.84, \"text\": \"they're conducting a thorough review.\"}, {\"start\": 400.48, \"end\": 415.4, \"text\": \"Country music star Carrie Underwood and hip-hop star Ludacris have teamed up to record a song\"}, {\"start\": 415.4, \"end\": 418.92, \"text\": \"for the Super Bowl.\"}, {\"start\": 418.92, \"end\": 424.8, \"text\": \"The song is called \\\"Championship.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 424.8, \"end\": 441.04, \"text\": \"They say they wrote the song with sports in mind, but also to help people overcome\"}, {\"start\": 441.04, \"end\": 443.92, \"text\": \"anything in their lives.\"}, {\"start\": 443.92, \"end\": 447.0, \"text\": \"The pair finished recording the song last year.\"}, {\"start\": 447.0, \"end\": 452.68, \"text\": \"NBC plans to air their video before the championship game.\"}, {\"start\": 452.68, \"end\": 460.64, \"text\": \"NBC liked the song so much the network is also using it for its Winter Olympics coverage.\"}, {\"start\": 460.64, \"end\": 465.84, \"text\": \"Super Bowl 52 airs February 4th.\"}, {\"start\": 465.84, \"end\": 472.76, \"text\": \"The Winter Olympics kickoff February 8th and goes until the 25th.\"}, {\"start\": 474.28, \"end\": 486.96, \"text\": \"A Missouri family is lucky to be alive and it's all thanks to their dog.\"}, {\"start\": 486.96, \"end\": 492.08, \"text\": \"Matt Beaudreau says he woke up around 2 AM to the sound of his dog, River, barking.\"}, {\"start\": 492.08, \"end\": 501.0, \"text\": \"He got up, took River out to do her business and went back to sleep.\"}, {\"start\": 501.0, \"end\": 504.6, \"text\": \"Fifteen minutes later, River started barking again.\"}, {\"start\": 504.6, \"end\": 510.48, \"text\": \"That's when they discovered an intense fire raging inside the family's garage.\"}, {\"start\": 510.48, \"end\": 515.64, \"text\": \"They quickly gathered their three kids and the dogs and got out of the house.\"}, {\"start\": 515.64, \"end\": 520.6, \"text\": \"The fire went through the garage wall and burned down the front porch.\"}, {\"start\": 520.64, \"end\": 528.88, \"text\": \"Beaudreau says they have working smoke detectors in the home but it was River's heroic actions\"}, {\"start\": 528.88, \"end\": 533.8, \"text\": \"that save the family from the tragedy.\"}, {\"start\": 535.56, \"end\": 537.96, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 537.96, \"end\": 539.16, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 539.16, \"end\": 541.08, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 541.08, \"end\": 545.36, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 545.36, \"end\": 551.16, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "M6miJXkHI4g": {
    "video_id": "M6miJXkHI4g",
    "title": "Over 1,600 LBS of cocaine hidden in pineapples (ASL - 1.19.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180120",
    "duration": 53,
    "view_count": 530,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.82, \"end\": 14.28, \"text\": \"On Wednesday The Spanish national police announced on Twitter they had seized 1,642 pounds of\"}, {\"start\": 14.28, \"end\": 16.84, \"text\": \"cocaine.\"}, {\"start\": 16.84, \"end\": 27.7, \"text\": \"The cocaine was hidden inside pineapples shipped from South America.\"}, {\"start\": 27.8, \"end\": 37.66, \"text\": \"Nine people were arrested in a joint operation the Portuguese police to seize the pineapples.\"}, {\"start\": 37.66, \"end\": 50.0, \"text\": \"The investigation took 10 months and it broke up an international smuggling ring led by\"}, {\"start\": 50.0, \"end\": 51.52, \"text\": \"Colombians.\"}]"
  },
  "eG9ElwObQXk": {
    "video_id": "eG9ElwObQXk",
    "title": "NY helicopter crash moment of impact (ASL - 3.12.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180313",
    "duration": 74,
    "view_count": 102,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.48, \"end\": 6.6, \"text\": \"We have the video of the moment a chartered helicopter in New York City slowly loses altitude\"}, {\"start\": 6.6, \"end\": 10.0, \"text\": \"and crashes into the East River.\"}, {\"start\": 10.0, \"end\": 13.56, \"text\": \"The blades slice the water briefly and then the craft stinks into the frigid water.\"}, {\"start\": 27.12, \"end\": 34.2, \"text\": \"Emergency crews had trouble getting the passengers out because they were tightly harnessed and\"}, {\"start\": 34.2, \"end\": 40.32, \"text\": \"the harnesses had to be cut while the helicopter was upside down and underwater.\"}, {\"start\": 40.32, \"end\": 52.36, \"text\": \"All five passengers on board died; two are pronounced dead at the scene, three others\"}, {\"start\": 52.36, \"end\": 55.56, \"text\": \"died afterwards.\"}, {\"start\": 55.56, \"end\": 59.6, \"text\": \"The pilot was the only survivor.\"}, {\"start\": 59.6, \"end\": 67.04, \"text\": \"He told investigators he believes one of the passengers' bags may have hit the emergency\"}, {\"start\": 67.04, \"end\": 72.64, \"text\": \"fuel shut off button by mistake.\"}]"
  },
  "Q1Z1BjgiyY4": {
    "video_id": "Q1Z1BjgiyY4",
    "title": "Retiring trooper makes emotional final radio call (ASL - 4.1.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180402",
    "duration": 109,
    "view_count": 183,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.34, \"end\": 10.92, \"text\": \"Arizona trooper Mark Gilberg began his law enforcement career with the Department of\"}, {\"start\": 10.92, \"end\": 17.68, \"text\": \"Public Safety on March 11, 1981.\"}, {\"start\": 17.68, \"end\": 24.11, \"text\": \"On Thursday the 37-year veteran signed off for the last time.\"}, {\"start\": 24.11, \"end\": 32.46, \"text\": \"And his emotional final radio call is making the rounds on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 32.46, \"end\": 38.74, \"text\": \"Watch as Gilberg calls into dispatch for the last time.\"}, {\"start\": 39.66, \"end\": 43.76, \"text\": \"I just wanted to thank everyone for everything they've ever done.\"}, {\"start\": 43.76, \"end\": 48.06, \"text\": \"It's been an honor and privilege and a great career.\"}, {\"start\": 48.06, \"end\": 50.16, \"text\": \"It's been a great adventure.\"}, {\"start\": 50.16, \"end\": 57.0, \"text\": \"I thank everyone that's ever helped me and as I said it's been an honor and a great pleasure\"}, {\"start\": 57.0, \"end\": 60.42, \"text\": \"to serve in this great department and to work with all of you fine people.\"}, {\"start\": 61.56, \"end\": 68.38, \"text\": \"This is 1-5-2, badge 2988, 39 years and three weeks later.\"}, {\"start\": 68.38, \"end\": 69.94, \"text\": \"It's been a great ride.\"}, {\"start\": 69.94, \"end\": 71.88, \"text\": \"Thank you very much and keep smiling.\"}, {\"start\": 74.42, \"end\": 79.44, \"text\": \"(radio dispatch) Unit 1-5-2, thank you for your service too.\"}, {\"start\": 79.44, \"end\": 82.62, \"text\": \"We appreciate everything that you have done.\"}, {\"start\": 82.68, \"end\": 85.7, \"text\": \"And congratulations on your tenure.\"}, {\"start\": 85.7, \"end\": 87.78, \"text\": \"That's awesome.\"}, {\"start\": 88.0, \"end\": 89.94, \"text\": \"You have good luck in your future endeavors.\"}, {\"start\": 89.94, \"end\": 91.86, \"text\": \"We appreciate it.\"}, {\"start\": 92.84, \"end\": 94.72, \"text\": \"10-4, 10-7.\"}, {\"start\": 95.76, \"end\": 102.72, \"text\": \"(radio dispatch) 1-5-2, 10-4 at 16:07.\"}, {\"start\": 102.78, \"end\": 109.56, \"text\": \"(sounds of crying)\"}]"
  },
  "lraA2o6flpc": {
    "video_id": "lraA2o6flpc",
    "title": "18 states sue Trump Administration over census (ASL - 4.3.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180404",
    "duration": 86,
    "view_count": 135,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.86, \"end\": 15.92, \"text\": \"The Trump administration wants to demand citizenship information on the next census in 2020.\"}, {\"start\": 15.92, \"end\": 21.04, \"text\": \"But if 18 states have their way, that won't happen.\"}, {\"start\": 21.04, \"end\": 28.84, \"text\": \"A multi-state federal lawsuit has been filed to block the Trump administration from asking\"}, {\"start\": 28.84, \"end\": 32.28, \"text\": \"a question about citizenship.\"}, {\"start\": 32.28, \"end\": 43.32, \"text\": \"Those states say adding a citizenship question will greatly reduce the level of participation\"}, {\"start\": 43.32, \"end\": 60.06, \"text\": \"in the census and would end up costing states tens of millions of dollars in federal funding\"}, {\"start\": 60.06, \"end\": 65.42, \"text\": \"for education and infrastructure.\"}, {\"start\": 65.42, \"end\": 84.96, \"text\": \"The Trump administration says the citizenship question will help enforce voting rights.\"}]"
  },
  "AIJhIR1IfbM": {
    "video_id": "AIJhIR1IfbM",
    "title": "Sign1News 4.4.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180405",
    "duration": 574,
    "view_count": 1677,
    "description": "4.4.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY’S HEADLINES:\n-YouTube shooter identified, possible motive revealed\n-Facebook’s Zuckerberg will testify April 11\n-China accuses Trump of spreading “fake news”\n-50th anniversary of MLK, Jr. assassination\n-Jay-Z opens up about his mom coming out\n-Police mocked for bizarre police sketch\n-Adorable puppies go to Disneyland!\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality new",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 7.3, \"end\": 9.06, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 9.06, \"end\": 10.98, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.98, \"end\": 13.02, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 13.02, \"end\": 16.12, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 19.52, \"end\": 25.2, \"text\": \"The YouTube community is still in shock today after a female gunman shot three people on\"}, {\"start\": 25.2, \"end\": 27.88, \"text\": \"the campus yesterday afternoon.\"}, {\"start\": 27.88, \"end\": 31.2, \"text\": \"Police say Nasim Aghdam walked into the company's headquarters in San Bruno, California just\"}, {\"start\": 31.2, \"end\": 45.6, \"text\": \"before 1 PM local time and shot three people with a handgun.\"}, {\"start\": 45.6, \"end\": 47.84, \"text\": \"Then she took her own life.\"}, {\"start\": 47.84, \"end\": 52.32, \"text\": \"The police still don't know why Aghdam did it.\"}, {\"start\": 52.32, \"end\": 58.32, \"text\": \"They say there's no evidence that she knew any of the people she shot.\"}, {\"start\": 58.32, \"end\": 66.16, \"text\": \"However her family says she did have a complaint against the company.\"}, {\"start\": 66.16, \"end\": 75.42, \"text\": \"Aghdam's family says she was very active on YouTube where she preached in favor of veganism\"}, {\"start\": 75.44, \"end\": 77.22, \"text\": \"and animal rights.\"}, {\"start\": 77.22, \"end\": 85.82, \"text\": \"But she became frustrated with YouTube because she believed her video posts were being restricted\"}, {\"start\": 85.82, \"end\": 88.86, \"text\": \"from getting views.\"}, {\"start\": 88.86, \"end\": 95.9, \"text\": \"Her father reportedly said Aghdam was staying with her grandmother in San Diego and she\"}, {\"start\": 95.9, \"end\": 99.8, \"text\": \"went missing a few days ago.\"}, {\"start\": 99.8, \"end\": 107.16, \"text\": \"Officials are now examining her website as part of their investigation.\"}, {\"start\": 111.46, \"end\": 120.28, \"text\": \"Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg is set to testify before Congress next week,\"}, {\"start\": 120.28, \"end\": 127.96, \"text\": \"April 11, about the company's consumer data privacy issues.\"}, {\"start\": 127.96, \"end\": 136.04, \"text\": \"It was revealed last month that data firm Cambridge Analytica was able to access information\"}, {\"start\": 136.04, \"end\": 143.58, \"text\": \"on roughly 50 million Facebook users without their knowledge.\"}, {\"start\": 143.58, \"end\": 149.8, \"text\": \"Cambridge Analytica's purpose for accessing information was to conduct voter-targeting\"}, {\"start\": 149.8, \"end\": 152.28, \"text\": \"during the 2016 presidential campaign.\"}, {\"start\": 152.28, \"end\": 159.54, \"text\": \"The chairman of the House Energy and Commerce committee said the April 11 hearing will be\"}, {\"start\": 159.64, \"end\": 164.66, \"text\": \"a good chance to explore consumer data privacy issues.\"}, {\"start\": 164.68, \"end\": 169.42, \"text\": \"But Facebook now has another problem to address.\"}, {\"start\": 169.42, \"end\": 176.94, \"text\": \"Yesterday the company says it found almost 300 more accounts run by the Russian group\"}, {\"start\": 176.98, \"end\": 182.92, \"text\": \"the \\\"Internet Research Agency\\\" or the IRA.\"}, {\"start\": 182.92, \"end\": 190.4, \"text\": \"The pages had a total of more than 1 million followers.\"}, {\"start\": 190.4, \"end\": 196.78, \"text\": \"Last summer, Facebook removed hundreds of fake pages and accounts run by the same group.\"}, {\"start\": 196.78, \"end\": 204.1, \"text\": \"The pages were designed to look like they were by authentic American activists.\"}, {\"start\": 204.16, \"end\": 213.42, \"text\": \"Zuckerberg said the removal of these accounts and pages was an important step to protect\"}, {\"start\": 213.42, \"end\": 217.6, \"text\": \"the integrity of elections around the world.\"}, {\"start\": 217.6, \"end\": 227.12, \"text\": \"Special Counsel Robert Mueller's office indicted 13 Russian nationals in February who allegedly\"}, {\"start\": 227.12, \"end\": 230.2, \"text\": \"had links to the group.\"}, {\"start\": 232.62, \"end\": 244.9, \"text\": \"The world's two largest economies, China and United States, are locked in a tariff tit-for-tat.\"}, {\"start\": 244.9, \"end\": 251.16, \"text\": \"China and the United States have announced tariffs on more than $100 billion worth of\"}, {\"start\": 251.24, \"end\": 254.24, \"text\": \"combined goods.\"}, {\"start\": 254.24, \"end\": 262.2, \"text\": \"The latest clash came Wednesday when the Chinese government proposed new tariffs on dozens\"}, {\"start\": 262.26, \"end\": 268.4, \"text\": \"of US products including airplanes, cars and soybeans.\"}, {\"start\": 268.4, \"end\": 274.54, \"text\": \"President Trump downplayed the tariffs on Twitter Wednesday morning.\"}, {\"start\": 274.56, \"end\": 280.64, \"text\": \"He insists the US is not in a trade war with China.\"}, {\"start\": 280.66, \"end\": 291.84, \"text\": \"He also slammed previous US leaders who he says allowed China's theft of US intellectual\"}, {\"start\": 291.84, \"end\": 301.6, \"text\": \"property.\"}, {\"start\": 301.6, \"end\": 308.0, \"text\": \"Beijing responded to those claims by saying: \\\"As for the media reports, we think would\"}, {\"start\": 308.0, \"end\": 314.14, \"text\": \"like to use the term President Trump often loves to say and call them 'fake news.'\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 316.12, \"end\": 328.6, \"text\": \"Today marks the 50th anniversary of the assassination of civil rights leader Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.\"}, {\"start\": 328.6, \"end\": 339.52, \"text\": \"He was shot to death on the balcony of the Lorraine Motel in Memphis, Tennessee in 1968.\"}, {\"start\": 339.56, \"end\": 349.6, \"text\": \"Cities across the country honored him with ceremonies, performances and peaceful marches.\"}, {\"start\": 349.64, \"end\": 358.18, \"text\": \"Several cities also rang bells 39 times, symbolizing King's age at the time of his death.\"}, {\"start\": 358.18, \"end\": 363.92, \"text\": \"The bells rang around the time King was shot, 7 PM.\"}, {\"start\": 363.92, \"end\": 370.48, \"text\": \"Various speakers challenged listeners to push for justice and equality just as King would\"}, {\"start\": 370.48, \"end\": 374.76, \"text\": \"have if he were still alive today.\"}, {\"start\": 376.44, \"end\": 382.9, \"text\": \"Jay-Z is opening up about his mother coming out as a lesbian.\"}, {\"start\": 382.9, \"end\": 391.8, \"text\": \"In a Netflix interview with David Letterman, the 48-year-old said he knew about his mom's\"}, {\"start\": 391.8, \"end\": 397.76, \"text\": \"love life for a while before she sat him down to tell him a year ago.\"}, {\"start\": 397.76, \"end\": 403.62, \"text\": \"And when she did, Jay-Z said he cried tears of joy!\"}, {\"start\": 403.62, \"end\": 415.88, \"text\": \"In the third track of his 13th studio album, Jay-Z raps about his mom in a duet called \\\"Smile.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 415.88, \"end\": 423.66, \"text\": \"And at the end his mom, Gloria Carter, says: \\\"Life is short and it is time to be free.\"}, {\"start\": 423.66, \"end\": 430.02, \"text\": \"Love who you love because life isn't guaranteed.\"}, {\"start\": 430.02, \"end\": 431.9, \"text\": \"Smile.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 434.5, \"end\": 440.54, \"text\": \"Take a look at this bizarre police sketch.\"}, {\"start\": 440.54, \"end\": 444.22, \"text\": \"Turns out it's not a joke.\"}, {\"start\": 444.22, \"end\": 450.96, \"text\": \"Police in the UK say it's real and they hope all the attention it's getting on social media\"}, {\"start\": 451.12, \"end\": 453.72, \"text\": \"will help them nab the suspect.\"}, {\"start\": 453.72, \"end\": 464.46, \"text\": \"Authorities used Electronic Facial Identification Techniques (or E-FIT) to create a computer\"}, {\"start\": 464.46, \"end\": 467.16, \"text\": \"rendering of the burglar's face based on descriptions of his features.\"}, {\"start\": 467.16, \"end\": 474.66, \"text\": \"Police say all jokes aside, two men tricked their way into a woman's flat in the UK.\"}, {\"start\": 474.76, \"end\": 479.62, \"text\": \"One of them distracted the woman while the other stole cash.\"}, {\"start\": 479.62, \"end\": 483.64, \"text\": \"And this is the description of one of the suspects.\"}, {\"start\": 483.64, \"end\": 489.74, \"text\": \"Anyone with information is asked to contact Crimestoppers UK.\"}, {\"start\": 492.64, \"end\": 500.52, \"text\": \"A group of service dogs took a field trip to the happiest place on earth -- Disneyland.\"}, {\"start\": 500.52, \"end\": 507.1, \"text\": \"And the images are going viral on social media.\"}, {\"start\": 507.2, \"end\": 516.8, \"text\": \"Meet Essie, Aryssa, Ortega and Chekov.\"}, {\"start\": 516.8, \"end\": 522.74, \"text\": \"They are a group of service dogs in training as canine companions to enhance the lives\"}, {\"start\": 522.74, \"end\": 525.92, \"text\": \"of people with disabilities.\"}, {\"start\": 526.06, \"end\": 533.34, \"text\": \"The trip to Disneyland was designed to improve their social skills.\"}, {\"start\": 533.34, \"end\": 540.24, \"text\": \"The fun-loving pups nosed their way around the park and even made new friends.\"}, {\"start\": 540.24, \"end\": 547.26, \"text\": \"They also patiently pose for photos until they were dog-gone tired.\"}, {\"start\": 549.62, \"end\": 551.98, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 551.98, \"end\": 553.66, \"text\": \"I'm Jethro Wooddall.\"}, {\"start\": 553.74, \"end\": 555.88, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 555.88, \"end\": 560.04, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 560.04, \"end\": 561.36, \"text\": \"Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 561.36, \"end\": 562.5, \"text\": \"Your life.\"}, {\"start\": 562.58, \"end\": 565.58, \"text\": \"Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "j-d7B2pYpbk": {
    "video_id": "j-d7B2pYpbk",
    "title": "Governor tells Trump Greenland is not for sale (ASL - 8.17.19)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20190817",
    "duration": 132,
    "view_count": 271,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 2.68, \"end\": 12.6, \"text\": \"President Trump has reportedly, on multiple occasions, expressed interest in buying Greenland\"}, {\"start\": 12.76, \"end\": 17.94, \"text\": \"from the Danish government.\"}, {\"start\": 17.94, \"end\": 24.3, \"text\": \"The President's interest in buying Greenland was first reported by the Wall Street Journal.\"}, {\"start\": 24.3, \"end\": 33.12, \"text\": \"According to the Journal, he has raised the issue during meetings and dinners with varying\"}, {\"start\": 33.12, \"end\": 40.039, \"text\": \"degrees of seriousness, questioning aides about the possible advantages of purchasing\"}, {\"start\": 40.04, \"end\": 47.38, \"text\": \"the autonomous Danish territory.\"}, {\"start\": 47.38, \"end\": 58.74, \"text\": \"It's home to the US military's northernmost base, some 750 miles above the Arctic Circle.\"}, {\"start\": 58.74, \"end\": 69.439, \"text\": \"Greenland officials immediately released a statement saying \\\"Greenland is not for sale.\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 69.439, \"end\": 80.03, \"text\": \"One member of Parliament said: \\\"This must be a joke. It's an insult against the people\"}, {\"start\": 80.03, \"end\": 89.899, \"text\": \"Greenland. It's 2019. You don't sell islands, countries or people like this. It's a grotesque\"}, {\"start\": 89.9, \"end\": 98.98, \"text\": \"idea. It's not going to happen under no circumstance\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 98.98, \"end\": 107.58, \"text\": \"America tried to acquire Greenland in 1867 and then again in the 1940s during World War\"}, {\"start\": 107.58, \"end\": 109.5, \"text\": \"II and failed.\"}, {\"start\": 109.5, \"end\": 117.36, \"text\": \"Many people believe Trump is expressing an interest in buying Greenland because it has\"}, {\"start\": 117.36, \"end\": 130.74, \"text\": \"a lot of natural resources and China has been trying to get in on that lucrative business.\"}]"
  },
  "s0p5sNW2vXQ": {
    "video_id": "s0p5sNW2vXQ",
    "title": "Reminder: clocks spring forward one hour (ASL - 3.10.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180310",
    "duration": 78,
    "view_count": 507,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.56, \"end\": 6.9, \"text\": \"Don't forget to set your clocks ahead one hour tonight.\"}, {\"start\": 6.9, \"end\": 17.72, \"text\": \"The good news: the sun will set later so people will enjoy more daylight hours.\"}, {\"start\": 17.72, \"end\": 20.58, \"text\": \"The bad news: we will lose one hour of sleep.\"}, {\"start\": 20.58, \"end\": 27.64, \"text\": \"Losing one hour may not seem like much, but that small change can be a big deal for your health.\"}, {\"start\": 27.64, \"end\": 34.0, \"text\": \"According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) many people aren't getting\"}, {\"start\": 34.0, \"end\": 35.96, \"text\": \"enough sleep to begin with.\"}, {\"start\": 35.96, \"end\": 40.72, \"text\": \"And losing another hour can lead to deadly consequences.\"}, {\"start\": 40.72, \"end\": 47.36, \"text\": \"According to a Stanford University study, the Monday after the timeshift is linked to\"}, {\"start\": 47.4, \"end\": 51.96, \"text\": \"an increase in tragic car accidents.\"}, {\"start\": 51.96, \"end\": 60.92, \"text\": \"Also adults who miss out on even one hour of sleep a day are more likely to report health\"}, {\"start\": 61.0, \"end\": 66.24, \"text\": \"problems like diabetes, depression and heart disease.\"}, {\"start\": 66.24, \"end\": 74.12, \"text\": \"Experts suggest you use the time change to reset your sleep habits to make sure you get\"}, {\"start\": 74.14, \"end\": 76.43, \"text\": \"enough rest.\"}]"
  },
  "drxldErz6LM": {
    "video_id": "drxldErz6LM",
    "title": "What do recent school shootings in American have in common? (ASL - 2.15.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180216",
    "duration": 62,
    "view_count": 58,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.64, \"end\": 8.44, \"text\": \"Many of the worst mass shootings in recent years have something in common: The same weapon,\"}, {\"start\": 8.44, \"end\": 11.28, \"text\": \"the AR-15 rifle, was used in all of the shootings.\"}, {\"start\": 11.28, \"end\": 22.36, \"text\": \"The Sutherland Springs church, the Las Vegas country music concert, Pulse nightclub, the\"}, {\"start\": 22.36, \"end\": 40.84, \"text\": \"San Bernardino office shooting, Sandy Hook elementary and the Aurora movie theater.\"}, {\"start\": 40.96, \"end\": 51.16, \"text\": \"The National Rifle Association says the AR-15 is adaptable, reliable and accurate.\"}, {\"start\": 51.16, \"end\": 58.52, \"text\": \"The NRA says the AR-15 is America's most popular rifle.\"}, {\"start\": 58.52, \"end\": 61.72, \"text\": \"It is owned by more than 8 million people in this country.\"}]"
  },
  "EiPM2y8c1RE": {
    "video_id": "EiPM2y8c1RE",
    "title": "Sign1News 3.31.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180401",
    "duration": 792,
    "view_count": 1572,
    "description": "3.31.18 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-Autopsy reveals Clark shot 6 times in the back\n-Alton Sterling shooting video released\n-Trump lashes out at California governor\n-Skepticism grows over Trump’s pick to head VA\n-Winning $521 Mega Millions ticket sold in New Jersey\n-Musician plays flute during brain surgery\n-Sign1News celebrates deaf culture with local school\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE\nOur talented staff works hard each day to",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 8.22, \"end\": 10.04, \"text\": \"Hello everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 10.04, \"end\": 12.5, \"text\": \"Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 12.52, \"end\": 14.06, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 14.06, \"end\": 17.42, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 20.52, \"end\": 31.5, \"text\": \"Two weeks ago 22-year-old Stephon Clark was shot and killed by Sacramento police while\"}, {\"start\": 31.5, \"end\": 36.14, \"text\": \"he was standing in his grandmother's backyard.\"}, {\"start\": 36.14, \"end\": 41.78, \"text\": \"The officers say they believed Clark was pointing a gun at them.\"}, {\"start\": 41.78, \"end\": 52.42, \"text\": \"But investigators only found a cell phone near his body.\"}, {\"start\": 52.48, \"end\": 68.32, \"text\": \"Now the doctor retained by Clark's family says his independent autopsy does not line\"}, {\"start\": 68.4, \"end\": 70.92, \"text\": \"up with what police say happened.\"}, {\"start\": 71.0, \"end\": 85.04, \"text\": \"The autopsy released revealed Clark was shot eight times by police, six of those shots\"}, {\"start\": 85.04, \"end\": 87.48, \"text\": \"were in the back.\"}, {\"start\": 87.48, \"end\": 102.0, \"text\": \"The autopsy results contradict the police report which said Clark assaulted the officers.\"}, {\"start\": 102.0, \"end\": 110.42, \"text\": \"That means Clark would have been facing them.\"}, {\"start\": 110.42, \"end\": 120.9, \"text\": \"The autopsy also revealed Clark did not immediately die after he was shot.\"}, {\"start\": 120.9, \"end\": 130.3, \"text\": \"The doctor said it took him about 3 to 10 minutes to die.\"}, {\"start\": 130.3, \"end\": 135.78, \"text\": \"The Sacramento Police Department issued a statement in response to the findings outlined\"}, {\"start\": 135.78, \"end\": 144.14, \"text\": \"in the independent autopsy.\"}, {\"start\": 144.14, \"end\": 155.18, \"text\": \"It says they have not been provided with the official report from the Sacramento County\"}, {\"start\": 155.18, \"end\": 163.26, \"text\": \"coroner's office and will not give any further comment at this time.\"}, {\"start\": 166.32, \"end\": 182.12, \"text\": \"Police in Baton Rouge, Louisiana released video showing the deadly shooting of Alton Sterling.\"}, {\"start\": 182.12, \"end\": 190.04, \"text\": \"We want to warn you: the video is graphic.\"}, {\"start\": 190.04, \"end\": 203.56, \"text\": \"The video includes body cam video from Howie Lake, one of two officers involved in the incident.\"}, {\"start\": 203.56, \"end\": 218.62, \"text\": \"The video shows police approaching Sterling in July 2016 after a 911 call about a man with a gun.\"}, {\"start\": 218.62, \"end\": 225.84, \"text\": \"That's when officers tell him to put his hands on a car.\"}, {\"start\": 225.84, \"end\": 233.32, \"text\": \"Sterling is tasered twice but remains standing.\"}, {\"start\": 233.32, \"end\": 236.52, \"text\": \"And then a tussle breaks out.\"}, {\"start\": 236.52, \"end\": 240.36, \"text\": \"Someone then screams \\\"He's got a gun!\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 240.36, \"end\": 249.72, \"text\": \"The voice is believed to belong to Blane Salamoni, the other officer involved in the incident.\"}, {\"start\": 249.84, \"end\": 254.02, \"text\": \"Then six shots are fired.\"}, {\"start\": 254.32, \"end\": 262.48, \"text\": \"Hey sir. What I did?\"}, {\"start\": 262.72, \"end\": 265.84, \"text\": \"Don't (beep) move or I will shoot your (beep)!\"}, {\"start\": 266.08, \"end\": 268.72, \"text\": \"Put your (beep) hands on the car!\"}, {\"start\": 268.72, \"end\": 271.12, \"text\": \"Put your hands on the car or I'll shoot you in the (beep) head!\"}, {\"start\": 271.12, \"end\": 272.52, \"text\": \"Do you understand me?\"}, {\"start\": 272.52, \"end\": 273.88, \"text\": \"Don't you (beep) or I'll shoot you in the (beep) head!\"}, {\"start\": 273.88, \"end\": 274.92, \"text\": \"Don't you move!\"}, {\"start\": 275.02, \"end\": 276.2, \"text\": \"Hold up! Hold up man! You hurtin' my arm!\"}, {\"start\": 276.24, \"end\": 277.12, \"text\": \"Stop!\"}, {\"start\": 277.12, \"end\": 277.92, \"text\": \"\\\"I'm saying what happened man?\"}, {\"start\": 277.92, \"end\": 281.22, \"text\": \"Tase him! (sound of taser) Get on the ground!\"}, {\"start\": 281.28, \"end\": 282.96, \"text\": \"Pop him again Howie! (sound of taser)\"}, {\"start\": 282.96, \"end\": 284.88, \"text\": \"I ain't do nothing! What the (beep)!\"}, {\"start\": 284.88, \"end\": 286.4, \"text\": \"(sound of fighting)\"}, {\"start\": 286.4, \"end\": 288.48, \"text\": \"I'm going to search your pockets!\"}, {\"start\": 288.48, \"end\": 294.96, \"text\": \"He's got a gun!\"}, {\"start\": 295.28, \"end\": 297.92, \"text\": \"He's got a gun! (sound of three gun shots)\"}, {\"start\": 297.92, \"end\": 301.36, \"text\": \"Get on the ground!\"}, {\"start\": 301.36, \"end\": 304.08, \"text\": \"(sound of three gun shots)\"}, {\"start\": 312.48, \"end\": 316.0, \"text\": \"16-19 shots fired! Shots fired!\"}, {\"start\": 316.0, \"end\": 318.08, \"text\": \"(inaudible radio communication)\"}, {\"start\": 318.08, \"end\": 321.36, \"text\": \"16-19 both officers are okay.\"}, {\"start\": 321.44, \"end\": 323.6, \"text\": \"Suspect is down.\"}, {\"start\": 323.6, \"end\": 326.48, \"text\": \"I need an EMS code 3!\"}, {\"start\": 331.76, \"end\": 334.24, \"text\": \"Hey... hold on y'all! Stop!\"}, {\"start\": 334.24, \"end\": 337.6, \"text\": \"Everybody stop!\"}, {\"start\": 339.52, \"end\": 346.4, \"text\": \"The officers said Sterling tried to reach for a gun during the tussle.\"}, {\"start\": 346.4, \"end\": 355.12, \"text\": \"Both officers were later cleared of criminal wrongdoing.\"}, {\"start\": 355.28, \"end\": 369.12, \"text\": \"But officer Salamoni, who shot Sterling, was fired Friday for violating the department's\"}, {\"start\": 369.12, \"end\": 372.96, \"text\": \"use- of-force policies.\"}, {\"start\": 372.96, \"end\": 381.36, \"text\": \"Officer Lake is facing a three-day suspension for losing his temper.\"}, {\"start\": 384.4, \"end\": 395.68, \"text\": \"On Friday, California Governor Jerry Brown granted 56 pardons and 14 commutations for\"}, {\"start\": 395.68, \"end\": 398.96, \"text\": \"a group of illegal immigrants.\"}, {\"start\": 398.96, \"end\": 410.64, \"text\": \"According to the Sacramento Bee, five of those pardons were immigrants facing possible deportation.\"}, {\"start\": 410.88, \"end\": 418.56, \"text\": \"Today President Trump lashed out at Governor Brown on Twitter over the issue.\"}, {\"start\": 418.56, \"end\": 442.88, \"text\": \"He tweeted: \\\"Governor Jerry \\\"Moonbeam\\\" Brown pardoned five criminal illegal aliens whose\"}, {\"start\": 442.88, \"end\": 451.36, \"text\": \"crimes include (1) kidnapping and robbery (2) badly beating wife and threatening a crime\"}, {\"start\": 451.36, \"end\": 454.24, \"text\": \"with intent to terrorize (3) dealing drugs.\"}, {\"start\": 454.24, \"end\": 459.36, \"text\": \"Is this what the great people of California want?\\\"\"}, {\"start\": 459.36, \"end\": 468.48, \"text\": \"Brown said the people he pardoned all completed their sentences years ago and the majority\"}, {\"start\": 468.48, \"end\": 472.8, \"text\": \"were convicted of drug-related and other nonviolent crimes.\"}, {\"start\": 475.52, \"end\": 481.68, \"text\": \"There is growing skepticism on Capitol Hill about the qualifications of President Trump's\"}, {\"start\": 481.7, \"end\": 493.94, \"text\": \"new pick to lead the Department of Veterans Affairs, White House Dr. Ronny Jackson.\"}, {\"start\": 493.94, \"end\": 504.46, \"text\": \"Jackson has worked at the White House for years but he has no management experience.\"}, {\"start\": 504.46, \"end\": 512.58, \"text\": \"And if he is confirmed, he would take control of the second largest department in the federal\"}, {\"start\": 512.58, \"end\": 514.82, \"text\": \"government.\"}, {\"start\": 514.82, \"end\": 526.28, \"text\": \"The VA has 375,000 employees, a budget of close to $200 billion and serves 9 million\"}, {\"start\": 526.28, \"end\": 532.5, \"text\": \"veterans who rely on its services.\"}, {\"start\": 532.5, \"end\": 547.14, \"text\": \"The Washington Post reports that Jackson himself was taken aback by his nomination and hesitated\"}, {\"start\": 547.14, \"end\": 554.32, \"text\": \"to take on such a big job, but the president continued to push for his selection.\"}, {\"start\": 559.36, \"end\": 564.78, \"text\": \"Congratulations to one lucky person in New Jersey.\"}, {\"start\": 564.78, \"end\": 569.94, \"text\": \"They are now $521 million richer!\"}, {\"start\": 569.94, \"end\": 580.94, \"text\": \"Lottery officials say a single Mega Millions winning ticket matched all six numbers drawn.\"}, {\"start\": 580.94, \"end\": 589.02, \"text\": \"The jackpot's worth was the fourth largest jackpot in the history of the game.\"}, {\"start\": 589.02, \"end\": 597.96, \"text\": \"Here are the winning numbers just in case you matched some of the numbers.\"}, {\"start\": 618.36, \"end\": 626.5, \"text\": \"Sixty-three-year-old Anna Henry had been suffering from intense tremors in her left hand and fingers.\"}, {\"start\": 626.5, \"end\": 633.6, \"text\": \"So surgeons at the Texas Medical Center in Houston implanted tiny electrodes in her brain.\"}, {\"start\": 633.6, \"end\": 639.44, \"text\": \"While she was still an the operating table the team handed Henry her flute to test if\"}, {\"start\": 639.84, \"end\": 646.32, \"text\": \"her hands were steady enough to play.\"}, {\"start\": 646.32, \"end\": 656.96, \"text\": \"After playing one of her favorite classical concertos, doctors and nurses burst into applause.\"}, {\"start\": 658.46, \"end\": 664.86, \"text\": \"We want to thank Cleveland Road elementary school for inviting us to participate in their\"}, {\"start\": 664.86, \"end\": 669.42, \"text\": \"Deaf Culture Celebration on Friday.\"}, {\"start\": 669.42, \"end\": 680.88, \"text\": \"Sign1News anchor Jethro Wooddall shared with the students his life story and what it's\"}, {\"start\": 680.88, \"end\": 688.8, \"text\": \"like to be a news anchor and a deaf interpreter.\"}, {\"start\": 688.8, \"end\": 696.06, \"text\": \"The kids was thoroughly engaged and asked lots of great questions.\"}, {\"start\": 696.06, \"end\": 702.42, \"text\": \"Afterwards all of the invited speakers fellowshipped in the cafeteria with the students.\"}, {\"start\": 702.42, \"end\": 708.4, \"text\": \"It was an exciting, inspiring and educational day for everyone.\"}, {\"start\": 708.4, \"end\": 714.58, \"text\": \"It was important for me to show the kids what they can achieve when they dream big, that\"}, {\"start\": 714.58, \"end\": 716.24, \"text\": \"nothing is impossible.\"}, {\"start\": 716.24, \"end\": 722.38, \"text\": \"If they thought being deaf would limited them, I'm here to prove them wrong and to show that\"}, {\"start\": 722.38, \"end\": 723.84, \"text\": \"they can become anything they want.\"}, {\"start\": 723.84, \"end\": 729.16, \"text\": \"This was such an important day for the students, teachers and staff.\"}, {\"start\": 729.16, \"end\": 734.26, \"text\": \"We all learned the different aspects of deaf culture but at the same time we learned that\"}, {\"start\": 734.26, \"end\": 737.83, \"text\": \"the deaf culture is not different than any other culture and should be honored equally.\"}, {\"start\": 737.83, \"end\": 740.16, \"text\": \"We learned so much!\"}, {\"start\": 740.16, \"end\": 748.3, \"text\": \"Now a lot of people know about deaf culture so it was cool having everyone come together\"}, {\"start\": 748.3, \"end\": 754.78, \"text\": \"to understand that being deaf is more than just a physical condition.\"}, {\"start\": 754.78, \"end\": 758.58, \"text\": \"It's about teaching hearing people who want to learn more about American Sign Language\"}, {\"start\": 758.58, \"end\": 759.8, \"text\": \"so they can communicate with deaf people.\"}, {\"start\": 762.66, \"end\": 765.58, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 765.8, \"end\": 767.38, \"text\": \"I'm Candace Jones.\"}, {\"start\": 767.38, \"end\": 770.46, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 770.48, \"end\": 776.68, \"text\": \"Remember to like us on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 776.7, \"end\": 783.66, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "SBbvV7KZ2PQ": {
    "video_id": "SBbvV7KZ2PQ",
    "title": "Dr. G answers your questions: Is there a cure?",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20200321",
    "duration": 85,
    "view_count": 370,
    "description": "Posted 3.21.20",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.78, \"end\": 4.22, \"text\": \"This question is from Lena Daron.\"}, {\"start\": 4.22, \"end\": 7.32, \"text\": \"She asked is there a cure yet.\"}, {\"start\": 7.32, \"end\": 14.8, \"text\": \"No not yet but scientiests from all over the world are researching and working hard day\"}, {\"start\": 14.8, \"end\": 16.08, \"text\": \"and night.\"}, {\"start\": 16.14, \"end\": 18.26, \"text\": \"But they haven't yet found a cure.\"}, {\"start\": 18.4, \"end\": 26.0, \"text\": \"Also many people are working hard to find a vaccine it won't happen this month or the\"}, {\"start\": 26.0, \"end\": 28.86, \"text\": \"next two months.\"}, {\"start\": 28.86, \"end\": 36.62, \"text\": \"You just need to help protect yourselves by staying home and not contacting other people.\"}, {\"start\": 36.62, \"end\": 39.54, \"text\": \"Practice social distancing.\"}, {\"start\": 39.55, \"end\": 45.829, \"text\": \"That's the best protection right now because a vaccine has not been developed yet.\"}, {\"start\": 45.829, \"end\": 49.62, \"text\": \"Lena also asked how long will it last.\"}, {\"start\": 49.62, \"end\": 52.52, \"text\": \"We don't know. No one really knows.\"}, {\"start\": 52.52, \"end\": 61.82, \"text\": \"But right now for the first day in China we see they have had no new cases pop up there.\"}, {\"start\": 61.86, \"end\": 65.4, \"text\": \"That's wonderful news but it took them three months.\"}, {\"start\": 65.4, \"end\": 71.48, \"text\": \"But here in the US there so many in this country who have it so we don't know how long it will last.\"}, {\"start\": 71.48, \"end\": 80.32, \"text\": \"So just breathe, get ready and prepare yourself, wait, sit and relax if you can.\"}, {\"start\": 80.32, \"end\": 84.56, \"text\": \"Take care of yourself and your family and stay home.\"}]"
  },
  "I-BuvRRzqVc": {
    "video_id": "I-BuvRRzqVc",
    "title": "Sign1News 11.23.17 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL).",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20171123",
    "duration": 486,
    "view_count": 260,
    "description": "November 23, 2017 - News for the deaf community powered by CNN in American Sign Language (ASL). \n\nTODAY'S HEADLINES:\n-TEAM USA DOCTOR PLEADS GUILTY TO SEX CHARGES\n-MOORE'S COMMUNICATIONS DIRECTOR RESIGNS\n-TEXAS LAWMAKER APOLOGIZES FOR NUDE PHOTO TWEET\n-SEARCH INTENSIFIES FOR MISSING SUBMARINE\n-SEARCH FOR NAVY PLANE CONTINUES\n-TRUMP TWEETS THANKSGIVING MESSAGE\n-BUTTERBALL HOTLINE IS OPEN\n\nTHE SIGN1NEWS DIFFERENCE \nOur talented staff works hard each day to deliver quality news to you. We have back",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "en",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 6.84, \"end\": 10.0, \"text\": \"Hello everyone. Welcome to Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 10.24, \"end\": 11.88, \"text\": \"I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 11.88, \"end\": 14.1, \"text\": \"Here are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 15.38, \"end\": 23.14, \"text\": \"Former USA gymnastics team doctor Larry Nassar\"}, {\"start\": 23.14, \"end\": 28.4, \"text\": \"admitted he sexually abused under aged girls.\"}, {\"start\": 28.48, \"end\": 33.56, \"text\": \"In a Michigan courtroom\"}, {\"start\": 33.56, \"end\": 39.02, \"text\": \"Nassar pleaded guilty to 1st degree criminal sexual conduct.\"}, {\"start\": 40.36, \"end\": 42.54, \"text\": \"He will be behind bars for the rest of his life.\"}, {\"start\": 42.58, \"end\": 48.46, \"text\": \"One hundred twenty five women and girls told the Michigan State police\"}, {\"start\": 48.46, \"end\": 56.36, \"text\": \"the doctor sexually assaulted them under the guise of treatment.\"}, {\"start\": 56.36, \"end\": 63.8, \"text\": \"Nassar served as the USA gymnastics physician during four Olympic Games.\"}, {\"start\": 63.82, \"end\": 67.54, \"text\": \"He is also awaiting sentencing on federal charges of\"}, {\"start\": 67.54, \"end\": 77.54, \"text\": \"receiving child pornography, possessing child pornography and\"}, {\"start\": 77.54, \"end\": 83.52, \"text\": \"and a charge that he hid and destroyed evidence in the case.\"}, {\"start\": 83.56, \"end\": 89.36, \"text\": \"That hearing is scheduled for Monday.\"}, {\"start\": 91.02, \"end\": 97.92, \"text\": \"The Communications Director for Alabama US Senate candidate Roy Moore\"}, {\"start\": 97.92, \"end\": 105.82, \"text\": \"announced his resignation last Friday.\"}, {\"start\": 105.9, \"end\": 109.94, \"text\": \"A senior campaign adviser says John Rogers did not\"}, {\"start\": 109.94, \"end\": 112.84, \"text\": \"have the experience to deal with the level of scrutiny\"}, {\"start\": 112.84, \"end\": 119.48, \"text\": \"brought on by the national media.\"}, {\"start\": 119.48, \"end\": 123.12, \"text\": \"Moore has been under fire after several women came forward\"}, {\"start\": 123.12, \"end\": 125.88, \"text\": \"alleging Moore pursued relationships with\"}, {\"start\": 125.88, \"end\": 131.96, \"text\": \"them when they were in their teens and he was in his 30's.\"}, {\"start\": 131.98, \"end\": 135.74, \"text\": \"Others have accused Moore of sexual assault.\"}, {\"start\": 135.74, \"end\": 139.12, \"text\": \"Moore has denied the allegations and\"}, {\"start\": 139.12, \"end\": 142.04, \"text\": \"says he will not drop out of the race.\"}, {\"start\": 142.04, \"end\": 151.7, \"text\": \"Moore faces Democrat Doug Jones in a special Senate election next month.\"}, {\"start\": 154.4, \"end\": 160.0, \"text\": \"Texas Republican representative Joe Barton\"}, {\"start\": 160.0, \"end\": 164.84, \"text\": \"apologized Wednesday for letting his constituents down\"}, {\"start\": 164.84, \"end\": 168.84, \"text\": \"and for not using better judgment.\"}, {\"start\": 168.88, \"end\": 174.86, \"text\": \"On Wednesday a nude picture of Barton was post online.\"}, {\"start\": 174.86, \"end\": 177.34, \"text\": \"Barton says he did not release the nude photo\"}, {\"start\": 177.34, \"end\": 180.02, \"text\": \"and does not know who did.\"}, {\"start\": 180.06, \"end\": 184.0, \"text\": \"He did admit the pictures stem from an extramarital\"}, {\"start\": 184.0, \"end\": 188.0, \"text\": \"affair he had before his divorce.\"}, {\"start\": 188.1, \"end\": 190.78, \"text\": \"But Barton says he is not resigning.\"}, {\"start\": 190.78, \"end\": 194.24, \"text\": \"Earlier this month he announced\"}, {\"start\": 194.24, \"end\": 197.66, \"text\": \"plans to seek re-election.\"}, {\"start\": 200.1, \"end\": 206.42, \"text\": \"Planes and ships from seven countries are scouring the Southern Atlantic ocean\"}, {\"start\": 206.5, \"end\": 215.42, \"text\": \"looking for the missing Argentine Navy submarine.\"}, {\"start\": 216.92, \"end\": 219.92, \"text\": \"There are 44 crew members on board.\"}, {\"start\": 220.06, \"end\": 222.46, \"text\": \"The submarine was last spotted on Wednesday.\"}, {\"start\": 222.46, \"end\": 226.18, \"text\": \"On Saturday the submarine may have attempted\"}, {\"start\": 226.18, \"end\": 240.12, \"text\": \"using an emergency beacon or satellite communications.\"}, {\"start\": 240.12, \"end\": 244.86, \"text\": \"But authorities now say there is no clear evidence detected signals actually\"}, {\"start\": 244.86, \"end\": 248.16, \"text\": \"came from the missing sub.\"}, {\"start\": 248.2, \"end\": 253.34, \"text\": \"Now officials warn the 44 crew members on board\"}, {\"start\": 253.34, \"end\": 259.96, \"text\": \"might be running out of oxygen soon.\"}, {\"start\": 263.0, \"end\": 268.08, \"text\": \"A military plane carrying 11 Navy personnel\"}, {\"start\": 268.08, \"end\": 272.7, \"text\": \"crashed into the Philippine Sea Wednesday.\"}, {\"start\": 272.7, \"end\": 281.26, \"text\": \"They were flying from a Japanese station to the USS Ronald Reagan aircraft carrier\"}, {\"start\": 281.3, \"end\": 293.4, \"text\": \"about 500 miles from the Okinawa coast.\"}, {\"start\": 293.44, \"end\": 297.0, \"text\": \"Eight people were rescued and are in good condition.\"}, {\"start\": 297.0, \"end\": 301.56, \"text\": \"But three remain unaccounted for.\"}, {\"start\": 301.56, \"end\": 304.8, \"text\": \"Japanese forces have joined in the search,\"}, {\"start\": 304.8, \"end\": 311.78, \"text\": \"which the Navy says is relentless.\"}, {\"start\": 311.78, \"end\": 315.44, \"text\": \"This is the latest in a string of\"}, {\"start\": 315.44, \"end\": 318.4, \"text\": \"difficult events for the Navy in the Pacific Ocean.\"}, {\"start\": 318.4, \"end\": 324.76, \"text\": \"There have been at least six apparent accidents involving the Navy in 2017.\"}, {\"start\": 326.38, \"end\": 334.14, \"text\": \"President Trump tweeted Thanksgiving greetings to the country.\"}, {\"start\": 334.14, \"end\": 337.98, \"text\": \"The tweet included several reasons why Americans should be thankful.\"}, {\"start\": 337.98, \"end\": 348.14, \"text\": \"He mentioned positive employment, stock market growth and a strong military.\"}, {\"start\": 348.16, \"end\": 353.64, \"text\": \"He also said the country should be thankful for the wall\"}, {\"start\": 353.64, \"end\": 360.5, \"text\": \"he's building along the US-Mexico border.\"}, {\"start\": 360.5, \"end\": 367.18, \"text\": \"President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump\"}, {\"start\": 367.18, \"end\": 370.5, \"text\": \"spent part of Thanksgiving with members\"}, {\"start\": 370.5, \"end\": 377.78, \"text\": \"of the Lake Worth, Florida Coast Guard.\"}, {\"start\": 377.78, \"end\": 383.28, \"text\": \"He shook hands with members, handed out sandwiches\"}, {\"start\": 383.28, \"end\": 388.7, \"text\": \"and thanked them for their service.\"}, {\"start\": 391.16, \"end\": 394.22, \"text\": \"If you're cooking the Thanksgiving turkey this year\"}, {\"start\": 394.24, \"end\": 396.42, \"text\": \"and especially if you're an amateur -- have no fear.\"}, {\"start\": 396.42, \"end\": 401.58, \"text\": \"Butterball is ready to help.\"}, {\"start\": 401.58, \"end\": 408.06, \"text\": \"For the second year, the company is offering 24/7 text message support.\"}, {\"start\": 408.06, \"end\": 413.44, \"text\": \"You can text questions about what size turkey to buy,\"}, {\"start\": 413.44, \"end\": 419.16, \"text\": \"how to thaw the bird and more.\"}, {\"start\": 419.16, \"end\": 422.8, \"text\": \"The Butterball turkey talk line will also be in effect\"}, {\"start\": 422.8, \"end\": 429.88, \"text\": \"if you prefer to talk with a real person.\"}, {\"start\": 429.96, \"end\": 434.14, \"text\": \"Services are available on Thanksgiving day\"}, {\"start\": 434.14, \"end\": 436.42, \"text\": \"and every day through December 24.\"}, {\"start\": 436.42, \"end\": 441.78, \"text\": \"You can call 1-800-Butterball or\"}, {\"start\": 441.78, \"end\": 447.72, \"text\": \"text 844-877-3456.\"}, {\"start\": 447.74, \"end\": 455.96, \"text\": \"Those numbers are also on the website Butterball.com\"}, {\"start\": 457.58, \"end\": 459.78, \"text\": \"And those are your top stories for today.\"}, {\"start\": 459.78, \"end\": 461.6, \"text\": \"I am Crystal Cousineau.\"}, {\"start\": 461.62, \"end\": 464.08, \"text\": \"Thank you for watching Sign1News.\"}, {\"start\": 464.08, \"end\": 469.74, \"text\": \"Remember to like this on Facebook and follow us on Twitter.\"}, {\"start\": 469.74, \"end\": 477.92, \"text\": \"Sign1News. Your life. Your language.\"}]"
  },
  "JCdXI56o7JA": {
    "video_id": "JCdXI56o7JA",
    "title": "China’s space station will crash to Earth soon (ASL - 3.26.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180327",
    "duration": 83,
    "view_count": 559,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.16, \"end\": 11.46, \"text\": \"If you see a fireball crashing to earth on April 1, it might not be an April Fools' Day prank.\"}, {\"start\": 11.46, \"end\": 18.22, \"text\": \"A Chinese space station is expected to crash to earth soon.\"}, {\"start\": 18.22, \"end\": 23.26, \"text\": \"But exactly where it will land is unknown.\"}, {\"start\": 23.26, \"end\": 38.12, \"text\": \"The Tiangong-1 is 34 feet long, which is about the size of a school bus, and weighs 9.4 tons.\"}, {\"start\": 38.12, \"end\": 47.32, \"text\": \"China stopped receiving data from the station back in 2016.\"}, {\"start\": 47.32, \"end\": 53.78, \"text\": \"The European space agency says there really is no cause for too much concern as the Earth's\"}, {\"start\": 53.78, \"end\": 60.48, \"text\": \"atmosphere will break apart and burn up much of the space station upon reentry.\"}, {\"start\": 60.48, \"end\": 71.74, \"text\": \"However there is a \\\"worst-case\\\" scenario location area from Northern California to Pennsylvania.\"}, {\"start\": 71.74, \"end\": 78.34, \"text\": \"The space agency predicted the space station will reenter Earth's atmosphere between March\"}, {\"start\": 78.36, \"end\": 81.4, \"text\": \"30 and April 3.\"}]"
  },
  "ZyxAd6N9MVo": {
    "video_id": "ZyxAd6N9MVo",
    "title": "Parkland shooter receives fan mail, donations (ASL - 3.29.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180330",
    "duration": 48,
    "view_count": 65,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.46, \"end\": 16.36, \"text\": \"Authorities say Parkland, Florida shooter Nikolas Cruz is actually receiving fan mail.\"}, {\"start\": 16.36, \"end\": 21.34, \"text\": \"Hundreds of letters are coming in from all over the US and Europe from young girls, women\"}, {\"start\": 21.34, \"end\": 24.04, \"text\": \"and even grown men.\"}, {\"start\": 24.04, \"end\": 27.48, \"text\": \"Some are typed, others handwritten on notebook paper.\"}, {\"start\": 27.48, \"end\": 32.24, \"text\": \"There are drawings, cards and envelopes filled with pictures of women and even teens in suggestive\"}, {\"start\": 32.24, \"end\": 34.8, \"text\": \"poses.\"}, {\"start\": 34.8, \"end\": 38.48, \"text\": \"Cruz hasn't seen any of the mail because he doesn't have access to it.\"}, {\"start\": 38.48, \"end\": 46.96, \"text\": \"Unless his lawyers or family tell him, he has no way of knowing these letters exists.\"}]"
  },
  "MKaxL6t-_G8": {
    "video_id": "MKaxL6t-_G8",
    "title": "More companies cutting ties with the NRA (ASL - 2.24.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180224",
    "duration": 102,
    "view_count": 156,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 0.7, \"end\": 6.98, \"text\": \"The number of companies are cutting ties with the National Rifle Association (NRA) continues\"}, {\"start\": 6.98, \"end\": 11.76, \"text\": \"to grow.\"}, {\"start\": 11.769, \"end\": 17.82, \"text\": \"The latest companies are Delta and United Airlines.\"}, {\"start\": 17.82, \"end\": 21.5, \"text\": \"Both companies announced they are no longer offering discounted rates to NRA members and\"}, {\"start\": 21.5, \"end\": 27.7, \"text\": \"Delta has requested that the NRA remove its information from their website.\"}, {\"start\": 27.7, \"end\": 37.58, \"text\": \"\\\"True Car\\\" announced on Twitter that it will end its car buying service relationship with\"}, {\"start\": 37.58, \"end\": 41.66, \"text\": \"the NRA at the end of this month.\"}, {\"start\": 41.7, \"end\": 46.76, \"text\": \"After the school shooting in Florida last week, many people demanded stronger gun laws.\"}, {\"start\": 46.86, \"end\": 55.4, \"text\": \"NRA supporters disagreed. As a result, many companies ended their partnerships with the organization.\"}, {\"start\": 55.46, \"end\": 67.88, \"text\": \"Several rental companies including Enterprise, Hertz and Avis, say they are ending discount\"}, {\"start\": 67.88, \"end\": 70.06, \"text\": \"programs with the NRA.\"}, {\"start\": 70.06, \"end\": 77.16, \"text\": \"Insurance giant MetLife will no longer offer home and auto policy discounts for\"}, {\"start\": 77.16, \"end\": 79.44, \"text\": \"NRA members.\"}, {\"start\": 79.44, \"end\": 89.78, \"text\": \"And the First National Bank of Omaha is pledging to no longer issue NRA-branded Visa cards.\"}, {\"start\": 89.78, \"end\": 98.42, \"text\": \"The bank says it made its decision due to what it called \\\"customer feedback\\\" but did\"}, {\"start\": 98.42, \"end\": 100.82, \"text\": \"not elaborate.\"}]"
  },
  "atbU5JjI8QM": {
    "video_id": "atbU5JjI8QM",
    "title": "Trump calls for rules change to end shutdown (ASL 1.21.18)",
    "channel": "Sign1News",
    "channel_id": "UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "channel_url": "https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuyQHJ4y76-i0w9N33vT-kg",
    "upload_date": "20180122",
    "duration": 72,
    "view_count": 293,
    "description": "Sign1News is the first and only digital network, partnered with world news leader CNN, to offer on-line news and information in American Sign Language. Sign1News provides equal access to local, regional and national news and information to the Deaf and hard-of-hearing community via a daily post-produced broadcast. Sign1News: Your Life. Your Language.",
    "has_captions": true,
    "caption_languages": "ase",
    "caption_timestamps": "[{\"start\": 1.28, \"end\": 8.28, \"text\": \"The House and Senate were back in session today attempting to break an impasse that\"}, {\"start\": 8.28, \"end\": 11.16, \"text\": \"caused federal agencies to shut down.\"}, {\"start\": 11.16, \"end\": 14.68, \"text\": \"And there is no indication lawmakers are any closer to reaching a deal.\"}, {\"start\": 14.68, \"end\": 21.16, \"text\": \"Chamber rules require 60 votes to break the budget impasse and Senate Republicans currently\"}, {\"start\": 21.16, \"end\": 24.74, \"text\": \"have 51 votes.\"}, {\"start\": 24.74, \"end\": 33.6, \"text\": \"President Trump was up and tweeting early Sunday morning.\"}, {\"start\": 33.6, \"end\": 38.56, \"text\": \"He tweeted \\\"Great to see how hard Republicans are fighting for our military and safety at\"}, {\"start\": 38.56, \"end\": 40.08, \"text\": \"the border.\"}, {\"start\": 40.08, \"end\": 46.08, \"text\": \"The Dems just want illegal immigrants to pour into our nation unchecked.\"}, {\"start\": 46.08, \"end\": 63.84, \"text\": \"If stalemate continues, Republicans should go to 51 percent -- \\\"nuclear option\\\" -- and\"}, {\"start\": 63.84, \"end\": 71.04, \"text\": \"vote on real, long-term budget, no C.R.'s.\\\"\"}]"
  }
}